obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (54025)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title extent, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54025&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Code on`
  line `Social Security, 2020.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint; and ^*different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Code and any`
  line `reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Code shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `coming into force of that provision.`
  line
  line `(4) The applicability of the Chapters specified in columns (1) and (2) of the First Schedule shall, without`
  line `prejudice to the applicability of the other provisions of this Code, be such as is specified in corresponding`
  line `entry in column (3) of that Schedule.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4), where it appears to the Central Provident`
  line `Fund Commissioner, whether on an application made to him by the employer of an establishment or`
  line `otherwise, that the employer and majority of employees of that establishment have agreed that the`
  line `provisions of Chapter III should be made applicable to that establishment, the Central Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner, may, by notification, apply the provisions of the said Chapter to that establishment on and`
  line `from the date of such agreement or from any subsequent date specified in the agreement:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the employer of an establishment to which the provisions of Chapter III applied`
  line `under this sub-section desires to come out of such applicability, he may make an application to the Central`
  line `Provident Fund Commissioner and the Central Provident Fund Commissioner shall, if satisfied that there`
  line `is an agreement between the employer and majority of the employees to this effect, make the provisions of`
  line `that Chapter inapplicable to such establishment, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, after giving not less than two months' notice of its intention so to do,`
  line `by notification, apply the provisions of this Code to any establishment employing not less than such number`
  line `of persons as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4), where it appears to the Director General of`
  line `the Corporation, whether on an application made to him by the employer of an establishment or otherwise,`
  line `that the employer and majority of employees of that establishment have agreed that the provisions of`
  line `Chapter IV should be made applicable to that establishment, the Director General of the Corporation, may,`
  line `by notification, apply the provisions of the said Chapter to that establishment on and from the date of such`
  line `agreement or from any subsequent date specified in the agreement:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the employer of an establishment to which the provisions of Chapter IV applied`
  line `under this sub-section desires to come out of such applicability, he may make an application to the Director`
  line `General of the Corporation and Director General of the Corporation shall, if satisfied that there is an agreement between the employer and majority of the employees to this effect, make the provisions of that`
  line `Chapter inapplicable to such establishment, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4), an establishment to which any Chapter`
  line `applies at the first instance shall continue to be applied thereafter even if the number of employees therein`
  line `at any subsequent time falls below the threshold specified in the First Schedule in respect of that Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1*. 3rd May, 2021--- S. 142, vide notification No. S.O. 1730(E), dated 30th April, 2021, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `21st day of November, 2025--- Ss.1 to 14, sub-sections (1) and (2) of section 15, clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 16,`
  line `sections 17 to 141, section 143, except the provisions of the Code specified at serial number (v) of S.O. 2060 (E), dated the 3rd`
  line `May, 2023, sections 144 to 163, Items 1 and 2 and items 4 to 9 of sub-section (1) of section 164, clause (a) and clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (2) and sub-section (3) of section 164, vide notification no. S.O. 5319 (E), dated 21st November, 2025, see Gazette`
  line `of India, Extraordinary, Part II, s. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (54026)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54026&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Code, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(1) "agent" when used in relation to an establishment, means every person, whether appointed as such`
  line `or not, who acting or purporting to act on behalf of the owner, takes part in the management, control,`
  line `supervision or direction of such establishment or part thereof;`
  line
  line `(2) "aggregator" means a digital intermediary or a market place for a buyer or user of a service to`
  line `connect with the seller or the service provider;`
  line
  line `(3) "appropriate" Government means---`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to, an establishment carried on by or under the authority of the Central Government`
  line `or concerning any such controlled industry as may be specified by notification in this behalf, by the`
  line `Central Government or the establishment of railways including metro railways, mines, oil field, major`
  line `ports, air transport service, telecommunication, banking and insurance company or a corporation or`
  line `other authority established by a Central Act or the central public sector undertaking or subsidiary`
  line `companies set up by the central public sector undertakings, subsidiary companies set up by the principal`
  line `undertakings or autonomous bodies owned or controlled by the Central Government, including`
  line `establishment of contractors for the purposes of such establishment, corporation or other authority,`
  line `central public sector undertakings, subsidiary companies or autonomous bodies or any company in`
  line `which not less than fifty-one per cent. of the paid up share capital is held by the Central Government,`
  line `as the case may be, or in relation to an establishment having departments or branches in more than one`
  line `State, as the case may be, the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to any other establishment, the State Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1---.For the purposes of this clause, the expression metro railway means the metro`
  line `railway as defined in sub-clause (i) of clause (1) of section 2 of the Metro Railways (Operation and`
  line `Maintenance ) Act, 2002 (60 of 2002).`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---For the purposes of this clause, the Central Government shall continue to be the`
  line `appropriate Government for the central public sector undertakings even if the holding of the Central`
  line `Government reduces to less than fifty per cent. equity in that public sector undertaking after the`
  line `commencement of this Code;`
  line
  line `(4) "audio-visual production" means audio-visual produced wholly or partly in India and includes---`
  line
  line `(i) animation, cartoon depiction, audio-visual advertisement;`
  line
  line `(ii) digital production or any of the activities in respect of making thereof; and`
  line
  line `(iii) features films, non-feature films, television, web-based serials, talk shows, reality shows and`
  line `sport shows;`
  line
  line `(5) "Authorised Officer" means such officer of the Central Board, or as the case may be, of the`
  line `Corporation notified by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(6) "building or other construction work" means the construction, alteration, repairs, maintenance or`
  line `demolition in relation to buildings, streets, roads, railways, tramways, airfields, irrigation, drainage,`
  line `embankment and navigation works, flood control works (including storm water drainage works),`
  line `generation, transmission and distribution of power, water works (including channels for distribution of`
  line `water), oil and gas installations, electric lines, internet towers, wireless, radio, television, telephone,`
  line `telegraph and overseas communications, dams, canals, reservoirs, watercourses, tunnels, bridges, viaducts,`
  line `aquaducts, pipelines, towers, cooling towers, transmission towers and such other work as may be specified`
  line `in this behalf by the Central Government, by notification, but does not include any building or other construction work which is related to any factory or mine or any building or other construction work`
  line `employing less than ten workers in the preceding twelve months or where such work is related to own`
  line `residential purposes of an individual or group of individuals for their own residence and the total cost of`
  line `such work does not exceed fifty lakhs rupees or such higher amount and employing more than such number`
  line `of workers as may be notified by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(7) "building worker" means a person who is employed to do any skilled, semi-skilled or unskilled,`
  line `manual, technical or clerical work for hire or reward, whether the terms of such employment are express or`
  line `implied, in connection with any building or other construction work, but does not include any such person`
  line `who is employed mainly in a managerial or supervisory or administrative capacity;`
  line
  line `(8) "Building Workers' Welfare Board" means the State Building and other Construction Workers'`
  line `Welfare Board constituted under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(9) career centre means any office (including employment exchange, place or portal) established and`
  line `maintained in the manner prescribed by the Central Government for providing such career services`
  line `(including registration, collection and furnishing of information, either by the keeping of registers or`
  line `otherwise, manually, digitally, virtually or through any other mode) as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government, which may, inter alia, relate generally or specifically to`
  line
  line `(i) persons who seek to employ employees;`
  line
  line `(ii) persons who seek employment;`
  line
  line `(iii) occurrence of vacancies; and`
  line
  line `(iv) persons who seek vocational guidance and career counselling or guidance to start selfemployment;`
  line
  line `(10) "Central Board" means the Board of Trustees of the Employees' Provident Fund constituted under`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(11) "Central Provident Fund Commissioner" means the Central Provident Fund Commissioner of the`
  line `Central Board appointed under sub-section (1) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(12) "child", for the purposes of Chapter VI, includes a stillborn child;`
  line
  line `(13) "Commissioning mother" means a biological mother who uses her egg to create an embryo`
  line `implanted in any other woman;`
  line
  line `(14) "company" means a company as defined in clause (20) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(15) "compensation" means compensation as provided under Chapter VII;`
  line
  line `(16) "competent authority" means any authority appointed under section 58 for the purposes of Chapter`
  line `V or notified for the purposes of Chapter VI or appointed under section 91 for the purposes of Chapter VII,`
  line `as the case may be, as competent authority by the appropriate Government or the State Government, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `(17) "completed year of service" means continuous service for twelve months;`
  line
  line `(18) "confinement" means labour resulting in the issue of a living child, or labour after twenty-six`
  line `weeks of pregnancy resulting in the issue of a child whether alive or dead;`
  line
  line `(19) "contract labour" means a worker who shall be deemed to be employed in or in connection with`
  line `the work of an establishment when he is hired in or in connection with such work by or through a contractor,`
  line `with or without the knowledge of the principal employer and includes inter-State migrant worker but does`
  line `not include an employee (other than part time employee) who is regularly employed by the contractor for`
  line `any activity of his establishment and his employment is governed by mutually accepted standards of the`
  line `conditions of employment (including engagement on permanent basis), and gets periodical increment in the`
  line `pay, social security coverage and other welfare benefits in accordance with the law for the time being in`
  line `force in such employment;`
  line
  line `(20) "contractor", in relation to an establishment means a person, who`
  line
  line `(i) undertakes to produce a given result for the establishment, other than a mere supply of goods or`
  line `articles of manufacture to such establishment through contract labour; or`
  line
  line `(ii) supplies contract labour for any work of the establishment as mere human resource, and includes`
  line `a sub-contractor;`
  line
  line `(21) "contribution" means the sum of money payable by the employer, under this Code, to the Central`
  line `Board and to the Corporation, as the case may be, and includes any amount payable by or on behalf of the`
  line `employee in accordance with the provisions of this Code;`
  line
  line `(22) "Corporation" means the Employees' State Insurance Corporation constituted under section 5;`
  line
  line `(23) delivery means the birth of a child;`
  line
  line `(24) "dependant" means any of the following relatives of deceased employee, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) a widow, a minor legitimate or adopted son, an unmarried legitimate or adopted daughter or a`
  line `widowed mother:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of Chapter IV, a legitimate adopted son, who has not attained the age of`
  line `twenty-five years, shall be dependant of the deceased employee;`
  line
  line `(b) if wholly dependant on the earnings of the employee at the time of his death, a legitimate or adopted`
  line `son or a daughter who has attained the age of eighteen years and who is infirm; except for the purposes of`
  line `Chapter IV wherein the word eighteen occurring in this sub-clause shall be deemed to have been`
  line `substituted by the word twenty-five;`
  line
  line `(c) if wholly or in part dependent on the earnings of the employee at the time of his death,`
  line
  line `(i) a widower;`
  line
  line `(ii) a parent other than a widowed mother;`
  line
  line `(iii) a minor illegitimate son, an unmarried illegitimate daughter or a daughter legitimate or`
  line `illegitimate or adopted if married and a minor or if widowed and a minor;`
  line
  line `(iv) a minor brother or an unmarried sister or a widowed sister if a minor;`
  line
  line `(v) a widowed daughter-in-law;`
  line
  line `(vi) a minor child of a pre-deceased son;`
  line
  line `(vii) a minor child of a pre-deceased daughter where no parent of the child is alive, or;`
  line
  line `(viii) a grandparent if no parent of the employee is alive.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of sub-clause (b) and items (vi) and (vii) of sub-clause (c), references`
  line `to a son, daughter or child include an adopted son, daughter or child, respectively;`
  line
  line `(25) "dock work" means any work in or within the vicinity of any port in connection with, or required`
  line `for, or incidental to, the loading, unloading, movement or storage of cargoes into or from ship or other`
  line `vessel, port, dock, storage place or landing place, and includes`
  line
  line `(i) work in connection with the preparation of ships or other vessels for receipt or discharge of`
  line `cargoes or leaving port;`
  line
  line `(ii) all repairing and maintenance processes connected with any hold, tank structure or lifting`
  line `machinery or any other storage area on board the ship or in the docks; and`
  line
  line `(iii) chipping, painting or cleaning of any hold, tank, structure or lifting machinery or any other`
  line `storage area in board the ship or in the docks;`
  line
  line `(26) "employee" means any person (other than an apprentice engaged under the Apprentices Act, 1961)`
  line `(52 of 1961) employed on wages by an establishment, either directly or through a contractor, to do any`
  line `skilled, semi-skilled or unskilled, manual, operational, supervisory, managerial, administrative, technical,`
  line `clerical or any other work, whether the terms of employment be express or implied, and also includes a`
  line `person declared to be an employee by the appropriate Government, but does not include any member of the`
  line `Armed Forces of the Union:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of Chapter III, except in case of the Employees Provident Fund Scheme`
  line `and Chapter IV, the term employee shall mean such employee drawing wages less than or equal to the`
  line `wage ceiling notified by the Central Government and includes such other persons or class of persons as the`
  line `Central Government may by notification, specify to be employee, for the purposes of those Chapters:`
  line
  line `Provided further that for the purposes of counting of employees for the coverage of an establishment`
  line `under Chapter III and Chapter IV, as the case may be, the employees, whose wages are more than the wage`
  line `ceiling so notified by the Central Government, shall also be taken into account:`
  line
  line `Provided also that for the purposes of Chapter VII, the term employee shall mean only such persons`
  line `as specified in the Second Schedule and such other persons or class of persons as the Central Government,`
  line `or as the case may be, the State Government may add to the said Schedule, by notification, for the purposes`
  line `of that Government;`
  line
  line `(27) "employer" means a person who employs, whether directly or through any person, or on his behalf,`
  line `or on behalf of any person, one or more employees in his establishment and where the establishment is`
  line `carried on by any department of the Central Government or the State Government, the authority specified,`
  line `by the head of such department, in this behalf or where no authority is so specified, the head of the`
  line `department and in relation to an establishment carried on by a local authority, the chief executive of that`
  line `authority, and includes,---`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to an establishment which is a factory, the occupier of the factory;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to mine, the owner of the mine or agent or manager having requisite qualification`
  line `under the law for the time being in force and appointed by the owner or agent of the mine as such;`
  line
  line `(c) in relation to any other establishment, the person who, or the authority which has ultimate`
  line `control over the affairs of the establishment and where the said affairs are entrusted to a manager or`
  line `managing director, such manager or managing director;`
  line
  line `(d) contractor; and`
  line
  line `(e) legal representative of a deceased employer;`
  line
  line `(28) "employment injury" means a personal injury to an employee, caused by accident or an`
  line `occupational disease, as the case may be, arising out of and in the course of his employment,---`
  line
  line `(i) for the purposes of Chapter IV, if the employee is an insured or insurable employee under section`
  line `28 whether such accident occurs or the occupational disease is contracted within or outside the`
  line `territorial limits of India; and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the purposes of Chapter VII, whether such accident occurs or the occupational disease is`
  line `contracted within or outside the territorial limits of India;`
  line
  line `(29) "establishment" means---`
  line
  line `(a) a place where any industry, trade, business, manufacture or occupation is carried on; or`
  line
  line `(b) a factory, motor transport undertaking, newspaper establishment, audiovisual production,`
  line `building and other construction work or plantation; or`
  line
  line `(c) a mine, port or vicinity of port where dock work is carried out.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of Chapter III, where an establishment consists of different`
  line `departments or has branches, whether situate in the same place or in different places, all such departments`
  line `or branches shall be treated as parts of the same establishment;`
  line
  line `(30) "executive officer" means such officer of the appropriate Government as may be notified by that`
  line `Government for the purposes of Chapter XIII or an officer authorised in writing by such executive officer`
  line `to discharge his duties under that Chapter;`
  line
  line `(31) "exempted employee" for the purposes of Chapter III, means an employee to whom any of the`
  line `schemes referred to in section 15, but for the exemption granted under this Code, would have applied and`
  line `for the purposes of Chapter IV, means an employee, whose wage is specified in the notification by the`
  line `Central Government and who is not liable to pay employee's contribution;`
  line
  line `(32) "factory" means any premises including the precincts thereof---`
  line
  line `(a) whereon ten or more employees are working, or were working on any day of the preceding`
  line `twelve months, and in any part of which a manufacturing process is being carried on with the aid of`
  line `power, or is ordinarily so carried on, or`
  line
  line `(b) whereon twenty or more employees are working, or were working on any day of the preceding`
  line `twelve months, and in any part of which a manufacturing process is being carried on without the aid of`
  line `power, or is ordinarily so carried on, but does not include a mine, or a mobile unit belonging to the`
  line `Armed Forces of the Union, railways running shed or a hotel, restaurant or eating place.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---For computing the number of employees for the purposes of this clause, all the`
  line `employees in (different groups and relays) a day shall be taken into account.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---For the purposes of this clause, the mere fact that an Electronic Data Processing Unit`
  line `or a Computer Unit is installed in any premises or part thereof, shall not be construed as factory if no`
  line `manufacturing process is being carried on in such premises or part thereof;`
  line
  line `(33) "family" means all or any of the following relatives of an employee or an unorganised worker, as`
  line `the case may be, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) a spouse;`
  line
  line `(b) a minor legitimate or adopted child dependent upon the employee or an unorganised worker, as`
  line `the case may be;`
  line
  line `(c) a child who is wholly dependent on the earnings of the employee or an unorganised worker, as`
  line `the case may be, and who is---`
  line
  line `(i) receiving education, till he attains the age of twenty-one years; and`
  line
  line `(ii) an unmarried daughter;`
  line
  line `(d) a child who is infirm by reason of any physical or mental abnormality or injury and is wholly`
  line `dependent on the earnings of the employee or an unorganized worker, as the case may be, so long as`
  line `the infirmity continues;`
  line
  line `(e) dependent parents (including father-in-law and mother-in-law of a woman employee), whose`
  line `income from all sources does not exceed such income as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) in case the employee or an unorganised worker, as the case may be, is unmarried and his parents`
  line `are not alive, a minor brother or sister wholly dependent upon the earnings of the Insured Person;`
  line
  line `(34) "fixed term employment" means the engagement of an employee on the basis of a written contract`
  line `of employment for a fixed period:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) his hours of work, wages, allowances and other benefits shall not be lessthan that of a permanent`
  line `employee doing the same work or work of a similar nature; and`
  line
  line `(b) he shall be eligible for all benefits, under any law for the time being in force, available to a`
  line `permanent employee proportionately according to the period of service rendered by him even if his`
  line `period of employment does not extend to the required qualifying period of employment;`
  line
  line `(35) "gig worker" means a person who performs work or participates in a work arrangement and earns`
  line `from such activities outside of traditional employer-employee relationship;`
  line
  line `(36) "home-based worker" means a person engaged in, the production of goods or services for an`
  line `employer in his home or other premises of his choice other than the workplace of the employer, for`
  line `remuneration, irrespective of whether or not the employer provides the equipment, materials or other inputs;`
  line
  line `(37)" Inspector-cum-Facilitator" means an Inspector-cum-Facilitator appointed under section 122;`
  line
  line `(38) "Insurance Fund" means the Deposit-Linked Insurance Fund established under clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(39) "Insured Person" means the Insured Person referred to in section 28;`
  line
  line `(40) "Insurance Scheme" means the Deposit-Linked Insurance Scheme framed under clause (c) of subsection (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(41) "inter-State migrant worker" means a person who is employed in an establishment and who`
  line
  line `(i) has been recruited directly by the employer or indirectly through contractor in one State for`
  line `employment in such establishment situated in another State; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has come on his own from one State and obtained employment in an establishment of another`
  line `State (hereinafter called destination State) or has subsequently changed the establishment within the`
  line `destination State, under an agreement or other arrangement for such employment and drawing wages`
  line `not exceeding eighteen thousand rupees per month or such higher amount as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(42) "manufacturing process" means any process for---`
  line
  line `(i) making, altering, repairing, ornamenting,`
  line `finishing, oiling, washing, cleaning, breaking up, demolishing, refining, or otherwise treating or adapting`
  line `any article or substance with a view to its use, sale, transport, delivery or disposal; or`
  line
  line `(ii) pumping oil, water, sewage or any other substance; or`
  line
  line `(iii) generating, transforming or transmitting power; or`
  line
  line `(iv) composing, offset printing, printing by letter press, lithography, photogravure screen printing,`
  line `three or four dimensional printing, prototyping, flexography or other types of printing process or book`
  line `binding; or`
  line
  line `(v) constructing, reconstructing, repairing, refitting, finishing or breaking up ships or vessels; or`
  line
  line `(vi) preserving or storing any article in cold storage; or`
  line
  line `(vii) such other activities as the Central Government may notify;`
  line
  line `(43) "maternity benefit", in respect of Chapter VI, means the payment referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 60;`
  line
  line `(44) "medical practitioner" means a person registered under any law for the time being in force, or, any`
  line `person declared by the State Government, by notification, to be qualified as medical practitioner for the`
  line `purposes of this Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that different class or classes of medical practitioner having specific qualification may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government for the purposes of Chapter IV and by the appropriate Government for`
  line `other Chapters of this Code;`
  line
  line `(45) "medical termination of pregnancy" means the termination of pregnancy permissible under the`
  line `provisions of the Medical Termination of Pregnancy Act, 1971 (34 of 1971);`
  line
  line `(46) "mine" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (j) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the`
  line `Mines Act, 1952 (35 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(47) "minor" means a person who has not attained the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `(48)" miscarriage" means expulsion of the contents of a pregnant uterus at any period prior to or during`
  line `the twenty-sixth week of pregnancy, but does not include any miscarriage, the causing of which is`
  line `punishable under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(49) "National Social Security Board" means the National Social Security Board for Unorganised`
  line `Workers constituted under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(50) "notification" means a notification published in the Gazette of India or the Official Gazette of a`
  line `State, as the case may be, and the expression notify with its grammatical variations and cognate`
  line `expressions shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(51) "occupational disease" means a disease specified in the Third Schedule as a disease peculiar to the`
  line `employment of the employee;`
  line
  line `(52) "occupier in respect of a factory" means the person who has ultimate control over the affairs of`
  line `the factory:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a firm or other association of individuals, any one of the individual partners or`
  line `members thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a company, any one of the directors, except any independent director within the`
  line `meaning of sub-section (6) of section 149 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a factory owned or controlled by the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government, or any local authority, the person or persons appointed to manage the affairs of the factory`
  line `by the Central Government, the State Government or the local authority or such other authority as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be the occupier:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of a ship which is being repaired, or on which maintenance work is`
  line `being carried out, in a dry dock which is available for hire, the owner of the dock shall be deemed to be the`
  line `occupier for all purposes except the matters as may be prescribed by the Central Government which are`
  line `directly related to the condition of ship for which the owner of ship shall be deemed to be the occupier;`
  line
  line `(53) "oilfield" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (e) of section 3 of the Oilfields (Regulation`
  line `and Development) Act, 1948 (53 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(54) "organised sector" means an enterprise which is not an unorganised sector;`
  line
  line `(55) "permanent partial disablement" means, where the disablement is of a permanent nature, such`
  line `disablement as reduces the earning capacity of an employee in every employment which he was capable of`
  line `undertaking at the time of the accident resulting in the disablement:`
  line
  line `Provided that every injury specified in Part II of the Fourth Schedule shall be deemed to result in`
  line `permanent partial disablement;`
  line
  line `(56) "permanent total disablement" means such disablement of a permanent nature as incapacitates an`
  line `employee for all work which he was capable of performing at the time of the accident resulting in such`
  line `disablement:`
  line
  line `Provided that permanent total disablement shall be deemed to result from every injury specified in Part`
  line `I of the Fourth Schedule or from any combination of injuries specified in Part II thereof where the aggregate`
  line `percentage of the loss of earning capacity, as specified in the said Part II against those injuries, amounts to`
  line `one hundred per cent.;`
  line
  line `(57) "Pension Fund" means the Pension Fund established under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section`
  line 16;
  line
  line `(58) "Pension Scheme" means the Employees' Pension Scheme framed under clause (b) of sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(59) plantation means---`
  line
  line `(a) any land used or intended to be used for`
  line
  line `(i) growing tea, coffee, rubber, cinchona or cardamom which admeasures five hectares or more;`
  line
  line `(ii) growing any other plant, which admeasures five hectares or more and in which ten or more`
  line `persons are employed or were employed on any day of the preceding twelve months, if, after`
  line `obtaining the approval of the Central Government, the State Government, by notification, so`
  line directs.
  line
  line `Explanation.---Where any piece of land used for growing any plant referred to in this sub-clause`
  line `admeasures less than five hectares and is contiguous to any other piece of land not being so used, but`
  line `capable of being so used, and both such pieces of land are under the management of the same employer,`
  line `then, for the purposes of this sub-clause, the piece of land first mentioned shall be deemed to be a plantation,`
  line `if the total area of both such pieces of land admeasures five hectares or more;`
  line
  line `(b) any land which the State Government may, by notification, declare and which is used or`
  line `intended to be used for growing any plant referred to in sub-clause (a), notwithstanding that it`
  line `admeasures less than five hectares:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such declaration shall be made in respect of such land which admeasures less than five`
  line `hectares immediately before the commencement of this Code; and`
  line
  line `(c) offices, hospitals, dispensaries, schools and any other premises used for any purpose connected with`
  line `any plantation within the meaning of sub-clause (a) and sub-clause (b); but does not include factory on the`
  line premises;
  line
  line `(60) "platform work" means a work arrangement outside of a traditional employer employee`
  line `relationship in which organisations or individuals use an online platform to access other organisations or`
  line `individuals to solve specific problems or to provide specific services or any such other activities which may`
  line `be notified by the Central Government, in exchange for payment;`
  line
  line `(61) "platform worker" means a person engaged in or undertaking platform work;`
  line `(62) "port" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (4) of section 3 of the Indian Ports Act, 1908`
  line `(15 of 1908);`
  line
  line `(63) "Provident Fund" means the Employees' Provident Fund established under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(64) "Provident Fund Scheme" means the Employees' Provident Fund Scheme framed under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(65) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Code;`
  line
  line `(66) "railway" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (31) of section 2 of the Railways Act,`
  line `1989 (24 of 1989);`
  line
  line `(67) "railway company" includes any persons whether incorporated or not, who are owners or lessees`
  line `of a railway or parties to an agreement for working a railway;`
  line
  line `(68) "Recovery Officer" means any officer of the Central Government, the State Government, the`
  line `Central Board or the Corporation, who may be authorised by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, by notification, to discharge the functions and to exercise the powers of a`
  line `Recovery Officer under this Code;`
  line
  line `(69) "regulations" means regulations made by the Corporation under this Code;`
  line
  line `(70) "retirement" means termination of the service of an employee otherwise than on superannuation;`
  line
  line `(71) "sales promotion employees" means the sales promotion employees as defined in clause (d) of`
  line `section 2 of the Sales Promotion Employees (Conditions of Service) Act, 1976 (11 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(72) "Schedule" means a Schedule to this Code;`
  line
  line `(73) "seamen" means any person forming part of the crew of any ship, but does not include the master`
  line `of the ship;`
  line
  line `(74) "seasonal factory" means a factory which is exclusively engaged in one or more of the following`
  line `manufacturing processes, namely, cotton ginning, cotton or jute pressing, decortication of ground-nuts, the manufacture of indigo, lac, sugar (including gur) or any manufacturing process which is incidental to or`
  line `connected with any of the aforesaid processes and includes a factory which is engaged for a period not`
  line `exceeding seven months in a year in a manufacturing process as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(75) "self-employed worker" means any person who is not employed by an employer, but engages`
  line `himself in any occupation in the unorganised sector subject to a monthly earning of an amount as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, from time to time or holds`
  line `cultivable land subject to such ceiling as may be notified by the State Government;`
  line
  line `(76)" shop", in respect of a State, means a shop as defined in any law for the time being in force dealing`
  line `with the shop in that State;`
  line
  line `(77) "sickness" means a condition which requires medical treatment and attendance and necessitates`
  line `abstention from work on medical ground;`
  line
  line `(78) "social security" means the measures of protection afforded to employees, unorganised workers,`
  line `gig workers and platform workers to ensure access to health care and to provide income security,`
  line `particularly in cases of old age, unemployment, sickness, invalidity, work injury, maternity or loss of a`
  line `breadwinner by means of rights conferred on them and schemes framed, under this Code;`
  line
  line `(79) "Social Security Organisation" means any of the following organisations established under this`
  line `Code, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Board of Trustees of Employees' Provident Fund constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the Employees' State Insurance Corporation constituted under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the National Social Security Board for Unorganised Workers constituted under section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the State Unorganised Workers' Social Security Board constituted under section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the State Building and other Construction Workers' Welfare Boards constituted under section`
  line `7; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other organisation or special purpose vehicle declared to be the social security organisation`
  line `by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(80) "State Government" includes---`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to a Union territory with legislature, the Government of the Union territory; and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to a Union territory without legislature, the administrator appointed under article 239`
  line `of the Constitution as an administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `(81) "State Unorganised Workers' Board" means the State Unorganised Workers' Social Security Board`
  line `constituted under sub-section (9) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(82) "superannuation", in relation to an employee, means the attainment by the employee of such age`
  line `as is fixed in the contract or conditions of service, as the age on the attainment of which the employee shall`
  line `vacate the employment:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of Chapter III, the age of superannuation shall be fifty-eight years;`
  line
  line `(83) "temporary disablement" means a condition resulting from an employment injury which requires`
  line `medical treatment and renders an employee, as a result of such injury, temporarily incapable of doing the`
  line `work which he was doing prior to or at the time of the injury;`
  line
  line `(84) "Tribunal" means the Industrial Tribunal constituted by the appropriate Government under section`
  line `7A of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947);`
  line
  line `(85) "unorganised" sector means an enterprise owned by individuals or self-employed workers and`
  line `engaged in the production or sale of goods or providing service of any kind whatsoever, and where the`
  line `enterprise employs workers, the number of such workers is less than ten;`
  line
  line `(86) "unorganised worker" means a home-based worker, self-employed worker or a wage worker in`
  line `the unorganised sector and includes a worker in the organised sector who is not covered by the Industrial`
  line `Disputes Act, 1947 or Chapters III to VII of this Code;`
  line
  line `(87) "vacancy", for the purposes of Chapter XIII, means an unoccupied post (including newly created`
  line `post, post of trainee, post to be filled through apprentice or any unoccupied post created in an establishment`
  line `by any other means) in a cadre or occupation for the purpose of employing a person and carrying`
  line remuneration;
  line
  line `(88) "wages" means all remuneration, whether by way of salaries, allowances or otherwise, expressed`
  line `in terms of money or capable of being so expressed which would, if the terms of employment, express or`
  line `implied, were fulfilled, be payable to a person employed in respect of his employment or of work done in`
  line `such employment, and includes,---`
  line
  line `(a) basic pay;`
  line
  line `(b) dearness allowance; and`
  line
  line `(c) retaining allowance, if any,`
  line
  line `but does not include---`
  line
  line `(a) any bonus payable under any law for the time being in force, which does not form part of the`
  line `remuneration payable under the terms of employment;`
  line
  line `(b) the value of any house-accommodation, or of the supply of light, water, medical attendance or other`
  line `amenity or of any service excluded from the computation of wages by a general or special order of the`
  line `appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(c) any contribution paid by the employer to any pension or provident fund, and the interest which may`
  line `have accrued thereon;`
  line
  line `(d) any conveyance allowance or the value of any travelling concession;`
  line
  line `(e) any sum paid to the employed person to defray special expenses entailed on him by the nature of`
  line `his employment;`
  line
  line `(f) house rent allowance;`
  line
  line `(g) remuneration payable under any award or settlement between the parties or order of a court or`
  line Tribunal;
  line
  line `(h) any overtime allowance;`
  line
  line `(i) any commission payable to the employee;`
  line
  line `(j) any gratuity payable on the termination of employment;`
  line
  line `(k) any retrenchment compensation or other retirement benefit payable to the employee or any`
  line `ex gratia payment made to him on the termination of employment, under any law for the time being in`
  line `force:`
  line
  line `Provided that for calculating the wages under this clause, if payments made by the employer to the`
  line `employee under sub-clauses (a) to (i) exceeds one-half, or such other per cent. as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government, of the all remuneration calculated under this clause, the amount which exceeds such`
  line `one-half, or the per cent. so notified, shall be deemed as remuneration and shall be accordingly added in`
  line `wages under this clause:`
  line
  line `Provided further that for the purpose of equal wages to all genders and for the purpose of payment of`
  line `wages, the emoluments specified in sub-clauses (d), (f), (g) and (h) shall be taken for computation of wage.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---Where an employee is given in lieu of the whole or part of the wages payable to him,`
  line `any remuneration in kind by his employer, the value of such remuneration in kind which does not exceed`
  line `fifteen per cent. of the total wages payable to him, shall be deemed to form part of the wages of such`
  line employee;
  line
  line `(89) "wage ceiling" means such amount of wages as may be notified by the Central Government, for`
  line `the purposes of becoming a member under Chapter III and Chapter IV;`
  line
  line `(90) "wage worker" means a person employed for remuneration in the unorganized sector, directly by`
  line `an employer or through any contractor, irrespective of place of work, whether exclusively for one employer`
  line `or for one or more employers, whether in cash or in kind, whether as a home-based worker, or as a temporary`
  line `or casual worker, or as a migrant worker, or workers employed by households including domestic workers,`
  line `with a monthly wage of an amount as may be notified by the Central Government and the State Government,`
  line `as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(91)" woman" means a woman employed, whether directly or through any contractor, for wages in any`
  line `establishment:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purposes of Chapter IV, a woman who is or was an employee in respect of whom`
  line `contribution is or were payable under the said Chapter and who is by reason thereof, entitled to any of the`
  line `benefits provided under the said Chapter shall be called insured woman and shall include`
  line
  line `(i) a commissioning mother who as biological mother wishes to have a child and prefers to get`
  line `embryo implanted in any other woman;`
  line
  line `(ii) a woman who legally adopts a child of up to three months of age.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (54027)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Registration and cancellation of an establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54027&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every establishment to which this Code`
  line `applies shall be electronically or otherwise, registered within such time and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the establishment which is already registered under any other Central labour law for the`
  line `time being in force shall not be required to obtain registration again under this Code and such registration`
  line `shall be deemed to be registration for the purposes of this Code:`
  line
  line `(2) Any establishment to which Chapter III or Chapter IV applies, and whose business activities are in`
  line `the process of closure, may make an application for cancellation of registration granted under this section.`
  line
  line `(3) The manner of making application for cancellation of the registration under sub-section (2), the`
  line `conditions subject to which the registration shall be cancelled and the procedure of cancellation and other`
  line `matters relating thereto, shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (54028)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of Board of Trustees of Employees’ Provident Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54028&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, constitute, with effect from such date as may be specified therein, a Board of Trustees`
  line `of the Employees' Provident Fund to be called the Central Board, for the purposes of Chapter III and the`
  line `provisions of this Code relating to that Chapter, for the administration of the funds vested in it in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government, consisting of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson and a Vice-Chairperson to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) not more than five persons appointed by the Central Government from amongst its officials;`
  line
  line `(c) not more than fifteen persons representing Governments of such States asthe Central Government`
  line `may specify in this behalf, to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) ten persons representing employers of the establishments to which the schemes referred to in sub`
  line `section (1) of section 15 applies, to be appointed by the Central Government after consultation with such`
  line `organisations of employers as may be recognised by the Central Government in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(e) ten persons representing employees in the establishments to which schemes referred to in subsection (1) of section 15 applies, who shall be appointed by the Central Government after consultation`
  line `with such organisations of employees as may be recognised by that Government in this behalf; and`
  line
  line `(f) the Central Provident Fund Commissioner, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Board shall be a body corporate by the name of Board of Trustees of the Employees'`
  line `Provident Fund, having perpetual succession and a common seal and shall by the said name sue and be`
  line sued.
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, constitute, with effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified therein, an Executive Committee from amongst the members of the Central Board to assist the`
  line `Central Board in performance of its functions in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) The Central Board may, by order, constitute one or more committees of such composition as may be`
  line `specified in the order to assist it in the discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Board may, by order, delegate to its Chairperson or to its Executive Committee or to`
  line `any of its officers and a State Board constituted under section 12 may, by order, delegate to its Chairperson`
  line `or to any of its officers, subject to such conditions and limitations, if any, as it may specify in such order,`
  line `such of its powers and functions under this Code as it may deem necessary for efficient administration of`
  line `the schemes referred to in sub-section (1) of section 15.`
  line
  line `(6) The terms and conditions, including tenure of office, subject to which a member of the Central Board`
  line `and Executive Committee shall discharge their respective duties may be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member of the Central Board shall, notwithstanding the expiry of the tenure of his office,`
  line `continue to hold office until his successor is appointed.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Board, apart from the functions specified in this Code, shall also perform such other`
  line `functions in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (54029)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of Employees’ State Insurance Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54029&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, constitute with effect from such date as may be specified therein, the Employees' State`
  line `Insurance Corporation to be called the Corporation, for the purposes of Chapter IV and the provisions of`
  line `this Code relating to that Chapter and the administration thereof, in such manner as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government, consisting of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) a Vice-Chairperson to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) not more than five persons to be appointed by the Central Government from amongst its officials;`
  line
  line `(d) one person representing each of such States in such manner, as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(e) one person to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the Union territories;`
  line
  line `(f) ten persons representing employers to be appointed by the Central Government in consultation`
  line `with such organisations of employers as may be recognised for the purpose by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(g) ten persons representing employees to be appointed by the Central Government in consultation`
  line `with such organisations of employees as may be recognised for the purpose by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) two persons representing the medical profession to be appointed by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with such organisations of medical practitioners as may be recognised for the purpose by`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(i) three members of Parliament of whom two shall be members of the House of the People (Lok`
  line `Sabha) and one shall be a member of the Council of States (Rajya Sabha) elected respectively by the`
  line `members of the House of the People and the members of the Council of States; and`
  line `(j) the Director General of the Corporation, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation shall be a body corporate by the name of Employees' State Insurance Corporation,`
  line `having perpetual succession and a common seal and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, constitute, with effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified therein, a Standing Committee from amongst the members of the Corporation, in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the general superintendence and control of the Corporation, the Standing Committee—`
  line
  line `(a) shall administer the affairs of the Corporation and may exercise any of the powers and perform`
  line `any of the functions of the Corporation in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) shall submit for the consideration and decision of the Corporation all such cases and matters as`
  line `may be specified in the regulations made in this behalf; and`
  line
  line `(c) may, in its discretion, submit any other case or matter for the decision of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(5) (a) The Central Government may, by notification, constitute, with effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified therein, a Medical Benefit Committee of such composition as may be specified therein, to assist`
  line `the Corporation and the Standing Committee in performance of its functions relating to administration of`
  line `medical benefits.`
  line
  line `(b) the Medical Benefit Committee shall perform such duties and exercise such powers as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Corporation may, by order, constitute one or more committees of such composition as may be`
  line `specified in the regulations to assist it in the discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(7) The terms and conditions, including tenure of office, subject to which a member of the Corporation`
  line `and Standing Committee shall discharge their respective duties may be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member of the Corporation shall, notwithstanding the expiry of the tenure of his office,`
  line `continue to hold office until his successor is appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (54030)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `National Social Security Board and State Unorganised Workers’ Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54030&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification, constitute a National Social Security Board for unorganised workers to`
  line `exercise the powers conferred on, and to perform the functions assigned to, it under this Code, in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Social Security Board shall consist of the following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) Union Minister for Labour and Employment as Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Secretary, Ministry of Labour and Employment as Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) forty members to be nominated by the Central Government, out of whom---`
  line
  line `(i) seven members representing unorganised sector workers;`
  line
  line `(ii) seven members representing employers of unorganised sector;`
  line
  line `(iii) seven members representing eminent persons from civil society;`
  line
  line `(iv) two members representing the Lok Sabha and one from the Rajya Sabha;`
  line
  line `(v) ten members representing Central Government Ministries and Departments concerned;`
  line
  line `(vi) five members representing State Governments;`
  line
  line `(vii) one member representing the Union territories; and`
  line
  line `(d) the Director General Labour Welfare, as Member-Secretary, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) All members except Chairperson of the National Social Security Board shall be from amongst`
  line `persons of eminence in the fields of labour welfare, management, finance, law and administration.`
  line
  line `(4) The manner in which members shall be nominated from each of the categories specified in clause`
  line `(c) of sub-section (2), the term of office and other conditions of service of members, the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions by, and the manner of filling vacancies among the members of,`
  line `the National Social Security Board shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that adequate representation shall be given to persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes, the minorities and women.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of the National Social Security Board shall be three years.`
  line
  line `(6) The National Social Security Board shall meet at least thrice a year, at such time and place and shall`
  line `observe such rules of procedure relating to the transaction of business at its meetings, as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The National Social Security Board shall perform the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) recommend to the Central Government for framing suitable schemes for different sections of`
  line `unorganised workers, gig workers and platform workers;`
  line
  line `(b) advise the Central Government on such matters arising out of the administration of this Code as`
  line `may be referred to it;`
  line
  line `(c) monitor such social welfare schemes for unorganised workers, gig workers and platform workers`
  line `as are administered by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) review the record keeping functions performed at the State level;`
  line `(e) review the expenditure from the fund and account; and`
  line
  line `(f) undertake such other functions as are assigned to it by the Central Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government may, by notification, constitute with effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified therein one or more advisory committee to advise the Central Government upon such matters`
  line `arising out of the administration of this Code relating to unorganised workers and such other matters as the`
  line `Central Government may refer to it for advice.`
  line
  line `(9) Every State Government shall, by notification, constitute a State Board to be known as (name of the`
  line `State) Unorganised Workers' Social Security Board to exercise the powers conferred on, and to perform the`
  line `functions assigned to, it under this Code, in such manner as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(10) Every State Unorganised Workers' Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Minister of Labour and Employment of the concerned State as Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) Principal Secretary or Secretary (Labour) as Vice-Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(c) one member representing the Central Government in the Ministry of Labour and Employment;`
  line
  line `(d) thirty-one members to be nominated by the State Government, out of whom`
  line
  line `(i) seven representing the unorganised workers;`
  line
  line `(ii) seven representing employers of unorganised workers;`
  line
  line `(iii) two members representing the Legislative Assembly of the concerned State;`
  line
  line `(iv) five members representing eminent persons from civil society;`
  line
  line `(v) ten members representing the State Government Departments concerned; and`
  line
  line `(e) Member-Secretary as notified by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(11) All members except Chairperson of the State Unorganised Workers' Board shall be from amongst`
  line `persons of eminence in the fields of labour welfare, management, finance, law and administration.`
  line
  line `(12) The manner in which members shall be nominated from each of the categories specified in clause`
  line `(d) of sub-section (10), the term of office and other conditions of service of members, the procedure to be`
  line `followed in the discharge of their functions by, and the manner of filling vacancies among the members of,`
  line `the State Unorganised Workers' Board shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that adequate representation shall be given to persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes, the minorities and women.`
  line
  line `(13) The term of the State Unorganised Workers' Board shall be three years.`
  line
  line `(14) The State Unorganised Workers' Board shall meet at least once in a quarter at such time and place`
  line `and shall observe such rules of procedure relating to the transaction of business at its meetings, as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(15) The State Board shall perform the following functions, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) recommend the State Government for framing suitable schemes for different sections of the`
  line `unorganised sector workers;`
  line
  line `(b) advise the State Government on such matters arising out of the administration of this Code as`
  line `may be referred to it;`
  line
  line `(c) monitor such social welfare schemes for unorganised workers as are administered by the State`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(d) review the record keeping functions performed at the district level;`
  line
  line `(e) review the progress of registration and issue of cards to unorganised sector workers;`
  line
  line `(f) review the expenditure from the funds under various schemes; and`
  line
  line `(g) undertake such other functions as are assigned to it by the State Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(16) The State Government may, by notification, constitute with effect from such date as may be`
  line `specified therein, one or more advisory committee to advise the State Government upon such matters arising`
  line `out of the administration of this Code relating to unorganised workers and such other matters as the State`
  line `Government may refer to it for advice.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (54031)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Constitution of State Building Workers’ Welfare Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54031&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall,`
  line `with effect from such date as it may, by notification, appoint, constitute a Board to be known as`
  line `the................(name of the State) Building and Other Construction Workers' Welfare Board to exercise the`
  line `powers conferred on, and perform the functions assigned to, it under this section and Chapter VIII.`
  line
  line `(2) The Building Workers' Welfare Board shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having`
  line `perpetual succession and a common seal and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Building Workers' Welfare Board shall consist of a chairperson to be nominated by the State`
  line `Government, one member to be nominated by the Central Government and such number of other members,`
  line `not exceeding fifteen, as may be appointed to it by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Building Workers' Welfare Board shall include an equal number of members`
  line `representing the State Government, the employers and the building workers and that at least one member`
  line `of the Board shall be a woman.`
  line
  line `(4) The terms and conditions of appointment and the salaries and other allowances payable to the`
  line `chairperson and the other members of the Building Workers' Welfare Board, and the manner of filling of`
  line `casual vacancies of the members of the Building Workers' Welfare Board, shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) (a) The Building Workers' Welfare Board shall appoint a Secretary and such officers and employees`
  line `as it considers necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions under this Code.`
  line
  line `(b) The Secretary of the Building Workers' Welfare Board shall be its chief executive officer.`
  line
  line `(c) The terms and conditions of appointment and the salary and allowances payable to the Secretary and`
  line `the other officers and employees of the Building Workers' Welfare Board shall be such as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Building Workers' Welfare Board shall perform the following functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) provide death and disability benefits to a beneficiary or his dependants;`
  line
  line `(b) make payment of pension to the beneficiaries who have completed the age of sixty years;`
  line
  line `(c) pay such amount in connection with premium for Group Insurance Scheme of the beneficiaries`
  line `as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(d) frame educational schemes for the benefit of children of the beneficiaries as may be prescribed`
  line `by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(e) meet such medical expenses for treatment of major ailments of a beneficiary or, such dependant,`
  line `as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(f) make payment of maternity benefit to the beneficiaries;`
  line
  line `(g) frame skill development and awareness schemes for the beneficiaries;`
  line
  line `(h) provide transit accommodation or hostel facility to the beneficiaries;`
  line
  line `(i) formulation of any other welfare scheme for the building worker beneficiaries by State`
  line `Government in concurrence with the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(j) make provision and improvement of such other welfare measures and facilities as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The State Government may, by notification, constitute with effect from such date as may be specified`
  line `therein one or more advisory committee to advise the State Government upon such matters arising out of`
  line `the administration of this Code relating to building workers and such other matters as the State Government`
  line `may refer to it for advice.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (54032)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Disqualification and removal of a member of any Social Security Organisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54032&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person`
  line `shall be chosen as, or continue to be, a member of a Social Security Organisation, or any Committee thereof`
  line who,---
  line
  line `(a) is or at any time has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) is found to be a lunatic or becomes of unsound mind; or`
  line
  line `(c) is or has been convicted of any offence involving moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(d) is an employer in an establishment and has defaulted in the payment of any dues under this Code;`
  line
  line `(e) is a member of a Social Security Organisation being a member of the Parliament or a member of`
  line `a State Legislative Assembly, when he ceases to be such member of the Parliament or State Legislative`
  line `Assembly, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(f) is a member of Social Security Organisation being a member of the Parliament or a member of a`
  line `State Legislative Assembly, and he becomes a---`
  line
  line `(i) Minister of Central or State Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) Speaker or Deputy Speaker of House of the People or a State Legislative Assembly; or`
  line
  line `(iii) Deputy Chairman of the Council of States.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--- If any question arises whether any person is disqualified under clause (d), it shall be`
  line `referred to the appropriate Government and the decision of the appropriate Government on any such`
  line `question shall be final.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- Clause (f) shall not apply in case of persons who are members of the Social Security`
  line `Organisation ex officio, by virtue of being a Minister.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government, in case of the Central Board, the Corporation and the National Social`
  line `Security Board and the State Government in case of the State Unorganised Workers' Board and the Building`
  line `Workers' Welfare Board, may remove any member of such Social Security Organisation from his office,`
  line who,---
  line
  line `(a) is or has become subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in sub-section (1); or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the Social Security Organisation of which he is a member for more`
  line `than three consecutive meetings of the Social Security Organisation or a Committee thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) in the opinion of such Government, has so abused the position of his office as to render that`
  line `member's continuation in the office detrimental to the public interest or is otherwise unfit or unsuitable`
  line `to continue as such member in the opinion of such Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be removed under clauses (b) and (c), unless that person has been given`
  line `an opportunity to show cause as to why he should not be removed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a member of the Executive Committee of the Central Board or the Standing`
  line `Committee of the Corporation shall cease to hold office if he ceases to be a member of the Central Board`
  line `or the Corporation, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Any member of a Social Security Organisation or a Committee thereof may at any time resign from`
  line `his office in writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government or the State Government, as the`
  line `case may be, which had made his appointment and on acceptance of such resignation, his office shall`
  line `become vacant.`
  line
  line `(4) If in a Social Security Organisation or a Committee thereof, the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, is of the opinion that---`
  line
  line `(a) any member thereof representing employers or the employees or the unorganised workers, as the`
  line `case may be, ceases to adequately represent so; or`
  line
  line `(b) any member thereof representing to be an expert in a specified area, is later on found not to`
  line `possess sufficient expertise in that area; or`
  line
  line `(c) having regard to exigencies of circumstances or services in such Government, the member thereof`
  line `representing such Government cannot continue to represent the Government, then, such Government`
  line `may, by order, remove such member from his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be removed under clause (a) or clause (b), unless that person has been`
  line `given an opportunity to show cause as to why he should not be removed.`
  line
  line `(5) If any member of a Social Security Organisation or a Committee thereof, who is a director of a`
  line `company and who as such director, has any direct or indirect pecuniary interest in any matter coming up`
  line `for consideration of the Social Security Organisation or a Committee thereof, then, he shall, as soon as may`
  line `be possible after such fact of interest has come to his knowledge, disclose the nature of the interest and such`
  line `disclosure shall be recorded in the proceedings of the Social Security Organisation or the Committee`
  line `thereof, as the case may be, and such member, thereafter, shall not take part in any proceeding or decision`
  line `of the Social Security Organisation, or a Committee thereof relating to that matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (54033)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Procedure for transaction of business of Social Security Organisation, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54033&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `A Social Security`
  line `Organisation or any Committee thereof shall meet at such intervals and observe such procedure in regard`
  line `to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at such meetings) as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) All orders and decisions of the Social Security Organisation shall be authenticated by the Central`
  line `Provident Fund Commissioner, Director General, Director General Labour Welfare, State Principal`
  line `Secretary or Secretary (Labour) of the respective Social Security Organisations or such other officer as may`
  line `be notified by the appropriate Government and all other instruments issued by the Social Security`
  line `Organisation shall be authenticated by the signature of such officer as may be authorised by an order by the`
  line `respective Social Security Organisations.`
  line
  line `(3) No act done or proceeding taken by a Social Security Organisation or any Committee thereof shall`
  line `be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of`
  line `the Social Security Organisation or the Committee thereof, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Such members of a Social Security Organisation or any Committee thereof shall be entitled for such`
  line `fee and allowances as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (54034)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Executive Heads of Central Board and Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54034&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Central Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner and the Director General shall be the whole-time officer of the Central Board and the`
  line `Corporation, respectively, and such officer shall not undertake any work unconnected with his office`
  line `without the prior approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (54433)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Supersession of Corporation, Central Board, National Social Security Board or State Unorganised Workers’ Board or the Building Workers’ Welfare Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54433&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central`
  line `Government in case of the Central Board, the Corporation or the National Social Security Board and the`
  line `State Government, in case of the State Unorganised Workers' Board or the Building Workers' Welfare`
  line `Board, is of the opinion that the Corporation or the Central Board or the National Social Security Board or`
  line `the State Unorganised Workers Board or the Building Workers' Welfare Board or any of the Committee`
  line `thereof, as the case may be, is unable to perform its functions, or, has persistently made delay in the`
  line `discharge of its functions or has exceeded or abused its powers or jurisdiction, then such Government may,`
  line `by notification, supersede the Corporation or the Central Board or the National Social Security Board or`
  line `the State Unorganised Workers' Board or the Building Workers Welfare Board, or any of the Committees`
  line `thereof, as the case may be, and reconstitute it in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that, before issuing a notification under this sub-section on any of the grounds specified`
  line `herein, such Government shall give an opportunity to the Corporation or the Central Board or the National`
  line `Social Security Board or the State Unorganised Workers Board or the Building Workers' Welfare Board`
  line `or any Committee thereof, as the case may be, to show cause as to why it should not be superseded and`
  line `shall consider the explanations and objections raised by it and take appropriate action thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) After the supersession of the Corporation, or the Central Board or the National Social Security`
  line `Board, the State Unorganised Workers Board or the Building Workers Welfare Board, or any of the`
  line `Committee thereof, as the case may be, and until it is reconstituted, the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, shall make such alternate arrangements for the purpose of administration`
  line `of the relevant provisions of this Code, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall cause, a full report of`
  line `any action taken by it under this section and the circumstances leading to such action, to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament or the State Legislature, as the case may be, at the earliest opportunity and in any case`
  line `not later than three months from the date of the notification of supersession issued under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (54036)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `State Board, Regional Boards, local committees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54036&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line notification,—
  line
  line `(i) after consultation with the Government of any State, constitute for that State, a Board of Trustees`
  line `(hereinafter in this Code referred to as a State Board) which shall exercise such powers and perform`
  line `such functions as may be assigned by notification, to it by the Central Government from time to time;`
  line
  line `(ii) specify the manner of constitution of a State Board, the terms and conditions of the appointment`
  line `of its members and the procedure of its meeting and other proceedings relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation may, by order, appoint Regional Boards and local committees in such area and in`
  line `such manner to perform such functions and to exercise such powers as may be specified in the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (54037)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Entrustment of additional functions to Social Security Organisations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54037&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in this Code, the Central Government may, by notification,—`
  line
  line `(i) assign additional functions to a Social Security Organisation including administration of any`
  line `other Act or scheme relating to social security subject to such provisions as may be specified in this`
  line `behalf in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that while the additional function of administering the Act or scheme are assigned under`
  line `this clause to a Social Security Organisation, the officer or authority of such organisation, to whom`
  line `such function has been assigned, shall exercise the powers under the enactment or scheme required for`
  line `discharging such function in the manner as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Social Security Organisations may assign such additional functions to`
  line `existing officers or appoint or engage new officers necessary for such purpose, if such functions may`
  line `not be performed and completed with the assistance of its personnel as existing immediately before the`
  line `assignment of the additional functions;`
  line
  line `(ii) specify the terms and conditions of discharging the functions under clause (i) by the Social`
  line `Security Organisation;`
  line
  line `(iii) provide that the expenditure incurred in discharging the functions specified in clause (i)`
  line `including appointment or engagement of personnel necessary for proper discharge of such functions`
  line `shall be borne by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) specify the powers which the Social Security Organisation shall exercise while discharging the`
  line `functions specified in clause (i); and`
  line
  line `(v) provide that any expenditure referred to in clause (iii) shall be made by the Social Security`
  line `Organisation after prior approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (54038)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment of officers of Central Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54038&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may appoint a Central`
  line `Provident Fund Commissioner who shall be the Chief Executive Officer of the Central Board and shall also`
  line `function as head of the Employees' Provident Fund Organisation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this Code, the expression "Employees' Provident Fund`
  line `Organisation" means the organisation consisting of officers and employees of the Central Board.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Provident Fund Commissioner shall be subject to the general control and`
  line `superintendence of the Central Board in the discharge of his functions under this Code.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall also appoint a Financial Advisor and Chief Accounts Officer to assist`
  line `the Central Provident Fund Commissioner in the discharge of his duties.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Board may appoint, as many Additional Central Provident Fund Commissioners,`
  line `Deputy Provident Fund Commissioners, Regional Provident Fund Commissioners, Assistant Provident`
  line `Fund Commissioners and such other officers and employees as it may consider necessary for the efficient`
  line `administration of the Provident Fund Scheme, the Pension Scheme and the Insurance Scheme or other`
  line `responsibilities assigned to the Central Board from time to time by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) No appointment to the post of the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or an Additional Central`
  line `Provident Fund Commissioner or a Financial Adviser and Chief Accounts Officer or any other post under`
  line `the Central Board carrying a scale of pay equivalent to the scale of pay of any Group 'A' or Group 'B' post`
  line `under the Central Government shall be made except after consultation with the Union Public Service`
  line `Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such consultation shall be necessary in regard to any such appointment---`
  line
  line `(a) for a period not exceeding one year; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the person to be appointed is, at the time of his appointment,---`
  line
  line `(i) a member of the Indian Administrative Service, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in the service of the Central Government or the Central Board in a Group 'A' or Group 'B'`
  line post.
  line
  line `(6) The method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service of the`
  line `Central Provident Fund Commissioner and the Financial Adviser and Chief Accounts Officer shall be such`
  line `as may be specified by the Central Government and such salary and allowances shall be paid out of the`
  line `Provident Fund.`
  line
  line `(7) (a) The method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service of`
  line `the Additional Central Provident Fund Commissioners, Deputy Provident Fund Commissioners, Regional`
  line `Provident Fund Commissioners, Assistant Provident Fund Commissioners and other officers and`
  line `employees of the Central Board shall be such as may be specified by the Central Board in accordance with`
  line `the rules and orders applicable to the officers and employees of the Central Government drawing`
  line `corresponding scales of pay:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Central Board is of the opinion that it is necessary to make a departure from`
  line `the said rules or orders in respect of any of the matters aforesaid, it shall obtain the prior approval of the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the salary and allowances of the officers specified in this clause shall not exceed`
  line `the scale of pay respectively provided in the Provident Fund Scheme.`
  line
  line `(b) In determining the corresponding scales of pay of officers and employees under clause (a), the`
  line `Central Board shall have regard to the educational qualifications, method of recruitment, duties and`
  line `responsibilities of such officers and employees under the Central Government and in case of any doubt, the`
  line `Central Board shall refer the matter to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (54039)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Schemes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54039&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification---`
  line
  line `(a) frame a scheme to be called the Employees' Provident Fund Scheme for which the provident`
  line `funds shall be established under this Chapter for employees or for any class of employees and specify`
  line `the establishments or class of establishments to which the said scheme shall apply;`
  line
  line `(b) frame a scheme to be called the Employees' Pension Scheme for the purpose of providing for---`
  line
  line `(i) superannuation pension, retiring pension or permanent total disablement pension to the`
  line `employees of any establishment or class of establishments to which this Chapter applies;`
  line
  line `(ii) widow or widower's pension, children pension or orphan pension payable to the beneficiaries`
  line `of such employees; and`
  line
  line `(iii) nominee pension;`
  line
  line `(c) frame a scheme to be called the Employees' Deposit Linked Insurance Scheme for the purpose`
  line `of providing life insurance benefits to the employees of any establishment or class of establishments to`
  line `which this Chapter applies;`
  line
  line `(d) frame any other scheme or schemes for the purposes of providing social security benefits under`
  line `this Code to self-employed workers or any other class of persons; and`
  line
  line `(e) modify any scheme referred to in clauses (a), (b), (c) and (d) by adding thereto, amending or`
  line `varying therein, either prospectively or retrospectively.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, the schemes referred to in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) may provide for all or any of the matters respectively specified in Part A, Part B and Part C`
  line `of the Fifth Schedule.`
  line
  line `(3) The schemes may provide that all or any of its provisions shall take effect either prospectively or`
  line `retrospectively on and from such date as may be specified in that behalf in the scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (54040)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Funds.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54040&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, for the purposes of---`
  line
  line `(a) the Provident Fund Scheme, establish a Provident Fund where the contributions paid by the`
  line `employer to the fund shall be ten per cent. of the wages for the time being payable to each of the`
  line `employees (whether employed by him directly or by or through a contactor), and the employee's`
  line `contribution shall be equal to the contribution payable by the employer in respect of him and may, if`
  line `any employee so desires, be an amount exceeding ten per cent. of the wages, subject to the condition`
  line `that the employer shall not be under an obligation to pay any contribution over and above his`
  line `contribution payable under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that in its application to any establishment or class of establishments which the Central`
  line `Government, after making such inquiry as it deems fit, may, by notification, specify, this section shall`
  line `be subject to the modification that for the words 'ten per cent.' at both the places where they occur, the`
  line `words " twelve per cent." shall be substituted:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government, after making such inquiry as it deems fit, may, by`
  line `notification, specify rates of employees contributions and the period for which such rates shall apply`
  line `for any class of employee;`
  line
  line `(b) the Pension Scheme, establish a Pension Fund in the manner specified in that scheme by that`
  line `Government into which there shall be paid, from time to time, in respect of every employee who is a`
  line `member of the Pension Scheme,---`
  line
  line `(i) such sums from the employer's contribution under clause (a) not exceeding eight and onethird per cent. of the wages or such per cent. of wages as may be notified by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(ii) such sums payable as contribution to the Pension Fund, as may be specified in the Pension`
  line `Scheme, by the employers of the exempted establishments under section 143 to which the pension`
  line `scheme applies;`
  line
  line `(iii) such sums as the Central Government after due appropriation by Parliament by law in this`
  line `behalf, specify;`
  line
  line `(c) the Insurance Scheme, establish a Deposit-Linked Insurance Fund in the manner specified in`
  line `that scheme by that Government into which there shall be paid by the employer from time to time in`
  line `respect of every such employee in relation to whom he is the employer, such amount, not being more`
  line `than one per cent. of the wages or such per cent. of wages as may be notified by the Central Government`
  line `for the time being payable in relation to such employee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the employer shall pay into the Insurance Fund such further sums of money, not`
  line `exceeding one-fourth of the contribution which he is required to make under this clause, as the Central`
  line `Government may, from time to time, determine to meet all the expenses in connection with the`
  line `administration of the Insurance Scheme other than the expenses towards the cost of any benefits`
  line `provided by or under the Insurance Scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) The Provident Fund, the Pension Fund and the Insurance Fund shall vest in, and be administered`
  line `by, the Central Board in such manner as may be specified in the respective schemes.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (54041)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Contribution in respect of employees and contractors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54041&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The amount of contribution (that is`
  line `to say, the employer's contribution as well as the employee's contribution in pursuance of any scheme and`
  line `the employer's contribution in pursuance of the Insurance Scheme) and any charge for meeting the cost of`
  line `administering the fund paid or payable by an employer in respect of an employee employed by or through`
  line `a contractor may be recovered by such employer from the contractor, either by deduction from any amount`
  line `payable to the contractor under any contract or as a debt payable by the contractor.`
  line
  line `(2) A contractor from whom the amounts mentioned in sub-section (1) may be recovered in respect of`
  line `any employee employed by or through him may recover from such employee, the employee's contribution`
  line `under any scheme by deduction from the wages payable to such employee.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding any contract to the contrary, no contractor shall be entitled to deduct the employer's`
  line `contribution or the charges referred to in sub-section (1) from the wages payable to an employee employed`
  line `by or through him or otherwise to recover such contribution or charges from such employee.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (54042)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Fund to be recognised under Act 43 of 1961.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54042&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of the Income-tax Act, 1961,`
  line `the Provident Fund shall be deemed to be a recognised provident fund within the meaning of clause (38) of`
  line `section 2 of that Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in the said Act shall operate to render ineffective any provision of the`
  line `Provident Fund Scheme (under which the Provident Fund is established) which is repugnant to any of the`
  line `provisions of that Act or of the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (54043)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Priority of payment of contributions over other debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54043&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, any amount due under this Chapter shall be the charge on the`
  line `assets of the establishment to which it relates and shall be paid in priority in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (54044)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Chapter not to apply to certain establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54044&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Chapter shall not apply—`
  line
  line `(a) to any establishment registered under the Co-operative Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912) or under`
  line `any other law for the time being in force in any State relating to co-operative societies employing less`
  line `than fifty persons and working without the aid of power; or`
  line
  line `(b) to any other establishment belonging to or under the control of the Central Government or a State`
  line `Government and whose employees are entitled to the benefit of contributory provident fund or old age`
  line `pension in accordance with any scheme or rule framed by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government governing such benefits; or`
  line
  line `(c) to any other establishment set up under any Central or State or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force and whose employees are entitled to the benefits of contributory provident fund or old age pension`
  line `in accordance with any scheme or rule framed under that law governing such benefits; or`
  line
  line `(d) to the employees who, immediately before the commencement of this Code, were receiving`
  line `benefits of Provident Fund under any Central or State enactment.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Central Government is of the opinion that having regard to the financial position of any class`
  line `of establishment or other circumstances of the case, it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification and subject to such conditions, as may be specified in the notification, exempt, whether`
  line `prospectively or retrospectively, that class of establishments from the operation of this Chapter for such`
  line `period as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (54045)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Authorising certain employers to maintain provident fund accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54045&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, on an application made to it in this behalf by the employer and the majority of employees`
  line `in relation to an establishment employing one hundred or more persons, authorise the employer by an order`
  line `in writing, to maintain a provident fund account in relation to the establishment, in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government and subject to such terms and conditions as may be specified in the`
  line `Provident Fund Scheme:`
  line
  line `Provided that no authorisation shall be made under this sub-section if the employer of such`
  line `establishment had committed any default in the payment of provident fund contribution or had committed`
  line `any other offence under this Code during the three years immediately preceding the date of such`
  line authorisation.
  line
  line `(2) Where an establishment is authorised to maintain a provident fund account under sub-section (1),`
  line `the employer in relation to such establishment shall maintain such account, submit such return, deposit the`
  line `contribution in such manner, provide for such facilities for inspection, pay such administrative charges, and`
  line `abide by such other terms and conditions, as may be specified in the Provident Fund Scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) Any authorisation made under this section may be cancelled by the Central Government by order`
  line `in writing if the employer fails to comply with any of the terms and conditions of the authorisation or where`
  line `he commits any offence under any provision of this Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that before cancelling the authorisation, the Central Government shall give the employer a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (54046)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Transfer of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54046&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where an employee,—`
  line
  line `(a) employed in an establishment to which this Chapter applies, relinquishes his employment`
  line `therefrom and obtains employment in any other establishment to which this Chapter applies or not; or`
  line
  line `(b) employed in an establishment to which this Chapter does not apply, relinquishes his`
  line `employment therefrom and obtains employment in an establishment to which this Chapter applies, then,`
  line `his accumulated amount in provident fund account or pension account, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `transferred or dealt with in the manner as may be specified in the Provident Fund Scheme or the Pension`
  line `Scheme, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (54047)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Appeal to Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54047&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order passed by any authority in regard to`
  line `the following matters may prefer an appeal to the Tribunal constituted by the Central Government,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) determination and assessment of dues under section 125 relating to Chapter III; and`
  line
  line `(b) levy of damages under section 128 relating to Chapter III.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed in such form and manner, within such time and`
  line `accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No appeal under clause (a) of sub-section (1) by the employer shall be entertained by the Tribunal`
  line `unless he has deposited with Social Security Organisation concerned twenty-five per cent. of the amount`
  line `due from him as determined by an officer under section 125.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal shall endeavour to decide the appeal within a period of one year from the date on`
  line `which the appeal has been preferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (54048)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Principal Officers and other staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54048&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may appoint a Director General`
  line `of the Corporation and a Financial Commissioner, who shall be the Principal Officers of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director General and the Financial Commissioner shall hold office for such period, not`
  line `exceeding five years, as may be specified in the order of appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that outgoing Director General or Financial Commissioner, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `eligible for re-appointment if he is otherwise qualified.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director General or the Financial Commissioner shall receive such salary and allowances as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director General and the Financial Commissioner shall exercise such powers and discharge`
  line `such duties as may be prescribed by the Central Government and shall perform such other functions as may`
  line `be specified in the regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) A person shall be disqualified from being appointed as or for being the Director General of the`
  line `Corporation or the Financial Commissioner if he is subject to any of the disqualifications specified in`
  line `section 8.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may at any time remove the Director General of the Corporation or the`
  line `Financial Commissioner from office and shall do so if such removal is recommended by a resolution of the`
  line `Corporation passed at a special meeting called for the purpose and supported by the votes of not less than`
  line `two-third of the total strength of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(7) The Corporation may employ such other officers and employees as may be necessary for the`
  line `efficient transaction of its business and for discharge of any other responsibilities assigned to the`
  line `Corporation from time to time by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the sanction of the Central Government shall be obtained for the creation of any post the`
  line `maximum monthly salary of which exceeds such salary as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(8) (a) The method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service of`
  line `the officers and employees of the Corporation shall be such as may be specified in the regulations in`
  line `accordance with the rules and orders applicable to the officers and employees of the Central Government`
  line `drawing corresponding scales of pay:`
  line
  line `Provided that the terms and conditions of service including pay and allowances of such posts of medical`
  line `specialists and super specialists in the Corporation possessing comparable qualifications and expertise, as`
  line `may be notified by the Central Government, with the equivalent posts of the specialists and super specialists`
  line `in the All India Institute of Medical Sciences or in the Post Graduate Institutes of Medical Sciences and`
  line `Research or other similar institutions established by the Central Government, shall respectively be similar:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Corporation is of the opinion that it is necessary to make a departure`
  line `from the said rules or orders in respect of any of the matters aforesaid, it shall obtain the prior approval of`
  line `the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided also that this sub-section shall not apply to appointment of consultants and specialists in`
  line `various fields appointed on contract basis.`
  line
  line `(b) In determining the corresponding scales of pay of officers and employees under clause (a), the`
  line `Corporation shall have regard to the educational qualifications, method of recruitment, duties and`
  line `responsibilities of such officers and employees under the Central Government and in case of any doubt, the`
  line `Corporation shall refer the matter to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(9) Every appointment to posts (other than medical, nursing or para-medical posts) corresponding to`
  line `Group 'A' and Group 'B' Gazetted posts under the Central Government shall be made in consultation with`
  line `the Union Public Service Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply to an officiating or temporary appointment for a period not exceeding one year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any such officiating or temporary appointment shall not confer any claim for`
  line `regular appointment and the services rendered in that capacity shall not count towards seniority or minimum`
  line `qualifying service specified in the regulations for promotion to next higher grade.`
  line
  line `(10) If any question arises whether a post corresponds to a Group 'A' and Group 'B' posts under the`
  line `Central Government, the question shall be referred to that Government whose decision thereon shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (54049)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Employees’ State Insurance Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54049&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) All contributions and user charges paid under this`
  line `Chapter and all other moneys received on behalf of the Corporation shall be paid into a fund (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the Employees' State Insurance Fund) which shall be held and administered by the`
  line `Corporation for the purposes of this Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that the user charges collected from the other beneficiaries referred to in section 44 shall be`
  line `deemed to be contribution and shall form part of Employees' State Insurance Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation may accept grants, donations, Corporate Social Responsibility Fund and gifts from`
  line `the Central or any State Government, local authority, or any individual or body whether incorporated or`
  line `not, for all or any of the purposes of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the other provisions contained in this Code and to any rules or regulations made in this`
  line `behalf, all moneys accruing or payable to the said Fund shall be deposited in such bank or banks as may be`
  line `approved by the Central Government to the credit of an account styled the account of the Employees' State`
  line `Insurance Fund.`
  line
  line `(4) The Employees State Insurance Fund or any other money which is held by the Corporation shall be`
  line `deposited or invested in the manner prescribed by the Central Government and the account referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) shall be operated by such officers as may be authorised by the Committee constituted under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 5 (hereinafter referred to as the Standing Committee) with the approval of the`
  line Corporation.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (54050)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Purposes for which Employees’ State Insurance Fund may be expended.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54050&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter and the rules and regulations relating thereto, made under this Code, the`
  line `Employees' State Insurance Fund shall be expended only for the following purposes, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) payment of benefits and provision of medical treatment and attendance to Insured Persons referred`
  line `to in section 28 and, where the medical benefit is extended to their families, the provision of such`
  line `medical benefit to their families, in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter and the rules and`
  line `regulations relating thereto and defraying the charges and costs in connection therewith;`
  line
  line `(b) payment of fees and allowances to members of the Corporation, the Standing Committee, the`
  line `Medical Benefit Committee or other Committees thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) payment of salaries, leave and joining time allowances, travelling and compensatory allowances,`
  line `gratuities and compassionate allowances, pensions, contributions to provident or other benefit fund of`
  line `officers and staff of the Corporation and meeting the expenditure in respect of offices and other services`
  line `set up for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Code relating to this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(d) establishment and maintenance of hospitals, dispensaries and other institutions and the provision`
  line `of medical and other ancillary services for the benefit of Insured Persons referred to in section 28 and,`
  line `where the medical benefit is extended to their families;`
  line
  line `(e) payment of contributions to any State Government, local authority or any private body or`
  line `individual, towards the cost of medical treatment and attendance provided to Insured Persons referred`
  line `to in section 28 and, where the medical benefit is extended to their families, their families, including`
  line `the cost of any building and equipment, in accordance with any agreement entered into by the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(f) defraying the cost (including all expenses) of auditing the accounts of the Corporation and of the`
  line `valuation of its assets and liabilities;`
  line
  line `(g) defraying the cost (including all expenses) of the Employees' Insurance Courts set up under this`
  line Chapter;
  line
  line `(h) payment of any sums under any contract entered into for the purposes of this Code by Corporation`
  line `or the Standing Committee or by any officer duly authorised by the Corporation or the Standing`
  line `Committee in that behalf;`
  line
  line `(i) payment of sums under any decree, order or award of any Court or Tribunal against the`
  line `Corporation or any of its officers or staff for any act done in the execution of his duty or under a`
  line `compromise or settlement of any suit or other legal proceeding or claim instituted or made against the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(j) defraying the cost and other charges of instituting or defending any civil or criminal proceedings`
  line `arising out of any action taken under this Code relating to this Chapter;`
  line
  line `(k) defraying expenditure, within the limits prescribed by the Central Government after consultation`
  line `with the Corporation, on measures for the improvement of the health and welfare of Insured Persons`
  line `and for the rehabilitation and re-employment of Insured Persons referred to in section 28 who have`
  line `been disabled or injured; and`
  line
  line `(l) such other purposes as may be authorised by the Corporation with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (54051)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Holding of property, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54051&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may, subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government, acquire and hold property, both movable and immovable, sell or`
  line `otherwise transfer any movable or immovable property which may have become vested in or have been`
  line `acquired by it and do all things necessary for the purposes for which the Corporation is established.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government, the Corporation may`
  line `from time to time invest any moneys which are not immediately required for expenses properly defrayable`
  line `under this Code and may, subject to as aforesaid, from time to time re-invest or realise such investments.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation may, with the previous sanction of the Central Government and on such terms as`
  line `may be prescribed by it, raise loans and take measures for discharging such loans.`
  line
  line `(4) The Corporation may constitute for the benefit of its officers and staff or any class of them, such`
  line `provident or other benefit fund as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (54052)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `All employees to be insured.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54052&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Code, every employee in an`
  line `establishment to which this Chapter applies shall be insured in such manner whether electronically or`
  line `otherwise, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) An employee whether insured or insurable under sub-section (1) in respect of whom contributions`
  line `are or were payable and who is by reason thereof, entitled to any of the benefits provided under this Chapter,`
  line `shall be called “Insured Person”.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (54053)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Contributions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54053&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The contribution payable under this Chapter in respect of an employee shall`
  line `comprise contribution payable by the employer (hereinafter referred to as the employer's contribution) and`
  line `contribution payable by the employee (hereinafter referred to as the employee's contribution) and shall be`
  line `paid to the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The contributions (employer's contribution and the employees contribution both) shall be paid at`
  line `such rates as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The wage period in relation to an employee shall be the unit as specified in the regulations`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the wage period) in respect of which all contributions shall be payable under this`
  line Chapter.
  line
  line `(4) The contributions payable in respect of each wage period shall ordinarily fall due on the last day of`
  line `the wage period, and where an employee is employed for part of the wage period, or is employed under two`
  line `or more employers during the same wage period, the contributions shall fall due on such days as may be`
  line `specified in the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (54054)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Administrative expenses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54054&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The types of expenses which may be termed as administrative`
  line `expenses and the percentage of the income of the Corporation which may be spent for such expenses shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government and the Corporation shall keep its administrative`
  line `expenses within the limit so prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (54055)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Provisions as to payment of contributions by employer, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54055&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The employer shall pay in`
  line `respect of every employee, whether directly employed by him or by or through a contractor, both the`
  line `employer's contribution and the employee's contribution.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, but subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Code and the rules and regulations, if any, made thereunder in this behalf, the employer`
  line `shall, in the case of an employee directly employed by him (not being an exempted employee), be entitled`
  line `to recover from the employee the employee's contribution by reduction from his wages and not otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such deduction shall be made from any wages other than such as relates to the period`
  line `or part of the period in respect of which the contribution is payable or in excess of the sum representing the`
  line `employee's contribution for the period.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding any contract to the contrary, neither the employer nor the contractor shall be`
  line `entitled to deduct the employer's contribution from any wages payable to an employee or otherwise to`
  line `recover it from him.`
  line
  line `(4) Any sum deducted by the employer from wages under this Chapter shall be deemed to have been`
  line `entrusted to him by the employee for the purpose of paying the contribution in respect of which it was`
  line deducted.
  line
  line `(5) The employer shall bear the expenses of remitting the contributions to the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(6) An employer, who has paid contribution in respect of an employee employed by or through a`
  line `contractor, shall be entitled to recover the amount of the contribution so paid (that is to say the employer's`
  line `contribution as well as the employee's contribution, if any,) from the contractor, either by deduction from`
  line `any amount payable to him by the employer under any contract, or as a debt payable by the contractor.`
  line
  line `(7) The contractor shall maintain a register of employees employed by or through him as provided in`
  line `the regulations and submit the same to the employer before the settlement of any amount payable under`
  line `sub-section (6).`
  line
  line `(8) In the case referred to in sub-section (6), the contractor shall be entitled to recover the employee's`
  line `contribution from the employee employed by or through him by deduction from wages and not otherwise,`
  line `subject to such conditions as specified in the proviso to sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(9) Subject to the provisions of this Code, the Corporation may make regulations for any matter relating`
  line `or incidental to the payment and collection of contributions payable under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (54056)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title Benefits.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54056&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Code, the Insured Persons, their dependants or the`
  line `persons hereinafter mentioned, as the case may be, shall be entitled to the following benefits, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) periodical payments to any Insured Person in case of his sickness certified by a duly appointed`
  line `medical practitioner or by any other person possessing such qualifications and experience as the`
  line `Corporation may, by the regulations, specify in this behalf (hereinafter referred to as sickness benefit);`
  line
  line `(b) periodical payments to an Insured Person being a woman in case of confinement or miscarriage`
  line `or sickness arising out of pregnancy, confinement, premature birth of child or miscarriage, such woman`
  line `being certified to be eligible for such payments by an authority specified in this behalf by the regulations`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as maternity benefit);`
  line
  line `(c) periodical payments to an Insured Person suffering from disablement as a result of an employment`
  line `injury sustained by him as an employee for the purposes of this Chapter and certified to be eligible for`
  line `such payments by an authority specified in this behalf by the regulations (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `disablement benefit);`
  line
  line `(d) periodical payments to such dependants of an Insured Person who dies as a result of an`
  line `employment injury sustained by him as an employee for the purposes of this Chapter, as are entitled`
  line `under this Chapter (hereinafter referred to as dependents’ benefit);`
  line
  line `(e) medical treatment for and attendance on Insured Persons (hereinafter referred to as medical`
  line `benefit); and`
  line
  line `(f) payment to the eldest surviving member of the family of an Insured Person who has died, towards`
  line `the expenditure on the funeral of the deceased Insured Person, or, where the Insured Person did not`
  line `have a family or was not living with his family at the time of his death, to the person who actually`
  line `incurs the expenditure on the funeral of the deceased Insured Person (to be known as funeral expenses):`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of payment under this clause shall not exceed such amount as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government and the claim for such payment shall be made within three months`
  line `of the death of the Insured Person or within such extended period as the Corporation or any officer or`
  line `authority authorised by it in this behalf may allow.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation may, subject to such conditions as may be laid down in the regulations, extend the`
  line `medical benefits to the family of an Insured Person.`
  line
  line `(3) The qualification of a person to claim sickness benefit, maternity benefit, disablement benefit and`
  line `dependants' benefit and the conditions subject to which such benefit may be given and the rate and period`
  line `thereof, shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of this Code and the rules made thereunder relating to this Chapter, the`
  line `Corporation may make regulations for any matter relating or incidental to the accrual and payment of`
  line `benefits payable under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (54057)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Corporation’s power to promote measures for health, etc., of Insured Persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54057&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Corporation may, in addition to the benefits specified in this Chapter, promote measures for the`
  line `improvement of the health and welfare of Insured Persons and for the rehabilitation and re-employment of`
  line `Insured Persons who have been disabled or injured and may incur in respect of such measures, expenditure`
  line `from the Employees' State Insurance Fund within such limits as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (54058)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Presumption as to accident arising in course of employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54058&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this`
  line `Chapter, an accident arising in the course of an employee's employment shall be presumed, in the absence`
  line `of evidence to the contrary, to have arisen out of that employment.`
  line
  line `(2) An accident happening to an employee in or about any premises at which he is for the time being`
  line `employed for the purpose of his employer's trade or business shall be deemed to arise out of and in the`
  line `course of his employment, if it happens while he is taking steps, on an actual or supposed emergency at`
  line `those premises, to rescue, succour or protect persons who are, or are thought to be or possibly to be, injured`
  line `or imperilled, or to avert or minimise serious damage to property.`
  line
  line `(3) An accident occurring to an employee while commuting from his residence to the place of`
  line `employment for duty or from the place of employment to his residence after performing duty, shall be`
  line `deemed to have arisen out of and in the course of employment if nexus between the circumstances, time`
  line `and place in which the accident occurred and the employment is established.`
  line
  line `(4) An accident happening while an employee is, with the express or implied permission of his`
  line `employer, travelling as a passenger by any vehicle to or from his place of work shall, notwithstanding that he is under no obligation to his employer to travel by that vehicle, be deemed to arise out of and in the`
  line `course of his employment, if---`
  line
  line `(a) the accident would have been deemed so to have arisen had he been under such obligation; and`
  line
  line `(b) at the time of the accident, the vehicle---`
  line
  line `(i) is being operated by or on behalf of his employer or some other person by whom it is provided`
  line `in pursuance of arrangements made with his employer; and`
  line
  line `(ii) is not being operated in the ordinary course of public transport service.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- In this section, vehicle includes a vessel and an aircraft.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (54059)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Accidents happening while acting in breach of law, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54059&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `An accident shall be deemed to arise`
  line `out of and in the course of an employee's employment notwithstanding that he is at the time of the accident`
  line `acting in contravention of the provisions of any law applicable to him, or of any orders given by or on`
  line `behalf of his employer or that he is acting without instructions from his employer, if—`
  line
  line `(a) the accident would have been deemed so to have arisen had the act not been done in contravention`
  line `as aforesaid or without instructions from his employer, as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(b) the act is done for the purpose of and in connection with the employer's trade or business.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (54060)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Occupational disease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54060&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an employee employed in any employment specified in Part A of`
  line `the Third Schedule contracts any disease specified therein as an occupational disease peculiar to that`
  line `employment, or if an employee employed in the employment specified in Part B of that Schedule for a`
  line `continuous period of not less than six months contracts any disease specified therein as an occupational`
  line `disease peculiar to that employment or if an employee employed in any employment specified in Part C of`
  line `that Schedule for such continuous period as the Corporation may specify by regulations in respect of each`
  line `such employment, contracts any disease specified in such Part C as an occupational disease peculiar to that`
  line `employment, the contracting of the disease shall, unless the contrary is proved, be deemed to be an`
  line `“employment injury “, arising out of and in the course of employment.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as provided by sub-section (1), no benefit shall be payable to an employee in respect of any`
  line `disease unless the disease is directly attributable to a specific injury by accident arising out of and in the`
  line `course of his employment.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) of section 34 shall not apply to the cases to which this section`
  line applies.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (54061)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `References to medical board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54061&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any question---`
  line
  line `(a) whether the relevant accident has resulted in permanent disablement; or`
  line
  line `(b) whether the extent of loss of earning capacity can be assessed provisionally or finally; or`
  line
  line `(c) whether the assessment of the proportion of the loss of earning capacity is provisional or final; or`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of provisional assessment, as to the period for which such assessment shall hold good,`
  line
  line `shall be determined by a medical board constituted in accordance with the provisions of the regulations`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as medical board) and any such question shall hereafter be referred to as the`
  line `"disablement question".`
  line
  line `(2) The case of any Insured Person for permanent disablement benefit shall be referred by the`
  line `Corporation to a medical board for determination of the disablement in question and if, on that or any`
  line `subsequent reference, the extent of loss of earning capacity of the Insured Person is provisionally assessed,`
  line `it shall again be so referred to the medical board not later than the end of the period taken into account by`
  line `the provisional assessment.`
  line
  line `(3) Any decision under this Chapter of a medical board may be reviewed at any time by the medical`
  line `board if it is satisfied by fresh evidence that the decision was given in consequence of the non-disclosure`
  line `or misrepresentation by the employee or any other person of a material fact whether the non-disclosure or`
  line `misrepresentation was or was not fraudulent.`
  line
  line `(4) Any assessment of the extent of the disablement resulting from the relevant employment injury may`
  line `also be reviewed by a medical board if it is satisfied that since the making of the assessment there has been`
  line `a substantial and unforeseen aggravation of the results of the relevant injury:`
  line
  line `Provided that an assessment shall not be reviewed under this sub-section unless the medical board is of`
  line `the opinion, having regard to the period taken into account by the assessment and the probable duration of`
  line `the aggravation aforesaid, that substantial injustice will be done by not reviewing it.`
  line
  line `(5) Except with the leave of a medical appeal tribunal constituted by regulations, an assessment shall`
  line `not be reviewed under sub-section (4) on any application made less than five years, or in the case of a`
  line `provisional assessment, six months, from the date thereof and on such a review the period to be taken into`
  line `account by any revised assessment shall not include any period before the date of the application.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the foregoing provisions of this section, a medical board may deal with a case of review`
  line `in any manner in which it could deal with it on an original reference to it, and in particular may make a`
  line `provisional assessment notwithstanding that the assessment under review was final and the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2) shall apply to an application for review under this sub-section and to a decision of a medical`
  line `board in connection with such application as they apply to a case for disablement benefit under that subsection and to a decision of the medical board in connection with such case.`
  line
  line `(7) (a) If the Insured Person or the Corporation is aggrieved by any decision of the medical board, the`
  line `Insured Person or the Corporation, as the case may be, may appeal in such manner and within such time as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government to---`
  line
  line `(i) the medical appeal tribunal constituted in accordance with the provisions of the regulations; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the Employees' Insurance Court directly:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal by an Insured Person shall lie under this sub-section if such person has applied`
  line `for commutation of disablement benefit on the basis of the decision of the medical board and received the`
  line `commuted value of such benefits:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal by the Corporation shall lie under this sub-section if the Corporation`
  line `paid the commuted value of the disablement benefit on the basis of the decision of the medical board.`
  line
  line `(b) Where the Insured Person or the Corporation preferred appeal to the medical appeal tribunal under`
  line `sub-clause (i) of clause (a) instead of to the Employees' Insurance Court under sub-clause (ii) of that clause,`
  line `then, he or it, as the case may be, shall have the further right to file second appeal to the Employees'`
  line `Insurance Court in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (54062)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Dependants’ benefit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54062&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) If an Insured Person dies as a result of an employment injury sustained`
  line `as an employee under this Chapter (whether or not he was in receipt of any periodical payment for`
  line `temporary disablement in respect of the injury), dependants' benefit shall be payable to his dependants`
  line `specified in sub-clause (a) and sub-clause (b) of clause (24) of section 2 at such rates and for such periods`
  line `and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In case the Insured Person dies without leaving behind him the dependants as aforesaid, the`
  line `dependants' benefit shall be paid to the other dependants of the deceased at such rates and for such periods`
  line `and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Any decision awarding dependants' benefit under this Chapter may be reviewed at any time by the`
  line `Corporation if it is satisfied by fresh evidence that the decision was given in consequence of non-disclosure`
  line `or misrepresentation by the claimant or any other person of a material fact (whether the non-disclosure or`
  line `misrepresentation was or was not fraudulent) or that the decision is no longer in accordance with this`
  line `Chapter due to any birth or death or due to the marriage, re-marriage, or ceasing of infirmity, or attainment`
  line `of the age of twenty-five years by, a claimant.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, the Corporation may, on such review under sub-section (3), direct that the dependants' benefit be continued, increased, reduced or discontinued.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (54063)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Medical benefit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54063&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) An Insured Person or (where such medical benefit is extended to his family)`
  line `a member of his family whose condition requires medical treatment and attendance shall be entitled to`
  line `receive medical benefit.`
  line
  line `(2) Such medical benefit may be given either in the form of out-patient treatment and attendance in a`
  line `hospital or dispensary, clinic or other institution or by visits to the home of the Insured Person or treatment`
  line `as in-patient in a hospital or other institution.`
  line
  line `(3) The qualification of an Insured Person and (where such medical benefit is extended to his family)`
  line `his family, to claim medical benefit and the conditions subject to which such benefit may be given, the scale`
  line `and period thereof shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person in respect of whom contribution ceases to be payable under this Chapter may be`
  line `allowed medical benefit for such period and of such nature as may be provided by the regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an Insured Person who has attained the age of superannuation, a person who retires`
  line `under a Voluntary Retirement Scheme or takes premature retirement, and his spouse shall be eligible to`
  line `receive medical benefits subject to payment of contribution and such other conditions as may be specified`
  line `in the regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided also that an Insured Person who ceases to be in insurable employment on account of`
  line `permanent disablement caused due to employment injury shall continue to receive medical benefits, subject`
  line `to payment of contribution and other conditions as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the conditions for grant of medical benefits to the Insured Person during employment`
  line `injury shall be as specified in the regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) (a) The Corporation may establish medical education institutions, including colleges, dental`
  line `colleges, nursing colleges and the training institutes for its officers and staff with a view to improve the`
  line `quality of their services.`
  line
  line `(b) The medical education institutions referred to in clause (a) shall require its students to furnish a`
  line `bond for serving the Corporation for such time and in such manner, as may be specified in the regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) The medical education institutions and training institutes referred to in sub-section (4) may be run`
  line `by the Corporation itself or on the request of the Corporation, by the Central Government, any State`
  line `Government, Public Sector Undertaking of the Central Government or the State Government or any other`
  line `body notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression other body means any such`
  line `organisation of persons which the Central Government considers capable to run colleges and training`
  line `institutions referred to in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) The Corporation may, in order to take preventive and curative measures for welfare of the Insured`
  line `Persons, carry out such occupational and epidemiological surveys and studies for assessment of health and`
  line `working conditions of Insured Persons in such manner as may be specified in the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (54064)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Provision of medical treatment by State Government or by Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54064&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government shall provide for Insured Persons and (where such benefit is extended to their families) their`
  line `families in the State, reasonable medical, surgical and obstetric treatment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, with the approval of the Corporation, arrange for medical`
  line `treatment at clinics of medical practitioners on such scale and subject to such terms and conditions as may`
  line `be agreed upon.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the incidence of sickness benefit payment to Insured Persons in any State is found to exceed`
  line `the all-India average, the amount of such excess shall be shared between the Corporation and the State`
  line `Government in such proportion as may be fixed by agreement between them:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Corporation may in any case waive the recovery of the whole or any part of the share`
  line `which is to be borne by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation may enter into an agreement with a State Government in regard to the nature and`
  line `scale of the medical treatment that should be provided to Insured Persons and (where such medical benefit`
  line `is extended to the families) their families (including provision of buildings, equipment, medicines, and`
  line `staff) and for the sharing of the cost thereof and of any excess in the incidence of sickness benefit to Insured`
  line `Persons between the Corporation and the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) In default of agreement between the Corporation and any State Government as aforesaid, the nature`
  line `and extent of the medical treatment to be provided by the State Government and the proportion in which`
  line `the cost thereof and of the excess in the incidence of sickness benefit shall be shared between the`
  line `Corporation and that Government, shall be determined by an arbitrator who shall be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the State Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Government may, in addition to the Corporation under this Code, with the previous`
  line `approval of the Central Government, establish such organisation (by whatever name called) to provide for`
  line `certain benefits to employees in case of sickness, maternity and employment injury:`
  line
  line `Provided that any reference to the State Government in this Code relating to this Chapter shall also`
  line `include reference to the organisation as and when such organisation is established by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The organisation referred to in sub-section (5) shall have such structure, discharge functions,`
  line `exercise powers and undertake such activities as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(7) The Corporation may establish and maintain in a State such hospitals, dispensaries and other`
  line `medical and surgical services as it may think fit for the benefit of Insured Persons and (where such medical`
  line `benefit is extended to their families), their families.`
  line
  line `(8) The Corporation may enter into agreement with any local authority, private body or individual in`
  line `regard to the provision of medical treatment and attendance for Insured Persons and (where such medical`
  line `benefit is extended to their families) their families, in any area and sharing the cost thereof.`
  line
  line `(9) The Corporation may also enter into agreement with any local authority, local body or private body`
  line `for commissioning and running Employees' State Insurance hospitals through third party participation for`
  line `providing medical treatment and attendance to Insured Persons and (where such medical benefit has been`
  line `extended to their families), to their families.`
  line
  line `(10) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Chapter, the Corporation may,`
  line `in consultation with the State Government, undertake the responsibility for providing medical benefit to`
  line `Insured Persons and (where such medical benefit is extended to their families), to the families of such`
  line `Insured Persons in the State subject to the condition that the State Government shall share the cost of such`
  line `medical benefit in such proportion as may be agreed upon between the State Government and the`
  line Corporation.
  line
  line `(11) In the event of the Corporation exercising its power under sub-section (10), the provisions relating`
  line `to medical benefit under this Chapter shall apply, so far as may be, as if a reference therein to the State`
  line `Government were a reference to the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(12) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Code, in respect of establishments located in the States`
  line `where medical benefit is provided by the Corporation, the Central Government shall be the appropriate`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (54065)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `General provisions as to benefits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54065&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as may be provided in the regulations, no person`
  line `shall be entitled to commute for a lump sum any disablement benefit admissible under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as may be provided in the regulations, no person shall be entitled to sickness benefit or`
  line `disablement benefit for temporary disablement on any day on which he works or remains on leave or on a`
  line `holiday in respect of which he receives wages or on any day on which he remains on strike.`
  line
  line `(3) A person who is in receipt of sickness benefit or disablement benefit (other than benefit granted on`
  line `permanent disablement)-`
  line
  line `(a) shall remain under medical treatment at a dispensary, hospital, clinic or other institution provided`
  line `under this Chapter, and shall carry out the instructions given by the medical officer or medical attendant`
  line `in-charge thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) shall not while under treatment do anything which might retard or prejudice his chances of`
  line recovery;
  line
  line `(c) shall not leave the area in which medical treatment provided by this Chapter is being given,`
  line `without the permission of the medical officer, medical attendant or such other authority as may be`
  line `specified in this behalf by the regulations; and`
  line
  line `(d) shall allow himself to be examined by any duly appointed medical officer or other person`
  line `authorised by the Corporation in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) An Insured Person shall not be entitled to receive for the same period—`
  line
  line `(a) both sickness benefit and maternity benefit; or`
  line
  line `(b) both sickness benefit and disablement benefit for temporary disablement; or`
  line
  line `(c) both maternity benefit and disablement benefit for temporary disablement.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a person is entitled to more than one of the benefits mentioned in sub-section (4), he shall be`
  line `entitled to choose which benefit he shall receive.`
  line
  line `(6) If a person dies during any period for which he is entitled to a cash benefit under this Chapter, the`
  line `amount of such benefit up to and including the day of his death shall be paid to any person nominated by`
  line `the deceased person in writing in such form as may be specified in the regulations or, if there is no such`
  line `nomination, to the heir or legal representative of the deceased person.`
  line
  line `(7) (a) Any person eligible for availing dependant or disablement benefit under this Chapter shall not`
  line `be entitled to claim Employees’ Compensation from his employer under Chapter VII.`
  line
  line `(b) Any women employee eligible for availing maternity benefit under this Chapter shall not be entitled`
  line `to claim maternity benefit from her employer under Chapter VI.`
  line
  line `(8) Where any person has received any benefit or payment under this Chapter when he is not lawfully`
  line `entitled thereto, he shall be liable to repay to the Corporation the value of the benefit or the amount of such`
  line `payment, or in the case of death, his legal representative shall be liable to repay the same from the assets of`
  line `the deceased devolved on him.`
  line
  line `(9) The value of any benefits received other than cash payments shall be determined by such authority`
  line `as may be specified in the regulations made in this behalf and the decision of such authority shall be final.`
  line
  line `(10) The amount recoverable under this section may be recovered in the manner specified under`
  line `sections 129 to 132.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (54066)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Corporation’s rights when an employer fails to register, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54066&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any employer,—`
  line
  line `(a) fails or neglects to insure under section 28, an employee at the time of his appointment or within`
  line `such extended period as may be prescribed by the Central Government, as a result of which the`
  line `employee becomes disentitled to any benefit under this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(b) insures under section 28, an employee on or after the date of accident which resulted in personal`
  line `injury to such employee which has the effect of making such employee disentitled to receive any`
  line `dependant benefit or disablement benefit from the Corporation; or`
  line
  line `(c) fails or neglects to pay any contribution which under this Chapter he is liable to pay in respect of`
  line `any employee and by reason thereof such employee becomes disentitled to any benefit or becomes`
  line `entitled to a benefit on a lower scale,`
  line
  line `then, the Corporation may, on being satisfied in the manner prescribed by the Central Government that the`
  line `benefit is payable to the employee, pay to the employee benefit at such rate to which he is entitled or would`
  line `have been entitled if the failure or neglect would not have occurred, and the Corporation shall be entitled`
  line `to recover from the employer, subject to the employer being given an opportunity of being heard, the capitalised value of the benefit paid to the employee, to be calculated in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the capitalised value to be calculated may be adjusted for the payment of any contribution`
  line `and interest or damages that the employer is liable to pay for delay in the payment of or non-payment of`
  line `such contribution.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount recoverable under this section may be recovered as if it were an arrear of land revenue`
  line `or recovered in the manner specified under sections 129 to 132.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (54067)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Liability of owner or occupier of factories, etc, for excessive sickness benefit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54067&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the`
  line `Corporation considers that the incidence of sickness among Insured Persons is excessive by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) insanitary working conditions in a factory or other establishment or the neglect of the owner or`
  line `occupier of the factory or other establishment to observe any health regulations enjoined on him by or`
  line `under any enactment for the time being in force, or`
  line
  line `(b) insanitary conditions of any tenements or lodgings occupied by Insured Persons and such`
  line `insanitary conditions are attributable to the neglect of the owner of the tenements or lodgings to observe`
  line `any health regulations enjoined on him by or under any enactments for the time being in force,`
  line
  line `then, the Corporation may send to the owner or occupier of the factory or other establishment or to the`
  line `owner of the tenements or lodgings, as the case may be, a claim for the payment of the amount of the extra`
  line `expenditure incurred by the Corporation as sickness benefit; and if the claim is not settled by agreement,`
  line `the Corporation may refer the matter, with a statement in support of its claim, to the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) If the appropriate Government is of the opinion that a prima facie case for inquiry is made out, it`
  line `may appoint a competent person or persons to hold an inquiry into the matter referred under sub-section`
  line `(1).`
  line
  line `(3) If upon inquiry under sub-section (2), it is proved to the satisfaction of the person or persons holding`
  line `the inquiry that the excess in incidence of sickness among the Insured Persons is due to the default or neglect`
  line `of the owner or occupier of the factory or other establishment or the owner of the tenements or lodgings, as`
  line `the case may be, the said person or persons shall determine, the amount of the extra expenditure incurred`
  line `as sickness benefit as well as the person or persons by whom the whole or any part of such amount shall be`
  line `paid to the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(4) A determination under sub-section (3) may be enforced as if it were a decree for payment of money`
  line `passed in a suit by a Civil Court.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of this section, “owner” of tenements or lodgings shall include any agent of the`
  line `owner and any person who is entitled to collect the rent of the tenements or lodgings as a lessee of the`
  line owner.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (54068)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Scheme for other beneficiaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54068&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, frame, amend, vary or rescind scheme for other beneficiaries and the`
  line `members of their families for providing medical facility in any hospital established by the Corporation in`
  line `any area which is underutilised on payment of user charges, and prescribe the terms and conditions subject`
  line `to which the scheme may be operated.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(a) "other beneficiaries"means persons other than employees insured under section 28;`
  line
  line `(b) "underutilised hospital" means any hospital not fully utilised by the employees insured under`
  line `section 28; and`
  line
  line `(c) "user charges" means the amount which is to be charged from other beneficiaries for medical`
  line `facilities as may be specified in the regulations after prior approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (54069)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Scheme for unorganised workers, gig workers and platform workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54069&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Chapter, the Central Government may, by notification, frame scheme for unorganised workers, gig workers and platform workers and the members of their families for providing`
  line `benefits admissible under this Chapter by the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(2) The contribution, user charges, scale of benefits, qualifying and eligibility conditions and other`
  line `terms and conditions subject to which the scheme may be operated shall be such as may be specified in the`
  line scheme.
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (54434)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Exemption of factories or other establishments belonging to Government or any local authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54434&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, after consultation with the Corporation, by notification and`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification, exempt any factory or other establishment`
  line `belonging to the Government or any local authority, from the operation of this Chapter if the employees in`
  line `any such factory or other establishment are otherwise in receipt of benefits substantially similar or superior`
  line `to the benefits provided under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (54071)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Contributions, etc., due to corporation to have priority over other debts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54071&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, any amount due under this Chapter shall be`
  line `the charge on the assets of the establishment to which it relates and shall be paid in priority in accordance`
  line `with the provisions of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (54072)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Constitution of Employees Insurance Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54072&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification,`
  line `constitute an Employees' Insurance Court for such local area as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The Employees’ Insurance Court shall consist of such number of Judges as the State Government`
  line `may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who is or has been a judicial officer or is a legal practitioner of five years' standing shall`
  line `be qualified to be a Judge of the Employees' Insurance Court.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may appoint the same Court for two or more local areas or two or more`
  line `Employees’ Insurance Courts for the same local area.`
  line
  line `(5) Where more than one Employees’ Insurance Court has been appointed for the same local area, the`
  line `State Government may by general or special order regulate the distribution of business between them.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (54073)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Matters to be decided by Employees Insurance court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54073&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any question or dispute or claim`
  line `arises as to—`
  line
  line `(a) whether any person is an employee within the meaning of this Code relating to this Chapter or`
  line `whether he is liable to pay the employee's contribution; or`
  line
  line `(b) the rate of wages or average daily wages of an employee for the purposes of this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(c) the rate of contribution payable by an employer in respect of any employee under this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(d) the person who is or was the employer in respect of any employee for the purposes of this Chapter;`
  line or
  line
  line `(e) the right of any person to any benefit under this Chapter and as to the amount and duration thereof;`
  line or
  line
  line `(f) any direction issued by the Corporation on a review of any payment of dependants' benefit under`
  line `this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which is in dispute between an employer and the Corporation relating to this`
  line `Chapter, or between an employer and a Contractor relating to this Chapter or between a person and the`
  line `Corporation relating to this Chapter or between an employee and an employer or Contractor relating to`
  line `this Chapter, in respect of any contribution or benefit or other dues payable or recoverable under this`
  line `Code relating to this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(h) claim for the recovery of contributions from the employer under this Code relating to this Chapter;`
  line or
  line
  line `(i) claim under sub-section (8) of section 41 for the recovery of the value or amount of the benefits`
  line `received by a person when he is not lawfully entitled thereto; or`
  line
  line `(j) claim against an employer under section 42; or`
  line
  line `(k) order of the appellate authority under section 126 in respect of Chapter IV; or`
  line
  line `(l) claim by an employer to recover contributions from any contractor under this Code relating to this`
  line `Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(m) any other claim for the recovery of any benefit admissible under this Chapter, such matter shall`
  line `be decided by the Employers' Insurance Court.`
  line
  line `(2) No matter which is in dispute between an employer and the Corporation in respect of any`
  line `contribution or any other dues under this Chapter shall be raised by the employer in the Employees'`
  line `Insurance Court unless he has deposited with that Court fifty per cent. of the amount due from him as`
  line `claimed by the Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Employees' Insurance Court may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, waive or`
  line `reduce the amount to be deposited under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) No Civil Court shall have jurisdiction to decide or deal with any question or dispute as specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) or to adjudicate on any liability which by or under this Code relating to this Chapter is to be`
  line `decided by a medical board, or by a medical appeal tribunal or by the Employees' Insurance Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (54074)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Powers of Employees Insurance court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54074&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Employees' Insurance Court shall have all the`
  line `powers of a Civil Court for the purposes of summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses,`
  line `compelling the discovery and production of documents and material objects, administering oath and`
  line `recording evidence and such court shall be deemed to be a Civil Court within the meaning of section 195`
  line `and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(2) The Employees' Insurance Court shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) All costs incidental to any proceeding before an Employees' Insurance Court shall, subject to such`
  line `rules as may be made in this behalf by the State Government, be in the discretion of that court.`
  line
  line `(4) An order of the Employees' Insurance Court shall be enforceable by it as if it were a decree passed`
  line `in a suit by a Civil Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (54075)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Proceedings of Employees Insurance courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54075&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) The manner of commencement of`
  line `proceedings before the Employees’ Insurance Court, fees and procedure thereof shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the limitation for initiating the proceedings by the aggrieved person in the Employees'`
  line `Insurance Court shall be three years from the date on which the cause of action arises:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the “arising of cause of action” in respect of a claim by the Insured Person or`
  line `dependants; by the Corporation for recovering contribution (including interests and damages) from the`
  line `employer; and the claim by the employer for recovering contributions from a Contractor and the time within`
  line `which such claims, recovery or contribution, from employer by the Corporation and recovery of`
  line `contribution by the employer from the Contractor, shall be as specified in the regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Any application, appearance or act required to be made or done by any person to, or before, an`
  line `Employees' Insurance Court (other than appearance of a person required for the purpose of his examination`
  line `as a witness) may be made or done by a legal practitioner or by an officer of a registered trade union`
  line `authorised in writing by such person or with the permission of that Court, by any other person so authorised.`
  line
  line `(3) An Employees' Insurance Court may submit any question of law for the decision of the High Court`
  line `and if it does so shall decide the question pending before it in accordance with such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (54076)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54076&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as expressly provided in this section, no appeal shall lie from`
  line `an order of an Employees' Insurance Court.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal shall lie to the High Court from an order of an Employees' Insurance Court, if it involves`
  line `a substantial question of law.`
  line
  line `(3) The appeal shall be filed under this section within a period of sixty days from the date of the order`
  line `made by the Employees' Insurance Court.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sections 5 and 12 of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963) shall apply to appeals`
  line `under this section.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Corporation has presented an appeal against an order of the Employees' Insurance Court,`
  line `that Court may, and if so directed by the High Court, shall, pending the decision of the appeal, withhold the`
  line `payment of any sum directed to be paid by the order appealed against.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (54077)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Payment of gratuity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54077&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) Gratuity shall be payable to an employee on the termination of his`
  line `employment after he has rendered continuous service for not less than five years,---`
  line
  line `(a) on his superannuation; or`
  line
  line `(b) on his retirement or resignation; or`
  line
  line `(c) on his death or disablement due to accident or disease; or`
  line
  line `(d) on termination of his contract period under fixed term employment; or`
  line
  line `(e) on happening of any such event as may be notified by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of working journalist as defined in clause (f) of section 2 of the Working`
  line `Journalists and Other Newspaper Employees (Condition of Service) and Miscellaneous Provisions Act,`
  line `1955 (45 of 1955), the expression "five years" occurring in this sub-section shall be deemed to be three`
  line `years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the completion of continuous service of five years shall not be necessary where`
  line `the termination of the employment of any employee is due to death or disablement or expiration of fixed`
  line `term employment or happening of any such event as may be notified by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in the case of death of the employee, gratuity payable to him shall be paid to his`
  line `nominee or, if no nomination has been made, to his heirs, and where any such nominees or heirs is a minor,`
  line `the share of such minor, shall be deposited with the competent authority as may be notified by the`
  line `appropriate Government who shall invest the same for the benefit of such minor in such bank or other`
  line `financial institution, as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government, until such minor attains majority.`
  line
  line `(2) For every completed year of service or part thereof in excess of six months, the employer shall pay`
  line `gratuity to an employee at the rate of fifteen days' wages or such number of days as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government, based on the rate of wages last drawn by the employee concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a piece-rated employee, daily wages shall be computed on the average of`
  line `the total wages received by him for a period of three months immediately preceding the termination of his`
  line `employment, and, for this purpose, the wages paid for any overtime work shall not be taken into account:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of an employee who is employed in a seasonal establishment and who`
  line `is not so employed throughout the year, the employer shall pay the gratuity at the rate of seven days' wages`
  line `for each season:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in the case of an employee employed on fixed term employment or a deceased`
  line `employee, the employer shall pay gratuity on pro rata basis.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of gratuity payable to an employee shall not exceed such amount as may be notified by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purpose of computing the gratuity payable to an employee who is employed, after his`
  line `disablement, on reduced wages, his wages for the period preceding his disablement shall be taken to be the`
  line `wages received by him during that period, and his wages for the period subsequent to his disablement shall`
  line `be taken to be the wages as so reduced.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall affect the right of an employee to receive better terms of gratuity under`
  line `any award or agreement or contract with the employer.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),---`
  line
  line `(a) the gratuity of an employee, whose services have been terminated for any act, wilful omission or`
  line `negligence causing any damage or loss to, or destruction of, property belonging to the employer, shall`
  line `be forfeited to the extent of the damage or loss so caused;`
  line
  line `(b) the gratuity payable to an employee may be wholly or partially forfeited---`
  line
  line `(i) if the services of such employee have been terminated for his riotous or disorderly conduct or`
  line `any other act of violence on his part, or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the services of such employee have been terminated for any act which constitutes an offence`
  line `involving moral turpitude, provided such offence is committed by him in the course of his employment.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--- For the purposes of this Chapter, employee does not include any such person who`
  line `holds a post under the Central Government or a State Government and is governed by any other Act or by`
  line `any rules providing for payment of gratuity.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---For the purposes of this section, disablement means such disablement as incapacitates`
  line `an employee for the work which he was capable of performing before the accident or disease, resulting in`
  line `such disablement.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.--- For the purposes of this section, it is clarified that in the case of a monthly rated`
  line `employee, the fifteen days' wages shall be calculated by dividing the monthly rate of wages last drawn by`
  line `him by twenty-six and multiplying the quotient by fifteen.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (54078)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Continuous service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54078&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter,---(A) an employee shall be said to be in`
  line `continuous service for a period if he has, for that period, been in uninterrupted service, including service`
  line `which may be interrupted on account of sickness, accident, leave, absence from duty without leave (not`
  line `being absence in respect of which an order treating the absence as break in service has been passed in`
  line `accordance with the standing orders, rules or regulations governing the employees of the establishment),`
  line `lay-off, strike or a lock-out or cessation of work not due to any fault of the employee, whether such`
  line `uninterrupted or interrupted service was rendered before or after the commencement of this Code;`
  line
  line `(B) where an employee (not being an employee employed in a seasonal establishment) is not in`
  line `continuous service within the meaning of clause (A), for any period of one year or six months, he shall be`
  line `deemed to be in continuous service under the employer---`
  line
  line `(a) for the said period of one year, if the employee during the period of twelve calendar months`
  line `preceding the date with reference to which calculation is to be made, has actually worked under the`
  line `employer for not less than---`
  line
  line `(i) one hundred and ninety days, in the case of any employee employed below the ground in a`
  line `mine or in an establishment which works for less than six days in a week; and`
  line
  line `(ii) two hundred and forty days, in any other case;`
  line
  line `(b) for the said period of six months, if the employee during the period of six calendar months`
  line `preceding the date with reference to which the calculation is to be made, has actually worked under the`
  line `employer for not less than---`
  line
  line `(i) ninety-five days, in the case of an employee employed below the ground in a mine or in an`
  line `establishment which works for less than six days in a week; and`
  line
  line `(ii) one hundred and twenty days, in any other case.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this clause, the number of days on which an employee has`
  line `actually worked under an employer shall include the days on which---`
  line
  line `(i) he has been laid-off under an agreement or as permitted by standing orders made under the`
  line `Industrial Employment (Standing Orders) Act, 1946 (20 of 1946), or under the Industrial Disputes`
  line `Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or under any other law applicable to the establishment;`
  line
  line `(ii) he has been on leave with full wages, earned in the previous year;`
  line
  line `(iii) he has been absent due to temporary disablement caused by accident arising out of and in the`
  line `course of his employment; and`
  line
  line `(iv) in the case of a female, she has been on maternity leave; so, however, that the total period of`
  line `such maternity leave does not exceed twenty-six weeks;`
  line
  line `(C) where an employee, employed in a seasonal establishment, is not in continuous service within the`
  line `meaning of clause (A), for any period of one year or six months, he shall be deemed to be in continuous`
  line `service under the employer for such period if he has actually worked for not less than seventy-five per cent.`
  line `of the number of days on which the establishment was in operation during such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (54079)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title Nomination.
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54079&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each employee, who has completed one year of service, shall make, a`
  line `nomination within such time, in such form and in such manner, as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) An employee may, in his nomination, distribute the amount of gratuity payable to him under this`
  line `Chapter amongst more than one nominee.`
  line
  line `(3) If an employee has a family at the time of making a nomination, the nomination shall be made in`
  line `favour of one or more members of his family, and any nomination made by such employee in favour of a`
  line `person who is not a member of his family shall be void.`
  line
  line `(4) If at the time of making a nomination the employee has no family, the nomination may be made in`
  line `favour of any person or persons but if the employee subsequently acquires a family, such nomination shall`
  line `forthwith become invalid and the employee shall make, within such time as may be prescribed by the`
  line `appropriate Government, a fresh nomination in favour of one or more members of his family.`
  line
  line `(5) A nomination may, subject to the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4), be modified by an employee`
  line `at any time, after giving to his employer a written intimation in such form and in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government, of his intention to do so.`
  line
  line `(6) If a nominee predeceases the employee, the interest of the nominee shall revert to the employee`
  line `who shall make a fresh nomination, in the form prescribed by the appropriate Government, in respect of`
  line `such interest.`
  line
  line `(7) Every nomination, fresh nomination or alteration of nomination, as the case may be, shall be sent`
  line `by the employee to his employer, who shall keep the same in his safe custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (54080)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Determination of amount of gratuity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54080&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person who is eligible for payment of gratuity under`
  line `this Chapter or any person authorised, in writing, to act on his behalf shall send a written application to the`
  line `employer, within such time and in such form, as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government, for`
  line `payment of such gratuity.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as gratuity becomes payable, the employer shall, whether an application referred to in subsection (1) has been made or not, determine the amount of gratuity and give notice in writing to the person`
  line `to whom the gratuity is payable and also to the competent authority specifying the amount of gratuity so`
  line determined.
  line
  line `(3) The employer shall arrange to pay the amount of gratuity within thirty days from the date it becomes`
  line `payable to the person to whom the gratuity is payable.`
  line
  line `(4) If the amount of gratuity payable under sub-section (3) is not paid by the employer within the period`
  line `specified in sub-section (3), the employer shall pay, from the date on which the gratuity becomes payable`
  line `to the date on which it is paid, simple interest at such rate, not exceeding the rate notified by the Central`
  line `Government from time to time for repayment of long term deposits:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such interest shall be payable if the delay in the payment is due to the fault of the`
  line `employee and the employer has obtained permission in writing from the competent authority for the delayed`
  line `payment on this ground.`
  line
  line `(5) (a) If there is any dispute as to the amount of gratuity payable to an employee under this Chapter or`
  line `as to the admissibility of any claim of, or in relation to, an employee for payment of gratuity, or as to the`
  line `person entitled to receive the gratuity, the employer shall deposit with the competent authority such amount`
  line `as he admits to be payable by him as gratuity.`
  line
  line `(b) Where there is a dispute with regard to any matter or matters specified in clause (a), the employer`
  line `or employee or any other person raising the dispute may make an application to the competent authority in`
  line `the form prescribed by the appropriate Government for deciding the dispute.`
  line
  line `(c) The competent authority shall, after due inquiry and after giving the parties to the dispute a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard, determine the matter or matters in dispute and if, as a result of such`
  line `inquiry any amount is found to be payable to the employee, the competent authority shall direct the`
  line `employer to pay such amount or, as the case may be, such amount as reduced by the amount already`
  line `deposited by the employer.`
  line
  line `(d) The competent authority shall pay the amount deposited, including the excess amount, if any,`
  line `deposited by the employer, to the person entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(e) As soon as may be after a deposit is made under clause (a), the competent authority shall pay the`
  line `amount of the deposit—`
  line
  line `(i) to the applicant where he is the employee; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the applicant is not the employee, to the nominee or, as the case may be, the guardian of`
  line `such nominee or heir of the employee if the competent authority is satisfied that there is no dispute as`
  line `to the right of the applicant to receive the amount of gratuity.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purpose of conducting an inquiry under sub-section (5), the competent authority shall have`
  line `the same powers as are vested in a court, while trying a suit, under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of`
  line `1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person or examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses.`
  line
  line `(7) Any inquiry under this section shall be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of section 193,`
  line `section 228 and for the purpose of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(8) Any person aggrieved by an order under sub-section (5) may, within sixty days from the date of the`
  line `receipt of the order, prefer an appeal to the appropriate Government or such other authority as may be`
  line `specified by the appropriate Government in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government or the appellate authority, as the case may be, may, if it is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within the said`
  line `period of sixty days, extend the said period by a further period of sixty days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal by an employer shall be admitted unless at the time of preferring the`
  line `appeal, the appellant either produces a certificate of the competent authority to the effect that the appellant`
  line `has deposited with him an amount equal to the amount of gratuity required to be deposited under subsection (5), or deposits with the appellate authority such amount.`
  line
  line `(9) The appropriate Government or the appellate authority, as the case may be, may, after giving the`
  line `parties to the appeal a reasonable opportunity of being heard, confirm, modify, or reverse the decision of`
  line `the competent authority`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (54081)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Compulsory Insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54081&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as may be notified by the appropriate`
  line `Government in this behalf, every employer, other than an employer or an establishment belonging to, or`
  line `under the control of, the Central Government or a State Government, shall, subject to the provisions of subsection (2), obtain an insurance in the manner prescribed by the Central Government, for his liability for`
  line `payment towards the gratuity under this Chapter, from any insurance company regulated by the Authority`
  line `as defined under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Insurance Regulatory and Development`
  line `Authority Act, 1999 (41 of 1999):`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different establishments or class of establishments`
  line `or for different areas.`
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government, exempt any employer who had already established an approved gratuity fund in respect of his`
  line `employees and who desires to continue such arrangement, and every employer employing five hundred or`
  line `more persons who establishes an approved gratuity fund in the manner prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government from the provisions of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of effectively implementing the provisions of this section, every employer shall`
  line `within such time as may be prescribed by the Central Government get his establishment registered with the`
  line `competent authority in the manner prescribed by the appropriate Government and no employer shall be`
  line `registered under the provisions of this section unless he has taken an insurance referred to in sub-section`
  line `(1) or has established an approved gratuity fund referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government may provide for the composition of the Board of Trustees of the`
  line `approved gratuity fund and for the recovery by the competent authority of the amount of the gratuity payable`
  line `to an employee from the insurer with whom an insurance has been taken under sub-section (1), or as the`
  line `case may be, the Board of Trustees of the approved gratuity fund, in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an employer fails to make any payment by way of premium in respect of the insurance`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) or by way of contribution to an approved gratuity fund referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2), he shall be liable to pay the amount of gratuity due under this Chapter (including interest,`
  line `if any, for delayed payments) forthwith to the competent authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- In this section, "approved gratuity fund" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it`
  line `in sub-section (5) of section 2 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (54082)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54082&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by notification, appoint any officer`
  line `of that Government having such qualifications and experience as may be prescribed by that Government to`
  line `be a competent authority for implementation of any provision of this Chapter for such area as may be`
  line `specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where more than one competent authority has been appointed for any area, the appropriate`
  line `Government may, by general or special order, regulate the distribution of business among them.`
  line
  line `(3) Any competent authority may, for the purpose of deciding any matter referred to him for decision`
  line `under this Chapter, choose one or more persons possessing special knowledge of any matter relevant to the`
  line `matter under reference to assist him in holding the inquiry relating thereto.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (54083)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Employment of, or work by, women prohibited during certain period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54083&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) No employer shall`
  line `knowingly employ a woman in any establishment during the six weeks immediately following the day of`
  line `her delivery, miscarriage or medical termination of pregnancy.`
  line
  line `(2) No woman shall work in any establishment during the six weeks immediately following the day of`
  line `her delivery, miscarriage or medical termination of pregnancy.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of section 62, no pregnant woman shall, on a request being`
  line `made by her in this behalf, be required by her employer to do, during the period specified in sub-section(4), any work which is of an arduous nature or which involves long hours of standing or which in any way is likely to interfere with her pregnancy or the normal development of the foetus or is likely to cause her`
  line `miscarriage or otherwise to adversely affect her health.`
  line
  line `(4) The period referred to in sub-section (3) shall be---`
  line
  line `(a) the period of one month immediately preceding the period of six weeks, before the date of her`
  line `expected delivery;`
  line
  line `(b) any period during the said period of six weeks for which the pregnant woman does not avail of`
  line `leave of absence under section 62.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, the expression "any work of arduous nature" shall mean`
  line `any work which involve or require strenuous effort or is difficult and tiring in nature.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (54084)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Right to payment of maternity benefit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54084&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Code, every`
  line `woman shall be entitled to, and her employer shall be liable for, the payment of maternity benefit at the rate`
  line `of the average daily wage for the period of her actual absence, that is to say, the period immediately`
  line `preceding the day of her delivery, and any period immediately following that day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, "the average daily wage" means the average of the`
  line `woman's wages payable to her for the days on which she has worked during the period of three calendar`
  line `months immediately preceding the date from which she absents herself on account of maternity, subject to`
  line `the minimum rate of wage fixed or revised under the Code on Wages, 2019 (29 of 2019).`
  line
  line `(2) No woman shall be entitled to maternity benefit unless she has actually worked in an establishment`
  line `of the employer from whom she claims maternity benefit, for a period of not less than eighty days in the`
  line `twelve months immediately preceding the date of her expected delivery.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of calculating the period under this sub-section, the days on which a`
  line `woman has actually worked in the establishment, the days for which she has been laid off or was on holidays`
  line `declared under any law for the time being in force to be holidays with wages, during the period of twelve`
  line `months immediately preceding the expected date of her delivery shall be taken into account.`
  line
  line `(3) The maximum period for which any woman shall be entitled to maternity benefit shall be twentysix weeks of which not more than eight weeks shall precede the expected date of her delivery:`
  line
  line `Provided that the maximum period entitled to maternity benefit by a woman having two or more`
  line `surviving children shall be twelve weeks of which not more than six weeks shall precede the date of her`
  line `expected delivery:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where a woman dies during this period, the maternity benefit shall be payable`
  line `only for the days up to and including the day of her death:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where a woman, having been delivered of a child, dies during her delivery or during`
  line `the period immediately following the date of her delivery for which she is entitled for the maternity benefit,`
  line `leaving behind in either case the child, the employer shall be liable for the maternity benefit for that entire`
  line `period but if the child also dies during the said period, then, for the days up to and including the date of the`
  line `death of the child.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, "child" includes a stillborn child.`
  line
  line `(4) A woman who legally adopts a child below the age of three months or a commissioning mother`
  line `shall be entitled to maternity benefit for a period of twelve weeks from the date the child is handed over to`
  line `the adopting mother or the commissioning mother, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(5) In case the work assigned to a woman is of such nature that she may work from home, the employer`
  line `may allow her to do so after availing of the maternity benefit for such period and on such conditions as the`
  line `employer and the woman may mutually agree.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (54085)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Continuance of payment of maternity benefit in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54085&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Every woman entitled to the`
  line `payment of maternity benefit under this Chapter, shall, notwithstanding the application of Chapter IV to`
  line `the factory or other establishment in which she is employed, continue to be so entitled until she becomes`
  line `qualified to claim maternity benefit under section 32.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (54086)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Notice of claim for maternity benefit and payment thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54086&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any woman employed in an`
  line `establishment and entitled to maternity benefit under the provisions of this Chapter may give notice in`
  line `writing in such form as may be prescribed by the Central Government, to her employer, stating that her`
  line `maternity benefit and any other amount to which she may be entitled under this Chapter may be paid to her`
  line `or to such person as she may nominate in the notice and that she will not work in any establishment during`
  line `the period for which she receives maternity benefit.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of a woman who is pregnant, such notice shall state the date from which she will be`
  line `absent from work, not being a date earlier than eight weeks from the date of her expected delivery.`
  line
  line `(3) Any woman who has not given the notice when she was pregnant may give such notice as soon as`
  line `possible after her delivery.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of the notice, the employer shall permit such woman to absent herself from the`
  line `establishment during the period for which she receives the maternity benefit.`
  line
  line `(5) The amount of maternity benefit for the period preceding the date of her expected delivery shall be`
  line `paid in advance by the employer to the woman on production of such proof as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government that the woman is pregnant, and the amount due for the subsequent period shall be`
  line `paid by the employer to the woman within forty-eight hours of production of such proof as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Central Government that the woman has been delivered of a child.`
  line
  line `(6) The failure to give notice under this section shall not disentitle a woman to maternity benefit or any`
  line `other amount under this Chapter if she is otherwise entitled to such benefit or amount and in any such case`
  line `an Inspector-cum-Facilitator may either of his own motion or on an application made to him by the woman,`
  line `order the payment of such benefit or amount within such period as may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (54087)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Payment of maternity benefit in case of death of a woman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54087&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `If a woman entitled to maternity`
  line `benefit or any other amount under this Chapter, dies before receiving such maternity benefit or amount, or`
  line `where the employer is liable for maternity benefit under the second proviso to sub-section (3) of section 60,`
  line `the employer shall pay such benefit or amount to the person nominated by the woman in the notice given`
  line `under section 62 and in case there is no such nominee, to her legal representative.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (54088)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Payment of medical bonus.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54088&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Every woman entitled to maternity benefit under this Chapter shall`
  line `also be entitled to receive from her employer a medical bonus of three thousand five hundred rupees or such`
  line `amount as may be notified by the Central Government, if no pre-natal confinement and post-natal care is`
  line `provided for by the employer free of charge.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (54089)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Leave for miscarriage, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54089&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) In case of miscarriage, or medical termination of pregnancy, a`
  line `woman shall, on production of such proof as may be prescribed by the Central Government, be entitled to`
  line `leave with wages at the rate of maternity benefit, for a period of six weeks immediately following the day`
  line `of her miscarriage or, as the case may be, her medical termination of pregnancy.`
  line
  line `(2) In case of tubectomy operation, a woman shall, on production of such proof as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government, be entitled to leave with wages at the rate of maternity benefit for a period of`
  line `two weeks immediately following the day of her tubectomy operation.`
  line
  line `(3) A woman suffering from illness arising out of pregnancy, delivery, premature birth of child,`
  line `miscarriage or medical termination of pregnancy shall, on production of such proof as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government, be entitled, in addition to the period of absence allowed to her under section`
  line `62, or, as the case may be, under sub-section (1), to leave with wages at the rate of maternity benefit for a`
  line `maximum period of one month.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (54090)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Nursing breaks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54090&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Every woman delivered of a child who returns to duty after such delivery shall,`
  line `in addition to the interval for rest allowed to her, be allowed in the course of her daily work two breaks of`
  line `such duration as may be prescribed by the Central Government, for nursing the child until the child attains`
  line `the age of fifteen months.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (54091)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Creche facility.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54091&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every establishment to which this Chapter applies, in which fifty employees`
  line `or such number of employees as may be prescribed by the Central Government, are employed shall have the facility of crèche within such distance as may be prescribed by the Central Government, either`
  line `separately or along with common facilities:`
  line
  line `Provided that the employer shall allow four visits a day to the crèche by the woman, which shall also`
  line `include the intervals of rest allowed to her:`
  line
  line `Provided further that an establishment may avail common crèche facility of the Central Government,`
  line `State Government, municipality or private entity or provided by non-Governmental organisation or by any`
  line `other organisation or group of establishments who may pool their resources for setting up of common crèche`
  line `in the manner as they may agree for such purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Every establishment to which this Chapter applies shall intimate in writing and electronically to`
  line `every woman at the time of her initial appointment in such establishment regarding every benefit available`
  line `under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (54092)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Dismissal for absence during pregnancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54092&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a woman absents herself from work in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Chapter, it shall be unlawful for her employer to discharge or dismiss`
  line `her during or on account of such absence or to give notice of discharge or dismissal on such a day that the`
  line `notice will expire during such absence, or to vary to her disadvantage any of the conditions of her service:`
  line
  line `Provided that the discharge or dismissal of a woman at any time during her pregnancy, if the woman`
  line `but for such discharge or dismissal would have been entitled to maternity benefit or medical bonus under`
  line `this Chapter, shall not have the effect of depriving her of the maternity benefit or medical bonus:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the dismissal is for any gross misconduct as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government, the employer may, by order in writing, communicated to the woman, deprive her of`
  line `the maternity benefit or medical bonus, or both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any woman deprived of maternity benefit or medical bonus, or both, or discharged or dismissed`
  line `under sub-section (1), may, within sixty days from the date on which order of such deprivation or discharge`
  line `or dismissal is communicated to her, appeal to the competent authority, and the decision of that authority`
  line `on such appeal, whether the woman should or should not be deprived of maternity benefit or medical bonus`
  line `or both, or discharged or dismissed, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (54093)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `No deduction of wages in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54093&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `No deduction from the normal and usual daily wages`
  line `of a woman entitled to maternity benefit under the provisions of this Chapter shall be made by reason only`
  line of—
  line
  line `(a) the nature of work assigned to her by virtue of the provisions contained in section 59; or`
  line
  line `(b) breaks for nursing the child allowed to her under the provisions of section 66.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (54094)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Forfeiture of maternity benefit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54094&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `A woman who works for remuneration during the period she`
  line `has been permitted by an employer to absent herself for availing the maternity benefits provided under this`
  line `Chapter shall not be entitled to receive maternity benefit for such period.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (54095)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Duties of employer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54095&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `An abstract of the provisions of this Chapter and the rules relating thereto`
  line `in the language or languages of the locality shall be exhibited in a conspicuous place by the employer in`
  line `every part of the establishment in which women are employed.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (54096)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Power of Inspector-cum-facilitator to direct payments to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54096&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any woman claiming`
  line that,---
  line
  line `(a) maternity benefit or any other amount to which she is entitled under this Chapter and any person`
  line `claiming that payment due under this Chapter has been improperly withheld;`
  line
  line `(b) her employer has discharged or dismissed her during or on account of her absence from work in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Chapter,`
  line
  line `may make a complaint to the Inspector-cum-Facilitator.`
  line
  line `(2) The Inspector-cum-Facilitator may, on receipt of a complaint referred to in sub-section (1), make`
  line `an inquiry or cause an inquiry to be made and if satisfied that---`
  line
  line `(a) payment has been wrongfully withheld, may direct the payment to be made in accordance with`
  line `his order in writing;`
  line
  line `(b) she has been discharged or dismissed during or on account of her absence from work in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Chapter,`
  line
  line `may pass such orders as he deems just and proper according to the circumstances of the case.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by the order of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator under sub-section (2) may,`
  line `within thirty days from the date on which such order is communicated to such person, appeal to the authority`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The decision of the authority referred to in sub-section (3), where an appeal has been preferred to it`
  line `under that sub-section or of the Inspector-cum-Facilitator where no such appeal has been preferred, shall`
  line `be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (54097)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Reports of fatal accidents and serious bodily injuries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54097&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, by any law for the time being`
  line `in force, notice is required to be given to any authority, by or on behalf of an employer, of any accident`
  line `occurring in his premises which results in death or serious bodily injury, the person required to give the`
  line `notice shall, within seven days of the death or serious bodily injury, send a report to the competent authority`
  line `giving the circumstances attending the death or serious bodily injury:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the State Government has so specified, the person required to give the notice may`
  line `instead of sending such report to the competent authority send it to the authority to whom he is required to`
  line `give the notice.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, "serious bodily injury" means an injury which`
  line `involves, or in all probability will involve the permanent loss of the use of, or permanent injury to, any`
  line `limb, or the permanent loss of or injury to the sight or hearing, or the fracture of any limb, or the enforced`
  line `absence of the injured person from work for a period exceeding twenty days.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification, extend the provisions of sub-section (1) to any class of`
  line `premises other than those coming within the scope of that sub-section, and may, by such notification,`
  line `specify the persons who shall send the report to the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to establishments to which Chapter IV, relating to Employees'`
  line `State Insurance Corporation, applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (54098)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Employer’s liability for compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54098&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `(1) If personal injury is caused to an employee by`
  line `accident or an occupational disease listed in the Third Schedule arising out of and in the course of his`
  line `employment, his employer shall be liable to pay compensation in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the employer shall not be so liable—`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of such injury which does not result in the total or partial disablement of the employee`
  line `for a period exceeding three days; and`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of such injury, not resulting in death or permanent total disablement caused by an`
  line `accident which is directly attributable to—`
  line
  line `(i) the employee having been at the time thereof under the influence of drink or drugs, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the wilful disobedience of the employee to an order expressly given, or to a rule expressly`
  line `framed, for the purpose of securing the safety of employees, or`
  line
  line `(iii) the wilful removal or disregard by the employee of any safety guard or other device which he`
  line `knew to have been provided for the purpose of securing the safety of employee.`
  line
  line `(2) An accident or an occupational disease referred to in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to arise out of`
  line `and in the course of an employee's employment notwithstanding that he is at the time of the accident or at the time of contracting the occupational disease, referred to in that sub-section, acting in contravention of`
  line `the provisions of any law applicable to him, or of any orders given by or on behalf of his employer or that`
  line `he is acting without instructions from his employer, if—`
  line
  line `(a) such accident or contracting of such occupational disease would have been deemed so to have`
  line `arisen had the act not been done in contravention as aforesaid or without instructions from his employer,`
  line `as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(b) the act is done for the purpose of, and in connection with, the employer's trade or business.`
  line
  line `(3) If an employee employed in any employment specified in the Second Schedule contracts any disease`
  line `specified in the Third Schedule, being an occupational disease peculiar to that employment whilst in the`
  line `service of an employer in whose service he has been employed for a continuous period of not less than six`
  line `months, then, such disease shall be deemed to be an injury by accident within the meaning of this section`
  line `and unless the contrary is proved, the accident shall be deemed to have arisen out of and in the course of`
  line `the employment.`
  line
  line `(4) An accident occurring to an employee while commuting from his residence to the place of`
  line `employment for duty or from the place of employment to his residence after performing duty, shall be`
  line `deemed to have arisen out of and in the course of employment if nexus between the circumstances, time`
  line `and place in which the accident occurred and his employment is established.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government or the State Government, after giving, by notification, not less than three`
  line `months' notice of its intention so to do, may, by a like notification, modify or add any description of`
  line `employment to the employments specified in the Second Schedule, and occupational diseases specified in`
  line `the Third Schedule and shall specify in the case of employments so modified or added, the diseases which`
  line `shall be deemed for the purposes of this section to be occupational diseases peculiar to those employments`
  line `respectively, and thereupon the provisions of sub-section (2) shall apply, in the case of a notification by the`
  line `Central Government, within the territories to which this Code extends or, in case of a notification by the`
  line `State Government, within that State as if such diseases had been declared by this Code to be occupational`
  line `diseases peculiar to those employments.`
  line
  line `(6) Save as provided by sub-sections (2), (3) and (4), no compensation shall be payable to an employee`
  line `in respect of any accident or disease unless the accident or disease is directly attributable to a specific injury`
  line `by accident or disease arising out of and in the course of his employment.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing herein contained shall be deemed to confer any right to compensation on an employee in`
  line `respect of any accident or disease if he has instituted in a civil court a suit for damages in respect of the`
  line `accident or disease against the employer or any other person; and no suit for damages shall be maintainable`
  line `by an employee in any Court of law in respect of such accident or disease—`
  line
  line `(a) if he has instituted a claim to compensation in respect of the accident or disease before a competent`
  line `authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) if an agreement has been made between the employee and his employer providing for the payment`
  line `of compensation in respect of the accident or disease in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (54099)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Compensation in case of death of or injury in plantation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54099&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `If death or injury is caused to any`
  line `worker or a member of his family as a result of the collapse of a house provided by the employer in a`
  line `plantation, and the collapse is not solely and directly attributable to a fault on the part of any occupant of`
  line `the house or to a natural calamity, the employer shall be liable to pay compensation under section 76 and`
  line `the Sixth Schedule, so far as may be applicable.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, the expression "worker" means a person employed in`
  line `a plantation for hire or reward, whether directly or through any agency, to do any work, skilled, unskilled,`
  line `manual or clerical, and includes a person employed on contract for more than sixty days in a year, but does`
  line `not include---`
  line
  line `(i) a medical officer employed in the plantation;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person employed in the plantation (including any member of the medical staff) whose`
  line `monthly wages exceed the amount as determined by the appropriate Government, by notification, from`
  line `time to time;`
  line
  line `(iii) any person employed in the plantation primarily in a managerial or administrative capacity,`
  line `notwithstanding that his monthly wages do not exceed the amount as determined by the appropriate`
  line `Government, by notification, from time to time;`
  line
  line `(iv) any person temporarily employed in the plantation in any work relating to the construction,`
  line `development or maintenance of buildings, roads, bridges, drains or canals.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (54100)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Amount of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54100&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, the amount of`
  line `compensation shall be,---`
  line
  line `(a) where death results from the injury, an amount equal to fifty per cent. of the monthly wages of`
  line `the deceased employee multiplied by the relevant factor or an amount as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government from time to time, whichever is more;`
  line
  line `(b) where permanent total disablement results from the injury, an amount equal to sixty per cent. of`
  line `the monthly wages of the injured employee multiplied by the relevant factor or an amount as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government from time to time, whichever is more:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification, from time to time, enhance the amount of`
  line `compensation specified in clauses (a) and (b).`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of clauses (a) and (b), "relevant factor", in relation to an employee`
  line `means the factor specified in column (3) of the Sixth Schedule relating to factors against the corresponding`
  line `entry in column (2) thereof, specifying the number of years which are the same as the completed years of`
  line `the age of the employee on his last birthday immediately preceding the date on which the compensation fell`
  line due;
  line
  line `(c) where permanent partial disablement results from the injury,---`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an injury specified in Part II of the Fourth Schedule, such percentage of the`
  line `compensation which would have been payable in the case of permanent total disablement as is`
  line `specified therein as being the percentage of the loss of earning capacity caused by that injury; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of an injury not specified in the Fourth Schedule, such percentage of the`
  line `compensation payable in the case of permanent total disablement as is proportionate to the loss of`
  line `earning capacity (as assessed by the medical practitioner) permanently caused by the injury.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---For the purposes of this clause, where more injuries than one are caused by the same`
  line `accident, the amount of compensation payable under this head shall be aggregated but not so in any case as`
  line `to exceed the amount which would have been payable if permanent total disablement had resulted from the`
  line injuries.
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---In assessing the loss of earning capacity under sub-clause (ii), the medical practitioner`
  line `shall have due regard to the percentage of loss of earning capacity in relation to different injuries specified`
  line `in the Fourth Schedule;`
  line
  line `(d) where temporary disablement, whether total or partial, results from the injury, a half-monthly`
  line `payment of the sum equivalent to twenty-five per cent. of monthly wages of the employee, to be paid`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), while fixing the amount of compensation`
  line `payable to an employee in respect of an accident which occurred outside India, the competent authority`
  line `shall take into account the amount of compensation, if any, awarded to such employee in accordance with`
  line `the law of the country in which the accident occurred and shall reduce the amount fixed by him by the`
  line `amount of compensation awarded to the employee in accordance with the law of that country.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, specify for the purposes of sub-section (1), such`
  line `monthly wages in relation to an employee as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The half-monthly payment referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1) shall be payable on the`
  line `sixteenth day---`
  line
  line `(i) from the date of disablement where such disablement lasts for a period of twenty-eight days or`
  line `more; or`
  line
  line `(ii) after the expiry of a waiting period of three days from the date of disablement, where such`
  line `disablement lasts for a period of less than twenty-eight days; and thereafter half-monthly during the`
  line `disablement or during a period of five years, whichever is shorter:`
  line
  line `Provided that---`
  line
  line `(a) there shall be deducted from any lump sum or half-monthly payments to which the employee is`
  line `entitled, the amount of any payment or allowance which the employee has received from the employer`
  line `by way of compensation during the period of disablement prior to the receipt of such lump sum or of`
  line `the first half-monthly payment, as the case may be, and such payment or allowance which the employee`
  line `has received from the employer towards his medical treatment shall not be deemed to be a payment or`
  line `allowance received by him by way of compensation;`
  line
  line `(b) no half-monthly payment shall in any case exceed the amount, if any, by which half the amount`
  line `of the monthly wages of the employee before the accident exceeds half the amount of such wages which`
  line `he is earning after the accident.`
  line
  line `(5) The employee shall be reimbursed, the actual medical expenditure incurred by him for treatment of`
  line `injuries caused during the course of employment, by his employer.`
  line
  line `(6) On the ceasing of the disablement before the date on which any half-monthly payment falls due,`
  line `there shall be payable in respect of that half-month a sum proportionate to the duration of the disablement`
  line `in that half-month.`
  line
  line `(7) If the injury of the employee results in his death, the employer shall, in addition to the compensation`
  line `under sub-section (1), deposit with the competent authority a sum of not less than fifteen thousand rupees`
  line `or such amount as may be prescribed by the State Government, for payment of the same to the eldest`
  line `surviving dependant of the employee towards the expenditure of the funeral of such employee or where the`
  line `employee did not have a dependant or was not living with his dependant at the time of his death, to the`
  line `person who actually incurred such expenditure:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification from time to time, enhance the amount`
  line `specified in this sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (54101)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Compensation to be paid when due and damages for default.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54101&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) Compensation under section`
  line `76 shall be paid as soon as it falls due.`
  line
  line `(2) In cases where the employer does not accept the liability for compensation to the extent claimed, he`
  line `shall be bound to make provisional payment based on the extent of liability which he accepts, and, such`
  line `payment shall be deposited with the competent authority or made to the employee, as the case may be,`
  line `without prejudice to the right of the employee to make any further claim.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any employer is in default in paying the compensation due under this Chapter within one`
  line `month from the date it fell due, the competent authority shall,—`
  line
  line `(a) direct that the employer shall, in addition to the amount of the arrears, pay interest at such rate as`
  line `may be prescribed by the Central Government, on the amount due; and`
  line
  line `(b) if in his opinion, there is no justification for the delay, direct that the employer shall, in addition`
  line `to the amount of the arrears and interest thereon, pay a further sum not exceeding fifty per cent. of such`
  line `amount of arrears by way of damages:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order for the payment of damages shall not be passed under clause (b) without giving`
  line `a reasonable opportunity to the employer to show cause as to why it should not be passed.`
  line
  line `(4) The interest and the damages payable under sub-section (3) shall be paid to the employee or his`
  line `dependant, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (54102)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Method of calculating monthly wages for purposes of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54102&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this`
  line `Chapter, the expression "monthly wages" means the amount of wages deemed to be payable for a month's`
  line `service (whether the wages are payable by the month or by whatever other period or at piece rates), and`
  line `calculated as follows, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) where the employee has, during a continuous period of not less than twelve months immediately`
  line `preceding the accident, been in the service of the employer who is liable to pay compensation, the`
  line `monthly wages of the employee shall be one-twelfth of the total wages which have fallen due for`
  line `payment to him by the employer in the last twelve months of that period;`
  line
  line `(b) where the whole of the continuous period of service immediately preceding the accident during`
  line `which the employee was in the service of the employer who is liable to pay the compensation was less`
  line `than one month, the monthly wages of the employee shall be the average monthly amount which, during`
  line `the twelve months immediately preceding the accident, was being earned by an employee employed on`
  line `the same work by the same employer, or, if there was no employee so employed, by an employee`
  line `employed on similar work in the same locality;`
  line
  line `(c) in other cases including cases in which it is not possible for want of necessary information to`
  line `calculate the monthly wages under clause (b), the monthly wages shall be thirty times the total wages`
  line `earned in respect of the last continuous period of service immediately preceding the accident from the`
  line `employer who is liable to pay compensation, divided by the number of days comprising such period.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, "a period of service" shall be deemed to be continuous`
  line `which has not been interrupted by a period of absence from work exceeding fourteen days.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (54103)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title Review.
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54103&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any half-monthly payment payable under this Chapter, either under an agreement`
  line `between the parties or under the order of a competent authority, may be reviewed by the competent`
  line `authority, on the application either of the employer or of the employee accompanied by the certificate of a`
  line `medical practitioner that there has been a change in the condition of the employee or, subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed by the State Government, on application made without such certificate.`
  line
  line `(2) Any half-monthly payment may, on review under this section, subject to the provisions of this`
  line `Chapter, be continued, increased, decreased or ended, or if the accident is found to have resulted in`
  line `permanent disablement, be converted to the lump sum to which the employee is entitled less any amount`
  line `which he has already received by way of half-monthly payments.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (54104)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Commutation of half-monthly payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54104&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Any right to receive half-monthly payments may, by`
  line `agreement between the parties or, if the parties cannot agree and the payments have been continued for not`
  line `less than six months, on the application of either party to the competent authority be redeemed by the`
  line `payment of a lump sum of such amount as may be agreed to by the parties or determined by the competent`
  line `authority, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (54105)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Distribution of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54105&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) No payment of compensation in respect of an employee`
  line `whose injury has resulted in death, and no payment of a lump sum as compensation to a woman or a person`
  line `under a legal disability, shall be made otherwise than by deposit with the competent authority, and no such`
  line `payment made directly by an employer shall be deemed to be a payment of compensation:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of a deceased employee, an employer may make to any dependant, advances`
  line `on account of compensation of an amount equal to three months' wages of such employee and so much of`
  line `such amount as does not exceed the compensation payable to that dependant shall be deducted by the`
  line `competent authority from such compensation and repaid to the employer.`
  line
  line `(2) Any other sum amounting to not less than five thousand rupees which is payable as compensation`
  line `may be deposited with the competent authority on behalf of the person entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(3) The receipt of the competent authority shall be a sufficient discharge in respect of any compensation`
  line `deposited with him.`
  line
  line `(4) (a) On the deposit of any money under sub-section (1) as compensation in respect of a deceased`
  line `employee, the competent authority shall, if he thinks necessary, cause notice to be published or to be served on each dependant in such manner as he thinks fit, calling upon the dependants to appear before him on`
  line `such date as he may fix for determining the distribution of the compensation.`
  line
  line `(b) If the competent authority is satisfied after any inquiry which he may deem necessary, that no`
  line `dependant exists, he shall repay the balance of the money to the employer by whom it was paid.`
  line
  line `(c) The competent authority shall, on an application by the employer, furnish a statement showing in`
  line `detail all disbursements made.`
  line
  line `(5) The compensation deposited in respect of a deceased employee shall, subject to any deduction made`
  line `under sub-section (1), be apportioned by order by the competent authority among the dependants of the`
  line `deceased employee or any of them in such proportion as the competent authority thinks fit, or may, in the`
  line `discretion of the competent authority, be allotted to any one dependant:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority shall not make any order under this sub-section without hearing`
  line `the dependants and shall record reasons in the order for the apportionment of such compensation among`
  line `dependants or any of them, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any compensation deposited with the competent authority is payable to any person, other`
  line `than a woman or a person under legal disability, the competent authority may pay the compensation to the`
  line `person entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any lump sum deposited with the competent authority is payable to a woman or a person`
  line `under a legal disability, such sum may be invested, applied or otherwise dealt with for the benefit of the`
  line `woman, or of such person during his disability, in such manner as the competent authority may direct; and`
  line `where a half-monthly payment is payable to any person under a legal disability, the competent authority`
  line `may, of his own motion or on an application made to him in this behalf, order that the payment be made`
  line `during the disability to any dependant of the employee or to any other person, whom the competent authority`
  line `thinks fit to provide for the welfare of the employee.`
  line
  line `(8) Where, on application made to him in this behalf or otherwise, the competent authority is satisfied`
  line `that, on account of neglect of children on the part of a parent or on account of the variation of the`
  line `circumstances of any dependant or for any other sufficient cause, an order of the competent authority as to`
  line `the distribution of any sum paid as compensation or as to the manner in which any sum payable to any such`
  line `dependant is to be invested, applied or otherwise dealt with, ought to be varied, the competent authority`
  line `may make such orders for the variation of the former order as he thinks just in the circumstances of the`
  line `case:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order prejudicial to any person shall be made unless such person has been given`
  line `an opportunity of showing cause as to why the order should not be made, or shall be made in any case in`
  line `which it would involve the repayment by a dependant of any sum already paid to him.`
  line
  line `(9) Where the competent authority varies any order under sub-section (8) by reason of the fact that`
  line `payment of compensation to any person has been obtained by fraud, impersonation or other improper`
  line `means, any amount so paid to or on behalf of such person may be recovered in the manner as specified in`
  line `sub-section (10).`
  line
  line `(10) The competent authority may recover as an arrear of land revenue any amount referred to in`
  line `sub-section (9), and for such purpose the competent authority shall be deemed to be a public officer within`
  line `the meaning of section 5 of the Revenue Recovery Act, 1890 (1 of 1890).`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (54106)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Notice and claim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54106&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `(1) No claim for compensation shall be entertained by a competent authority`
  line `unless notice of the accident has been given in the manner hereinafter provided as soon as practicable after`
  line `the happening thereof and unless the claim is preferred before him within two years of the occurrence of`
  line `the accident or, in case of death, within two years from the date of death:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the accident is the contracting of a disease in respect of which the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 74 are applicable, the accident shall be deemed to have occurred on the first of`
  line `the days during which the employee was continuously absent from work in consequence of the disablement`
  line `caused by the disease:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of partial disablement due to the contracting of any such disease and which`
  line `does not force the employee to absent himself from work, the period of two years shall be counted from the`
  line `day the employee gives notice of the disablement to his employer:`
  line
  line `Provided also that if an employee who, having been employed in an employment for a continuous`
  line `period specified under sub-section (3) of section 74 in respect of that employment, ceases to be so employed`
  line `and develops symptoms of an occupational disease peculiar to that employment within two years of the`
  line `cessation of employment, the accident shall be deemed to have occurred on the day on which the symptoms`
  line `were first detected.`
  line
  line `(2) The want of or any defect or irregularity, in a notice given under sub-section (1), shall not be a bar`
  line `to the entertainment of a claim—`
  line
  line `(a) if the claim is preferred in respect of the death of an employee resulting from an accident which`
  line `occurred on the premises of the employer, or at any place where the employee at the time of the accident`
  line `was working under the control of the employer or of any person employed by him, and the employee`
  line `died on such premises or at such place, or on any premises belonging to the employer, or died without`
  line `having left the vicinity of the premises or place where the accident occurred, or`
  line
  line `(b) if the employer or any one of several employers or any person responsible to the employer for the`
  line `management of any branch of the trade or business in which the injured employee was employed had`
  line `knowledge of the accident from any other source at or about the time when it occurred:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may entertain and decide any claim to compensation in any case`
  line `notwithstanding that the notice has not been given, or the claim has not been preferred in due time as`
  line `provided under sub-section (1), if he is satisfied that the failure so to give the notice or prefer the claim, as`
  line `the case may be, was due to sufficient cause.`
  line
  line `(3) Every such notice shall give the name and address of the person injured and shall state the cause of`
  line `the injury and the date on which the accident happened, and shall be served on the employer or upon any`
  line `one of several employers, or upon any person responsible to the employer for the management of any branch`
  line `of the trade or business in which the injured employee was employed.`
  line
  line `(4) The appropriate Government may require that any class of employers as may be prescribed by that`
  line `Government shall maintain, at their premises at which employees are employed, a notice-book, in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed by that Government, which shall be readily accessible at all reasonable times to`
  line `any injured employee employed on the premises and to any person acting bona fide on his behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) A notice under this section may be served by delivering it at, or sending it by registered post`
  line `addressed to, the residence or any office or place of business of the person on whom it is to be served, or`
  line `where possible, electronically or, where a notice-book is maintained, by entry in the notice-book.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (54107)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Special provisions relating to accidents occurring outside Indian Territory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54107&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions`
  line `of this section shall, subject to the modifications specified in this section, apply in case of employees who`
  line are—
  line
  line `(a) masters of ships or seamen; or`
  line
  line `(b) captain and other members of crew of aircraft;`
  line
  line `(c) persons recruited by companies registered in India and working as such abroad;`
  line
  line `(d) persons sent for work abroad along with motor vehicles registered under the Motor Vehicles Act,`
  line `1988 (59 of 1988) as drivers, helpers, mechanics, cleaners or other employees.`
  line
  line `(2) The notice of the accident and the claim for compensation by a person injured may be served on the`
  line `following persons, as if they were the employer—`
  line
  line `(a) in case of accident where the person injured is a seamen, but not the master of the ship, on the`
  line `master of the ship;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of accident where the person injured is a member of crew of an aircraft, but not the captain`
  line `of the aircraft, on the captain of the aircraft;`
  line
  line `(c) in case of persons recruited by companies registered in India and working as such abroad, on the`
  line `local agent of the company;`
  line
  line `(d) in case of persons sent for work abroad along with motor vehicles as drivers, helpers, mechanics,`
  line `cleaners or other employees, on the local agent of the owner of the motor vehicle, in the country of the`
  line `accident:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the accident happened and the disablement commenced on board, the ship or`
  line `aircraft, as the case may be, then, it shall not be necessary for any seaman or members of the crew of aircraft`
  line `to give any notice of the accident.`
  line
  line `(3) The claim of compensation shall be made—`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the death of an employee referred to in sub-section (1), one year after the news of`
  line `the death has been received by the claimant;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case where the ship or the aircraft as the case may be, has been or is deemed to have been`
  line `lost with all hands, eighteen months of the date on which the ship or the aircraft was, or is deemed to`
  line `have been, so lost:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may entertain any claim to compensation in any case`
  line `notwithstanding that the claim has not been preferred in due time as provided in this sub-section, if he is`
  line `satisfied that the failure so to prefer the claim was due to sufficient cause.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an injured employee referred to in sub-section (1) is discharged or left behind in any part of`
  line `India or in any foreign country, then, any depositions taken by any Judge or Magistrate in that part or by`
  line `any Consular Officer in the foreign country and transmitted by the person by whom they are taken to the`
  line `Central Government or any State Government shall, in any proceedings for enforcing the claim, be`
  line `admissible in evidence—`
  line
  line `(a) if the deposition is authenticated by the signature of the Judge, Magistrate or Consular Officer`
  line `before whom it is made;`
  line
  line `(b) if the defendant or the person accused, as the case may be, had an opportunity by himself or his`
  line `agent to cross-examine the witness; and`
  line
  line `(c) if the deposition was made in the course of a criminal proceeding, on proof that the deposition`
  line `was made in the presence of the person accused,`
  line
  line `and it shall not be necessary in any case to prove the signature or official character of the person appearing`
  line `to have signed any such deposition and a certificate by such person that the defendant or the person accused`
  line `had an opportunity of cross-examining the witness and that the deposition if made in a criminal proceeding`
  line `was made in the presence of the person accused shall, unless the contrary is proved, be sufficient evidence`
  line `that he had that opportunity and that it was so made.`
  line
  line `(5) No half-monthly payment shall be payable in respect of the period during which the owner of the`
  line `ship is, under any law for the time being in force relating to merchant shipping, liable to defray the expenses`
  line `of maintenance of the injured master or seaman.`
  line
  line `(6) Failure to give a notice or make a claim or commence proceedings within the time required by this`
  line `section shall not be a bar to the maintenance of proceedings under this Chapter in respect of any personal`
  line `injury, if such proceedings under this Chapter are commenced within one month from the date on which`
  line `the certificate of the State to that effect Government was furnished to the person commencing the`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (54108)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Medical examination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54108&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an employee has given notice of an accident, he, shall, if the`
  line `employer, before the expiry of three days from the time at which service of the notice has been effected,`
  line `offers to have him examined free of charge by a medical practitioner, submit himself for such examination,`
  line `and any employee who is in receipt of a half-monthly payment under this Chapter shall, if so required,`
  line `submit himself for such examination from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that an employee shall not be required to submit himself for examination by a medical`
  line `practitioner at more than such frequent interval as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) If an employee, on being required to do so by the employer under sub-section (1) or by the`
  line `competent authority at any time, refuses to submit himself for examination by a medical practitioner or in`
  line `any way obstructs the same, his right to compensation shall be suspended during the continuance of such`
  line `refusal or obstruction unless in the case of refusal, he was prevented by any sufficient cause from so`
  line `submitting himself.`
  line
  line `(3) If an employee, before the expiry of the period within which he is liable under sub-section (1) to be`
  line `required to submit himself for medical examination, voluntarily leaves the vicinity of the place in which he`
  line `was employed without having been so examined, his right to compensation shall be suspended until he`
  line `returns and offers himself for such examination:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such employee proves before the medical practitioner that he could not so submit`
  line `himself for medical examination due to the circumstances beyond his control and he was also handicapped`
  line `to communicate such information in writing, the medical practitioner may after recording such reasons in`
  line `writing, condone the delay and his right to compensation shall be revived as if no such suspension was`
  line made.
  line
  line `(4) Where an employee, whose right to compensation has been suspended under sub-section (2) or subsection (3), dies without having submitted himself for medical examination as required by either of those`
  line `sub-sections, the competent authority may, if he thinks fit, direct the payment of compensation to the`
  line `dependants of the deceased employee.`
  line
  line `(5) Where under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), a right to compensation is suspended, no`
  line `compensation shall be payable in respect of the period of suspension, and, if the period of suspension`
  line `commences before the expiry of the waiting period referred to in clause (ii) of sub-section (4) of section`
  line `76, the waiting period shall be increased by the period during which the suspension continues.`
  line
  line `(6) Where an injured employee has refused to be attended by a medical practitioner whose services`
  line `have been offered to him by the employer free of charge or having accepted such offer has deliberately`
  line `disregarded the instructions of such medical practitioner, then, if it is proved that the employee has not`
  line `thereafter been regularly attended by a medical practitioner or having been so attended has deliberately`
  line `failed to follow his instructions and that such refusal, disregard or failure was unreasonable in the`
  line `circumstances of the case and that the injury has been aggravated thereby, the injury and resulting`
  line `disablement shall be deemed to be of the same nature and duration as they might reasonably have been`
  line `expected to be if the employee had been regularly attended by a medical practitioner, whose instructions he`
  line `had followed, and compensation, if any, shall be payable accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (54109)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title Contracting.
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54109&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any employer in the course of or for the purposes of his trade or business`
  line `contracts with a contractor for the execution by or under the contractor of the whole or any part of any work`
  line `which is ordinarily part of the trade or business of the employer, the employer shall be liable to pay to any`
  line `employee employed in the execution of the work any compensation, which he would have been liable to`
  line `pay if that employee had been immediately employed by him; and that the amount of compensation shall`
  line `be calculated with reference to the wages of the employee under the employer by whom he is immediately`
  line employed.
  line
  line `(2) Where the employer is liable to pay compensation under this section, he shall be entitled to be`
  line `indemnified by the contractor, or any other person from whom the employee could have recovered the`
  line `compensation and where a contractor who is himself an employer is liable to pay compensation or to`
  line `indemnify an employer under this section, he shall be entitled to be indemnified by any person standing to`
  line `him in relation of a contractor from whom the employee could have recovered the compensation, and all`
  line `questions as to the right to and the amount of any such indemnity shall, in default of agreement, be settled`
  line `by the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall be construed as preventing an employee from recovering compensation`
  line `referred to in sub-section (2) from the contractor instead of the employer.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of this section shall not apply in any case where the accident occurred elsewhere`
  line `than on, in or about the premises on which the employer has undertaken or usually undertakes, as the case`
  line `may be, to execute the work or which are otherwise under his control or management.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (54110)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Remedies of employer against stranger.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54110&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `Where an employee has recovered compensation in`
  line `respect of any injury caused under circumstances creating a legal liability of some person other than the`
  line `person by whom the compensation was paid to pay damages in respect thereof, the person by whom the`
  line `compensation was paid and any person who has been called on to pay an indemnity under section 85 shall`
  line `be entitled to be indemnified by the person so liable to pay damages as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (54111)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Insolvency of employer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54111&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any employer has entered into a contract with any insurers`
  line `in respect of any liability under this Chapter to any employee, then, in the event of the employer becoming`
  line `insolvent or making a composition or scheme of arrangement with his creditors or, if the employer is a`
  line `company, in the event of the company having commenced to be wound up, the rights of the employer`
  line `against the insurers as respects that liability shall, notwithstanding anything in any law for the time being`
  line `in force relating to insolvency or the winding up of companies, be transferred to and vest in the employee,`
  line `and upon any such transfer the insurers shall have the same rights and remedies and be subject to the same`
  line `liabilities as if they were the employer, so, however, that the insurers shall not be under any greater liability`
  line `to the employee than they would have been under the employer.`
  line
  line `(2) If the liability of the insurers to the employee is less than the liability of the employer to the`
  line `employee, the burden of proof shall lie on the employee for the balance in the insolvency proceedings or`
  line liquidation.
  line
  line `(3) Where in any case such as is referred to in sub-section (1), the contract of the employer with the`
  line `insurers is void or voidable by reason of non-compliance on the part of the employer with any terms or`
  line `conditions of the contract (other than a stipulation for the payment of premium), the provisions of that subsection shall apply as if the contract were not void or voidable, and the insurers shall be entitled to prove in`
  line `the insolvency proceedings or liquidation for the amount paid to the employee:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply in any case in which the employee fails`
  line `to give notice to the insurers of the happening of the accident and of any resulting disablement as soon as`
  line `practicable after he becomes aware of the institution of the insolvency or liquidation proceedings.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall be deemed to be included among the debts which under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy`
  line `Code, 2016 (31 of 2016) or under the provisions of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) are in the`
  line `distribution of the assets of an insolvent or in the distribution of the assets of a company being wound up`
  line `to be paid in priority to all other debts, the amount due in respect of any compensation, the liability accrued`
  line `before the date of the order of adjudication of the insolvent or the date of the commencement of the winding`
  line `up, as the case may be, and the provisions of that Code and Act shall have effect accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the compensation is a half-monthly payment, the amount due in respect thereof shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this section, be taken to be the amount of the lump sum for which the half-monthly payment`
  line `could, if redeemable, be redeemed if applications were made for that purpose under section 80, and a`
  line `certificate of the competent authority as to the amount of such sum shall be conclusive proof thereof.`
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of sub-section (4) shall apply in the case of any amount for which an insurer is`
  line `entitled to prove under sub-section (3), but otherwise those provisions shall not apply where the insolvent`
  line `or the company being wound up has entered into such a contract with insurers as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(7) The provisions of this section shall not apply where a company is wound up voluntarily merely for`
  line `the purposes of reconstruction or of amalgamation with another company.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (54112)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Power to require from employers statements regarding fatal accidents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54112&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a`
  line `competent authority receives information from any source that an employee has died as a result of an`
  line `accident arising out of and in the course of his employment, he may send by registered post or where`
  line `possible, electronically a notice to the employee's employer requiring him to submit, within thirty days of`
  line `the service of the notice, a statement, in such form as may be prescribed by the State Government, giving`
  line `the circumstances attending the death of the employee, and indicating whether, in the opinion of the`
  line `employer, he is or is not liable to deposit compensation on account of the death and a copy of such notice`
  line `shall also be sent by the competent authority in the same manner to the dependants of such employee`
  line `ascertained by the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) If the employer is of the opinion that he is liable to deposit compensation, he shall make the deposit`
  line `within thirty days of the service of the notice.`
  line
  line `(3) If the employer is of the opinion that he is not liable to deposit compensation, he shall in his`
  line `statement indicate the grounds on which he disclaims liability.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the employer has so disclaimed liability, the competent authority, after such inquiry as he`
  line `may think fit, may inform any of the dependants of the deceased employee, that it is open to the dependants`
  line `to prefer a claim for compensation, and may give them such other further information as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Where in the opinion of the competent authority, a dependant of the deceased employee is not in a`
  line `position to engage an advocate to file a claim for compensation, the competent authority may provide an`
  line `advocate to such dependant, from the panel of advocates maintained by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (54113)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Registration of agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54113&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the amount of any lump sum payable as compensation`
  line `has been settled by agreement, whether by way of redemption of a half-monthly payment or otherwise, or`
  line `where any compensation has been so settled as being payable to a woman, or a person under a legal`
  line `disability, a memorandum thereof shall be sent by the employer to the competent authority, who shall, on`
  line `being satisfied as to its genuineness, record the memorandum in a register, electronically or otherwise, in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that-`
  line
  line `(a) no such memorandum shall be recorded before seven days after communication by the competent`
  line `authority of notice to the parties concerned;`
  line
  line `(b) the competent authority may at any time rectify the register;`
  line
  line `(c) where it appears to the competent authority that an agreement as to the payment of a lump sum`
  line `whether by way of redemption of a half-monthly payment or otherwise, or an agreement as to the`
  line `amount of compensation payable, to a woman or a person under a legal disability ought not to be`
  line `registered by reason of the inadequacy of the sum or amount, or by reason of the agreement having`
  line `been obtained by fraud or undue influence or other improper means, the competent authority may refuse`
  line `to record the memorandum of the agreement and may make such order including an order as to any`
  line `sum already paid under the agreement, as the competent authority thinks just in the circumstances.`
  line
  line `(2) An agreement for the payment of compensation which has been registered under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be enforceable under this Code notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Contract Act, 1872`
  line `(9 of 1872), or in any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a memorandum of any agreement, the registration of which is required under this section, is`
  line `not sent to the competent authority as required by this section, the employer shall be liable to pay the full`
  line `amount of compensation which he is liable to pay under the provisions of this Chapter, and notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 76, shall not, unless the competent authority`
  line `otherwise directs, be entitled to deduct more than half of any amount paid to the employee by way of`
  line `compensation whether under the agreement or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (54114)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Reference to competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54114&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any question arises in any proceedings under this`
  line `Chapter as to the liability of any person to pay compensation (including any question as to whether a person`
  line `injured is or is not an employee) or as to the amount or duration of compensation (including any question`
  line `as to the nature or extent of disablement), the question shall, in default of agreement, be settled by a`
  line `competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) No Civil Court shall have jurisdiction to settle, decide or deal with any question which is by or`
  line `under this Chapter required to be settled, decided or dealt with by a competent authority or to enforce any`
  line `liability incurred under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (54115)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Appointment of competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54115&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification, appoint`
  line `any person who is or has been a member of a State Judicial Service for a period of not less than five years`
  line `or is or has been for not less than five years an advocate or is or has been a Gazetted Officer for not less`
  line `than five years having educational qualifications and experience in personnel management, human resource`
  line `development, industrial relations and legal affairs or such other experience and qualifications as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government to be a competent authority for the purposes of this Chapter and`
  line `for such area as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where more than one competent authority has been appointed for any area, the State Government`
  line `may, by general or special order, regulate the distribution of business amongst them.`
  line
  line `(3) Any competent authority may, for the purpose of deciding any matter referred to him for decision`
  line `under this Chapter, choose one or more persons possessing special knowledge of any matter relevant to the`
  line `matter under inquiry to assist him in holding the inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (54116)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Venue of proceedings and transfer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54116&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any matter under this Chapter is to be done by`
  line `or before a competent authority, the same shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter and in the manner`
  line `prescribed in this behalf by the State Government, be done by or before the competent authority for the area`
  line `in which—`
  line
  line `(a) the accident took place which resulted in the injury; or`
  line
  line `(b) the employee or in case of his death, the dependant claiming the compensation ordinarily resides;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) the employer has his registered office:`
  line
  line `Provided that no matter shall be processed before or by a competent authority, other than the competent`
  line `authority having jurisdiction over the area in which the accident took place, without his giving notice`
  line `electronically or otherwise in the manner prescribed by the Central Government to the competent authority`
  line `having jurisdiction over the area and the State Government concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, where the employee, being the master of a ship or a seaman or the captain or a`
  line `member of the crew of an aircraft or an employee in a motor vehicle or a company, meets with the accident`
  line `outside India, any such matter may be done by or before a competent authority for the area in which the`
  line `owner or agent of the ship, aircraft or motor vehicle resides or carries on business or the registered office`
  line `of the company is situate, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If a competent authority, other than the competent authority with whom any money has been`
  line `deposited under section 81, proceeds with a matter under this Chapter, the former may for the proper`
  line `disposal of the matter call for transfer of any records or moneys remaining with the latter and on receipt of`
  line `such a request, he shall comply with the same.`
  line
  line `(3) If a competent authority is satisfied that any matter arising out of any proceedings pending before`
  line `him can be more conveniently dealt with by any other competent authority, whether in the same State or`
  line `not, he may, subject to rules made under this Code relating to this Chapter, order such matter to be`
  line `transferred to such other competent authority either for report or for disposal, and, if he does so, shall`
  line `forthwith transmit to such other competent authority all documents relevant for the decision of such matter`
  line `and, where the matter is transferred for disposal, shall also transmit in the manner as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Central Government any money remaining in his hands or invested by him for the benefit of any party`
  line `to the proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority shall not, where any party to the proceedings has appeared before`
  line `him, make any order of transfer relating to the distribution among dependants of a lump sum without giving`
  line `such party an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) The competent authority to whom any matter is so transferred shall, subject to rules made under this`
  line `Code relating to this Chapter, inquire therein to and, if the matter was transferred for report, return his report`
  line `thereon or, if the matter was transferred for disposal, continue the proceedings as if they had originally`
  line `commenced before him.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of a report from a competent authority to whom any matter has been transferred for report`
  line `under sub-section (3), the competent authority by whom it was referred shall decide the matter referred to`
  line `in conformity with such report.`
  line
  line `(6) The State Government may transfer any matter from any competent authority appointed by it to any`
  line `other competent authority appointed by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (54117)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Form of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54117&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an accident occurs in respect of which liability to pay`
  line `compensation under this Chapter arises, a claim for such compensation may, subject to the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter, be made before the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), no application for the settlement of any matter by`
  line `competent authority, other than an application by a dependant or joint application by dependants for`
  line `compensation, shall be made unless and until some question has arisen between the parties in connection`
  line `therewith which they have been unable to settle by agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) An application to a competent authority for claim under sub-section (1) or settlement under`
  line `sub-section (2) may be made electronically or otherwise in such form and in such manner accompanied by`
  line `such fee, if any, as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The time-limit for the disposal of applications under this section and the costs incidental to the`
  line `proceedings under this section to be imposed by the competent authority shall be such as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (54118)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Power of competent authority to require further deposit in cases of fatal accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54118&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where`
  line `any sum has been deposited by an employer as compensation payable in respect of an employee whose`
  line `injury has resulted in death, and in the opinion of the competent authority such sum is insufficient, the`
  line `competent authority may, by notice in writing stating his reasons, call upon the employer to show cause`
  line `why he should not make a further deposit within such time as may be stated in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If the employer fails to show cause to the satisfaction of the competent authority, the competent`
  line `authority may make an award determining the total amount payable, and requiring the employer to deposit`
  line `the deficiency.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (54119)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Powers and procedure of competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54119&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority shall have all the`
  line `powers of a Civil Court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the purpose of taking`
  line `evidence on oath (which such competent authority is hereby empowered to impose) and of enforcing the`
  line `attendance of witnesses and compelling the production of documents and material objects, and the`
  line `competent authority shall be deemed to be a Civil Court for all the purposes of section 195 and of Chapter`
  line `XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (54120)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Appearance of parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54120&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `Any appearance, application or act required to be made or done by any`
  line `person before or to a competent authority (other than an appearance of a party which is required for the`
  line `purpose of his examination as a witness) may be made or done on behalf of such person by a legal`
  line `practitioner or by an official of an Insurance Company or a registered Trade Union or by an Inspector-cumFacilitator appointed under sub-section (1) of section 122 or by any other officer specified by the State`
  line `Government in this behalf, authorised in writing by such person, or, with the permission of the competent`
  line `authority, by any other person so authorised.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (54121)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Method of recording evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54121&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority shall make a brief memorandum of the`
  line `substance of the evidence of every witness as the examination of the witness proceeds, and such`
  line `memorandum shall be authenticated under the hand of the competent authority or in the manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government and shall form part of the record:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the competent authority is prevented from making such memorandum, he shall record`
  line `the reason of his inability to do so and shall cause such memorandum to be made in writing from his`
  line `dictation and shall sign the same, and such memorandum shall form part of the record:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the evidence of any medical witness shall be taken down as nearly as may be word`
  line `for word.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (54122)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to submit cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54122&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `A competent authority may, if he thinks fit, submit any question of law`
  line `for the decision of the High Court and, if he does so, shall decide the question in conformity with such`
  line decision.
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (54123)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Appeal against order of competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54123&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal shall lie to the High Court from`
  line `the following orders of a competent authority under this Chapter, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) an order awarding as compensation a lump sum whether by way of redemption of a half-monthly`
  line `payment or otherwise or disallowing a claim in full or in part for a lump sum;`
  line
  line `(b) an order awarding interest or damages under section 77;`
  line
  line `(c) an order refusing to allow redemption of a half-monthly payment;`
  line
  line `(d) an order providing for the distribution of compensation among the dependants of a deceased`
  line `employee, or disallowing any claim of a person alleging himself to be such dependant;`
  line
  line `(e) an order allowing or disallowing any claim for the amount of an indemnity under the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (2) of section 85; or`
  line
  line `(f) an order refusing to register a memorandum of agreement or registering the same or providing for`
  line `the registration of the same subject to conditions:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal shall lie against any order unless a substantial question of law is involved in`
  line `the appeal, and in the case of an order other than an order referred to in clause (c), unless the amount in`
  line `dispute in the appeal is not less than ten thousand rupees or such higher amount as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal shall lie in any case in which the parties have agreed to abide by the`
  line `decision of the competent authority, or in which the order of the competent authority gives effect to an`
  line `agreement arrived at by the parties:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no appeal by an employer under clause (a) shall lie unless the memorandum of appeal`
  line `is accompanied by a certificate by the competent authority to the effect that the appellant has deposited with`
  line `him the amount payable under the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(2) The period of limitation for an appeal under this section shall be sixty days from the date of passing`
  line `of the order.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 5 of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), shall be applicable to appeal`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (54124)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Levy and collection of cess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54124&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be levied and collected a cess for the purposes of`
  line `social security and welfare of building workers at such rate not exceeding two per cent. but not less than`
  line `one per cent. of the cost of construction incurred by an employer, as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, from time to time, specify.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, the cost of construction shall not include,---`
  line
  line `(a) the cost of land; and`
  line
  line `(b) any compensation paid or payable to an employee or his kin under Chapter VII.`
  line
  line `(2) The cess levied under sub-section (1) shall be collected from every employer undertaking building`
  line `or other construction work in such manner and at such time, including deduction at source in relation to a`
  line `building or other construction work of a Government or of a public sector undertaking or advance collection`
  line `through a local authority where an approval of such building or other construction work by such local`
  line `authority or such other authority notified by the State Government is required, as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The proceeds of the cess collected under sub-section (2) shall be deposited by the local authority or`
  line `such other authority notified by the State Government to the Building Workers' Welfare Board in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the cess leviable under`
  line `this Chapter including payment of such cess in advance may, subject to final assessment to be made, be collected at a uniform rate or rates as may be prescribed by the Central Government on the basis of the`
  line `quantum of the building or other construction work involved.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (54125)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Interest payable on delay in payment of cess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54125&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `If any employer fails to pay any amount of cess`
  line `payable under section 100 within such time as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government, such`
  line `employer shall be liable to pay interest at such rate as may be prescribed by the Central Government, on`
  line `the amount of cess, to be paid, for the period from the date on which such payment is due till such amount`
  line `is actually paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (54126)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Power to exempt from cess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54126&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, the`
  line `appropriate Government may, by notification, exempt any employer or class of employers in a State from`
  line `the payment of cess payable under this Chapter where such cess is already levied and payable under any`
  line `corresponding law in force in that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (54127)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Self-assessment of cess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54127&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) The employer shall, within sixty days or such period as may be`
  line `notified by the Central Government of the completion of his each building and other construction work,`
  line `pay such cess (adjusting the advance cess already paid under section 100) payable under this Chapter on`
  line `the basis of his self-assessment on the cost of construction worked out on the basis of the documents and`
  line `in the manner prescribed by the Central Government and after such payment of cess, he shall file a return`
  line `under clause (d) of section 123.`
  line
  line `(2) If the officer or the authority to whom or to which the return has been filed under sub-section (1)`
  line `finds any discrepancy in the payment under the self-assessment and the payment required under the return`
  line `referred to in that sub-section, then, he or it shall, after making or causing to be made such inquiry as he or`
  line `it thinks fit and after such inquiry make the appropriate assessment order.`
  line
  line `(3) An order of assessment made under sub-section (2) shall specify the date within which the cess shall`
  line `be paid by the employer, if any.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (54128)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Penalty for non-payment of cess within the specified time.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54128&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `If any amount of cess payable by`
  line `any employer under section 103 is not paid within the date specified in the order of assessment made under`
  line `sub-section (2) of that section, it shall be deemed to be in arrears and the authority prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in this behalf may, after making such inquiry as it deems fit, impose on such employer a`
  line `penalty not exceeding the amount of cess:`
  line
  line `Provided that, before imposing any such penalty, such employer shall be given a reasonable opportunity`
  line `of being heard and if after such hearing the said authority is satisfied that the default was for any good and`
  line `sufficient reason, no penalty shall be imposed under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (54129)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Appeal to appellate authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54129&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any employer aggrieved by an order of assessment made`
  line `under section 103 or by an order imposing penalty made under section 104 may, within such time as may`
  line `be prescribed by the Central Government, appeal to such appellate authority in such form and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal preferred under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by such fees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) After the receipt of any appeal under sub-section (1), the appellate authority shall, after giving the`
  line `appellant an opportunity of being heard in the matter, dispose of the appeal as expeditiously as possible.`
  line
  line `(4) Every order passed in appeal under this section shall be final and shall not be called in question in`
  line `any court of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (54130)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Registration of building workers as beneficiaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54130&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `Every building worker who has completed`
  line `eighteen years of age, but has not completed sixty years of age, and who has been engaged in any building`
  line `or other construction work for not less than ninety days during the preceding twelve months shall be`
  line `registered by the officer authorised by the Building Workers' Welfare Board as a beneficiary under this`
  line `Chapter in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (54131)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Cessation as a beneficiary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54131&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) A building worker who has been registered as a beneficiary`
  line `under section 106 shall cease to be as such when he attains the age of sixty years or when he is not engaged`
  line `in building or other construction work for not less than ninety days in a year:`
  line
  line `Provided that in computing the period of ninety days under this sub-section, there shall be excluded`
  line `any period of absence from the building or other construction work due to any personal injury caused to the`
  line `building worker by accident arising out of and in the course of his employment.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if a person had been a beneficiary for at`
  line `least three years continuously immediately before attaining the age of sixty years, then, he shall be eligible`
  line `to get such benefits as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For computing the period of three years under this sub-section as a beneficiary registered`
  line `with a Building Workers' Welfare Board, there shall be added any period for which a person had been a`
  line `beneficiary registered with any other such Board immediately before his registration with the Building`
  line `Workers' Welfare Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (54132)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Building and other construction worker’s welfare Fund and its applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54132&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) There`
  line `shall be constituted by a Building Workers' Welfare Board a fund to be called the Building and Other`
  line `Construction Workers' Welfare Fund and there shall be credited thereto—`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of any cess levied under sub-section (1) of section 100;`
  line
  line `(b) any grants and loans made to the Building Workers' Welfare Board by the Central Government;`
  line and
  line
  line `(c) all sums received by the Building Workers' Welfare Board from such other sources as may be`
  line `decided by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Building and Other Construction Workers' Welfare Fund shall be applied for meeting—`
  line
  line `(a) expenses of the Building Workers' Welfare Board in the discharge of its functions under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) salaries, allowances and other remuneration of the members, officers and other employees of the`
  line `Building Workers' Welfare Board; and`
  line
  line `(c) expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Code.`
  line
  line `(3) No Building Workers' Welfare Board shall, in any financial year, incur expenses towards salaries,`
  line `allowances and other remuneration to its members, officers and other employees and for meeting the other`
  line `administrative expenses exceeding five per cent. of its total expenses during that financial year.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (54133)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Framing of schemes for unorganised workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54133&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall frame and`
  line `notify, from time to time, suitable welfare schemes for unorganised workers on matters relating to---`
  line
  line `(i) life and disability cover;`
  line
  line `(ii) health and maternity benefits;`
  line
  line `(iii) old age protection;`
  line
  line `(iv) education; and`
  line
  line `(v) any other benefit as may be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall frame and notify, from time to time, suitable welfare schemes for`
  line `unorganised workers, including schemes relating to---`
  line
  line `(i) provident fund;`
  line
  line `(ii) employment injury benefit;`
  line
  line `(iii) housing;`
  line
  line `(iv) educational schemes for children;`
  line
  line `(v) skill upgradation of workers;`
  line
  line `(vi) funeral assistance; and`
  line
  line `(vii) old age homes.`
  line
  line `(3) Any scheme notified by the Central Government under sub-section (1), may be---`
  line
  line `(i) wholly funded by the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(ii) partly funded by the Central Government and partly funded by the State Government; or`
  line
  line `(iii) partly funded by the Central Government, partly funded by the State Government and partly`
  line `funded through contributions collected from the beneficiaries of the scheme or the employers as may`
  line `be specified in the scheme by the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(iv) funded from any source including corporate social responsibility fund within the meaning of the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013) or any other such source as may be specified in the scheme.`
  line
  line `(4) Every scheme notified by the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall provide for such`
  line `matters that are necessary for the efficient implementation of the scheme including the matters relating to`
  line `all or any of the following, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) scope of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(ii) authority to implement the scheme;`
  line
  line `(iii) beneficiaries of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(iv) resources of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(v) agency or agencies that will implement the scheme;`
  line
  line `(vi) redressal of grievances; and`
  line
  line `(vii) any other relevant matter,`
  line
  line `and a special purpose vehicle may also be constituted by the Central Government for the purpose of`
  line `implementation of any such scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (54134)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Funding of state government schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54134&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any scheme notified by the State Government`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 109 may be—`
  line
  line `(a) wholly funded by the State Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) partly funded by the State Government, partly funded through contributions collected from the`
  line `beneficiaries of the scheme or the employers as may be specified in the scheme by the State`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(c) funded from any source including corporate social responsibility fund referred to in clause (iv) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 109 or any other such source as may be specified in the scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may seek financial assistance from the Central Government for the schemes`
  line `framed by it.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may provide such financial assistance to the State Governments for the`
  line `purpose of schemes for such period and on such terms and conditions as it may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (54135)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Record keeping.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54135&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `The Government formulating and notifying the scheme under this Chapter`
  line `shall provide therein the form and manner of keeping the records electronically or otherwise relating to the`
  line `scheme and the authority by whom such records shall be maintained:`
  line
  line `Provided that such records shall, as far as may be possible, bear continuous number for the purpose of`
  line `proper management of the scheme and for avoiding any duplication and overlapping in records.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (54435)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Helpline, facilitation centre, etc., for unorganised workers, gig workers and platform workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54435&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may set up a toll free call centre or helpline or such facilitation centres as may be considered necessary from time to time to perform any or more of the following functions,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) to disseminate information on available social security schemes for the unorganised workers, gig`
  line `workers and platform workers;`
  line
  line `(b) to facilitate filing, processing and forwarding of application forms for registration of unorganised`
  line `workers, gig workers and platform workers;`
  line
  line `(c) to assist unorganised workers, gig workers and platform workers to obtain registration; and`
  line
  line `(d) to facilitate the enrolment of the registered unorganised workers, gig workers and platform`
  line `workers in the social security schemes.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (54137)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Registration of unorganised workers, gig workers and platform workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54137&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `unorganised worker, gig worker or platform worker shall be required to be registered for the purposes of`
  line `this Chapter, subject to the fulfilment of the following conditions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) he has completed sixteen years of age or such age as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) he has submitted a self-declaration electronically or otherwise in such form and in such manner`
  line `containing such information as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every eligible unorganised worker, gig worker or platform worker referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `shall make an application for registration in such form along with such documents including Aadhaar`
  line `number as may be prescribed by the Central Government and such worker shall be assigned a`
  line `distinguishable number to his application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the system of electronic registration maintained by the appropriate Government shall also`
  line `provide for self registration by any such worker in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) A registered unorganised worker, gig worker or platform worker shall be eligible to avail the benefit`
  line `of the concerned scheme framed under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government, or as the case may be, the State Government shall make such contribution`
  line `in a scheme as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, the term Aadhaar shall have the same meaning as is`
  line `assigned to it in section 142.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (54138)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Schemes for gig workers and platform workers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54138&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may frame and`
  line `notify, from time to time, suitable social security schemes for gig workers and platform workers on matters`
  line `relating to---`
  line
  line `(a) life and disability cover;`
  line
  line `(b) accident insurance;`
  line
  line `(c) health and maternity benefits;`
  line
  line `(d) old age protection;`
  line
  line `(e) creche; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other benefit as may be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every scheme framed and notified under sub-section (1) may provide for---`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of administration of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(b) the agency or agencies for implementing the scheme;`
  line
  line `(c) the role of aggregators in the scheme;`
  line
  line `(d) the sources of funding of the scheme; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter as the Central Government may consider necessary for the efficient`
  line `administration of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(3) Any scheme notified by the Central Government under sub-section (1), may be---`
  line
  line `(a) wholly funded by the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) partly funded by the Central Government and partly funded by the State Government; or`
  line
  line `(c) wholly funded by the contributions of the aggregators; or`
  line
  line `(d) partly funded by the Central Government, partly funded by the State Government and partly`
  line `funded through contributions collected from the beneficiaries of the scheme or the aggregators, as may`
  line `be specified in the scheme framed by the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) funded from corporate social responsibility fund within the meaning of Companies Act, 2013 (18`
  line `of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(f) any other source.`
  line
  line `(4) The contribution to be paid by the aggregators for the funding referred to in clause (ii) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 141, shall be at such rate not exceeding two per cent., but not less than one per`
  line `cent., as may be notified by the Central Government, of the annual turnover of every such aggregator who`
  line `falls within a category of aggregators, as are specified in the Seventh Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that the contribution by an aggregator shall not exceed five per cent. of the amount paid or`
  line `payable by an aggregator to gig workers and platform workers.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the annual turnover of an aggregator shall not`
  line `include any tax, levy and cess paid or payable to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The date of commencement of contribution from aggregator under this section shall be notified by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The National Social Security Board constituted under sub-section (1) of section 6 shall be the Board`
  line `for the purposes of the welfare of gig workers and platform workers under the provisions of this Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that while such Board serves the purposes of welfare of, or matters relating to, gig workers`
  line `and platform workers, the following members shall constitute the Board instead of the members specified`
  line `in clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (2) of section 6, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) five representatives of the aggregators as the Central Government may nominate;`
  line
  line `(b) five representatives of the gig workers and platform workers as the Central Government may`
  line nominate;
  line
  line `(c) Director General of the Corporation;`
  line
  line `(d) Central Provident Fund Commissioner of the Central Board;`
  line
  line `(e) such expert members as the Central Government may consider appropriate;`
  line
  line `(f) five representatives of the State Governments by such rotation as the Central Government may`
  line `consider appropriate;`
  line
  line `(g) Joint Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of Labour and Employment, who shall`
  line `be the Member Secretary to the Board.`
  line
  line `(7) (i) The Central Government may provide that---`
  line
  line `(a) the authority to collect and to expend the proceeds of contribution collected;`
  line
  line `(b) the rate of interest to be paid by an aggregator in case of delayed payment, less payment or nonpayment of contribution;`
  line
  line `(c) self-assessment of contribution by aggregators;`
  line
  line `(d) conditions for cessation of a gig worker or a platform worker; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter relating to smooth functioning of the social security scheme notified under this`
  line `section, shall be such as may be prescribed by that Government.`
  line
  line `(ii) The Central Government may by notification, exempt such aggregator or class of aggregators from`
  line `paying of contribution under sub-section (4), subject to such conditions as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, an aggregator having more than one business shall be`
  line `treated as a separate business entity or aggregator.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (54139)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title Accounts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54139&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `Each of the Social Security Organisations shall maintain proper accounts of its`
  line `income and expenditure in such form and in such manner as the appropriate Government may, after`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (54140)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54140&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `The accounts of each of the Social Security Organisations shall be audited annually`
  line `by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with`
  line `such audit shall be payable by the respective Social Security Organisation to the Comptroller and AuditorGeneral of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection with`
  line `the audit of the accounts of a Social Security Organisation shall have the same rights and privileges and`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India has, in connection`
  line `with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers, documents and papers and to inspect any of the offices of the Social`
  line `Security Organisation.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of a Social Security Organisation as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `of India or any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded to the Social Security Organisation which shall along with its comments on the audit report of`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India forward the same to the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (54141)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Budget estimates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54141&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each of the Social Security Organisations shall in each year frame a`
  line `budget showing the probable receipts and the expenditure which it proposes to incur during the following`
  line `year and shall submit a copy of the budget for the approval of the appropriate Government before such date`
  line `as may be fixed by it in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The budget shall contain provisions adequate in the opinion of the appropriate Government for the`
  line `discharge of the liabilities incurred by the Social Security Organisation and for the maintenance of a`
  line `working balance.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (54142)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54142&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each of the Social Security Organisations shall submit to the appropriate`
  line `Government an annual report of its work and activities and the budget finally adopted by the Social Security`
  line Organisation.
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government shall cause a copy of the annual report, budget and the audited`
  line `accounts together with the report of the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and the comments of`
  line `the respective Social Security Organisation thereon to be laid before each House of Parliament or the State`
  line `legislature, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (54143)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Valuation of assets and liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54143&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `Each of the fund maintained by a Social Security`
  line `Organisation or by an establishment under this Code shall have a valuation of its assets and liabilities made`
  line `by a valuer or actuary, as the case may be, appointed, with the prior approval of the appropriate Government,`
  line `by such Social Security Organisation or the establishment, as the case may be, in the following manner,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) in case of Central Board, annually;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of Corporation, once in every three years;`
  line
  line `(c) in case of any other Social Security Organisation or establishment, as specified by the appropriate`
  line `Government, by order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appropriate Government, if it considers necessary, may direct such valuation to be`
  line `made at such intervals other than provided in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (54144)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Holding of property, etc., by social security organisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54144&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Social Security Organisation`
  line `(except Corporation) may, subject to such conditions as may by Social Security Organisation be prescribed`
  line `by the appropriate Government, acquire and hold property, both movable and immovable, sell or otherwise`
  line `transfer any movable or immovable property which may have become vested in or have been acquired by`
  line `it and do all things necessary for such purposes and for the purposes for which the said Social Security`
  line `Organisation is established.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government, a Social Security`
  line `Organisation may, from time to time invest any moneys vested in it, which are not immediately required`
  line `for expenses properly defrayable and may, subject to as aforesaid, from time to time re-invest or realise`
  line `such investments:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of Provident Fund, Pension Fund or Insurance Fund, such investment, reinvestment or realisation shall be specified in the Provident Fund Scheme or Pension Scheme or Insurance`
  line `Scheme, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Each of the Social Security Organisations (except Corporation) may, with the previous sanction of`
  line `the appropriate Government and on such terms as may be prescribed by such Government, raise loans and`
  line `take measures for discharging such loans.`
  line
  line `(4) Each of the Social Security Organisations (except Corporation) may, with the previous sanction of`
  line `the appropriate Government and on such terms as may be prescribed by such Government, constitute for`
  line `the benefit of its officers and staff or any class of them, such provident or other benefit funds as it may think`
  line `fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of officers and staff of the Central Board, such terms shall be specified in the`
  line `Provident Fund Scheme.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (54145)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Writing off of losses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54145&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the conditions as may be prescribed by the appropriate`
  line `Government, where any of the Social Security Organisations is of the opinion that the amount of`
  line `contribution, cess, interest and damages due to it, under this Code, is irrecoverable, the concerned Social`
  line `Security Organisation may sanction the writing off of the said amount in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of Provident Fund, Pension Fund or Insurance Fund, such writing off shall be`
  line `specified in the Provident Fund Scheme or Pension Scheme or Insurance Scheme, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (54146)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Appointment of Inspector-cum-Facilitators and their powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54146&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `for the purposes of Chapter III and Chapter IV and for the provisions in this Code relating to those Chapters,`
  line `and the appropriate Government for the purposes of other provisions of this Code, may, by notification,`
  line `appoint Inspectorcum-Facilitators who shall discharge his duties under this Code and exercise the powers`
  line `conferred on them under sub-section (6) in accordance with the inspection scheme referred to in sub-section`
  line `(2).`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government for the purposes of Chapter III and Chapter IV and for the provisions in`
  line `this Code relating to those Chapters and the appropriate Government in respect of other provisions of this`
  line `Code, may, by notification, lay down an inspection scheme which may provide for generation of a webbased inspection and calling of information relating to the inspection under this Code electronically and`
  line `such scheme shall, inter alia, have provisions to cater to special circumstances for assigning inspections`
  line `and calling for information from the establishment or any other person.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), the Central Government for the purposes of`
  line `Chapter III and Chapter IV and the other provisions in this Code relating to those Chapters and the`
  line `appropriate Government in relation to other provisions of this Code, may, by notification, confer such`
  line `jurisdiction of randomised selection of inspection for the purposes of this Code, to the Inspector-cumFacilitators as may be specified in such notification.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the powers of the Central Government or the appropriate Government, as the`
  line `case may be, under this section, the inspection scheme may be designed taking into account, inter alia, the`
  line `following factors, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) assignment of unique number to each establishment (which will be same as the registration`
  line `number allotted to that establishment), each Inspector-cum-Facilitator and each inspection in such`
  line `manner as may be notified for the purposes of Chapter III and Chapter IV and the other provisions of`
  line `this Code relating to those Chapters, by the Central Government, and in respect of other provisions of`
  line `this Code, by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(b) timely uploading of inspection reports in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `notified, for the purposes of Chapter III and Chapter IV and the other provisions of this Code relating`
  line `to those Chapters, by the Central Government, and in respect of other provisions of this Code, by the`
  line `appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(c) provisions for special inspections based on such parameters as may be notified, for the purposes`
  line `of Chapter III and Chapter IV and the other provisions of this Code relating to those Chapters, by the`
  line `Central Government, and in respect of other provisions of this Code, by the appropriate Government;`
  line and
  line
  line `(d) the characteristics of employment relationships, the nature of work and characteristics of the`
  line `workplaces based on such parameters as may be notified, for the purposes of Chapter III and Chapter`
  line `IV and the other provisions of this Code relating to those Chapters, by the Central Government, and in`
  line `respect of other provisions of this Code, by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Inspector-cum-Facilitator may—`
  line
  line `(a) advice the employers and employees relating to compliance with the provisions of this Code; and`
  line
  line `(b) inspect the establishments as assigned to him under the provisions of this Code,`
  line `subject to the instructions or guidelines issued by the appropriate Government from time to time.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), the Inspector-cum-Facilitator may,—`
  line
  line `(a) examine any person who is found in any premises of the establishment, whom the Inspector-cumFacilitator has reasonable cause to believe, is an employee of the establishment;`
  line
  line `(b) require any person whom the Inspector-cum-Facilitator has reasonable cause to believe, is an`
  line `employer of the establishment, to produce any document or to give any information, which is in his`
  line `power with respect to any of the purposes for which the inspection is made;`
  line
  line `(c) search, seize or take copies of such register, record of wages or notices or portions thereof as the`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator may consider relevant in respect of an offence under this Code and which the`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator has reason to believe has been committed by the employer;`
  line
  line `(d) bring to the notice of the appropriate Government defects or abuses not covered by any law for`
  line `the time being in force; and`
  line
  line `(e) exercise such other powers as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(7) Any person required to produce any document or to give any information required by an Inspectorcum-Facilitator for the purposes of sub-section (6) shall be deemed to be legally bound to do so within the`
  line `meaning of section 175 and section 176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(8) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall, so far as may be, apply`
  line `to the search or seizure for the purposes of sub-section (6), as they apply to the search or seizure made under`
  line `the authority of a warrant issued under section 94 of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (54147)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Maintenance of records, registers, returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54147&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `An employer of an establishment shall—`
  line
  line `(a) maintain records and registers in the form prescribed by the appropriate Government,`
  line `electronically or otherwise, containing such particulars and details with regard to persons employed,`
  line `muster roll, wages and such other particulars and details, in such manner, as may be prescribed by the`
  line `appropriate Government including—`
  line
  line `(i) number of days for which work performed by employees;`
  line
  line `(ii) number of hours of work performed by the employees;`
  line
  line `(iii) wage paid;`
  line
  line `(iv) leave, leave wages, wages for overtime work and attendance;`
  line
  line `(v) employees identification number, by whatever nomenclature it may be called;`
  line
  line `(vi) number of dangerous occurrences, accidents, injuries in respect of which compensation has`
  line `been paid by the employer and the amount of such compensation relating to Chapter IV and Chapter`
  line `VII, respectively;`
  line
  line `(vii) statutory deductions made by employer from the wages of an employee in respect of Chapter`
  line `III and Chapter IV;`
  line
  line `(viii) details as to cess paid in respect of building and other construction work;`
  line
  line `(ix) total number of employees (regular, contractual or fixed term employment) on the day`
  line specified;
  line
  line `(x) persons recruited during a particular period;`
  line
  line `(xi) occupational details of the employees; and`
  line
  line `(xii) vacancies for which suitable candidates were not available during the specified period.`
  line
  line `(b) display notices at the workplaces of the employees in such manner and form as may be prescribed`
  line `by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(c) issue wage slips to the employees, in electronic forms or otherwise; and`
  line
  line `(d) file such return electronically or otherwise to such officer or authority in such manner and during`
  line `such periods as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that matters to be provided under the rules required to be made under this section relating to`
  line `Chapter III shall, instead of providing them in rules to be made by the Central Government, be provided in`
  line `the Provident Fund Scheme or the Pension Scheme or the Insurance Scheme, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the forms of records and registers and that of the returns to be filed under Chapter`
  line `IV shall be specified in the regulations instead of providing them in the rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (54148)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Employer not to reduce wages, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54148&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `No employer in relation to an establishment to which this`
  line `Code or any scheme framed thereunder applies shall, by reason only of his liability for the payment of any`
  line `contribution under this Code, or any charges thereunder reduce whether directly or indirectly, the wages of`
  line `any employee to whom the provisions of this Code or any scheme framed thereunder applies or the total`
  line `quantum of benefits to which such employee is entitled under the terms of his employment, express or`
  line implied.
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (54149)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Assessment and determination of dues from employer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54149&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, authorise, such officers of the Central Board or the Corporation, as the case may be, not below`
  line `the rank of Group 'A' officer of that Government, to function as the Authorised Officers for the purposes of`
  line `Chapter III or Chapter IV, as the case may be, who may, by order---`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where a dispute arises regarding the applicability of Chapter III or Chapter IV, as the`
  line `case may be, to an establishment, decide such dispute; and`
  line
  line `(b) determine the amount due from any employer under any provision of Chapter III or Chapter IV,`
  line `as the case may be, or the schemes, or rules, regulations made under such Chapter; and`
  line
  line `(c) for any of the purposes relating to clause (a) and clause (b), conduct such inquiry, as he may deem`
  line `necessary for such purposes:`
  line
  line `Provided that no proceeding under this sub-section shall be initiated after the expiry of the period of`
  line `five years from the date on which the dispute referred to in clause (a) is alleged to have been arisen or, as`
  line `the case may be, the amount referred to in clause (b) is alleged to have been due from an employer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), the inquiry`
  line `under sub-section (1), as far as practicable, shall be held on day-to-day basis and endeavour shall be made`
  line `to ensure that the inquiry is concluded within a period of two years:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the inquiry is not concluded within the said period of two years, the Authorised`
  line `Officer conducting such inquiry shall record the circumstances and reasons for not having concluded so`
  line `and submit the circumstances and reasons so recorded to the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the`
  line `Director General of the Corporation, as the case may be, or such other officer authorised by him in this`
  line `behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the`
  line `Corporation, as the case may be, after considering the circumstances and the reasons which have been`
  line `submitted by the Authorised Officer may grant an extension for a period up to one year to conclude the said`
  line `inquiry:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the inquiries which are pending immediately before the date of commencement of`
  line `this Code shall be concluded by the Authorised Officer within a period not exceeding two years from the`
  line `date of such commencement.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authorised Officer conducting the inquiry under sub-section (1) shall, for the purposes of such`
  line `inquiry have the same powers as are vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908),`
  line `for trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person or examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit; and`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses,`
  line
  line `and any such inquiry shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and`
  line `228, and for the purpose of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) No order shall be made under sub-section (1), unless the employer concerned is given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of representing his case.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the employer, employee or any other person required to attend the inquiry under`
  line `sub-section (1) fails to attend such inquiry without assigning any valid reason or fails to produce any`
  line `document or to file any report or return when called upon to do so by the Authorised Officer conducting`
  line `the inquiry, such inquiry officer may decide the applicability of the relevant provisions of this Code or`
  line `determine the amount due from any employer, as the case may be, on the basis of the evidence adduced`
  line `during such inquiry and other documents available on record.`
  line
  line `(6) Where an order under sub-section (1) is passed against an employer ex parte, he may, within three`
  line `months from the date of communication of such order, apply to the Authorised Officer for setting aside`
  line `such order and if the Authorised Officer is satisfied that the show cause notice was not duly served or that`
  line `such employer was prevented by any sufficient cause from appearing when the inquiry was held, the`
  line `Authorised Officer shall make an order setting aside his earlier order and shall appoint a date for proceeding`
  line `with the inquiry:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be set aside merely on the ground that there has been an irregularity`
  line `in the service of the show cause notice if the Authorised Officer is satisfied that the employer had notice of`
  line `the date of hearing and had sufficient time to appear before the Authorised Officer.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---Where an appeal has been preferred under this Code against an order passed ex parte`
  line `and such appeal has been disposed of otherwise than on the ground that the appellant has withdrawn the`
  line `appeal, no application shall lie under this sub-section for setting aside the ex parte order.`
  line
  line `(7) No order passed under this section shall be set aside on any application under sub-section (6) unless`
  line `notice thereof has been served on the opposite party.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (54150)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Appeal against order of Authorised officer relating to chapter IV.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54150&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `If an employer is not`
  line `satisfied with the order referred to in section 125 and relates to Chapter IV, he may prefer an appeal to the`
  line `appellate authority not below the rank of the Joint Director of the Corporation as may be provided by`
  line `regulations, within sixty days from the date of such order after depositing twenty-five per cent. of the`
  line `contribution so ordered or the contribution as per his own calculation, whichever is higher, with the`
  line `Corporation:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority shall decide the appeal within a period of six months from the date`
  line `of preferring the appeal:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the employer finally succeeds in the appeal, the Corporation shall refund such`
  line `deposit to the employer together with such interest as may be specified in the regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (54151)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Interest on amount due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54151&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `Except where expressly provided otherwise in this Code, the employer`
  line `shall be liable to pay simple interest at such rate as may be notified from time to time by the Central`
  line `Government, from the date on which any amount has become due under this Code till the date of its actual`
  line payment.
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (54152)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Power to recover damages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54152&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `Where an employer makes default in the payment of any`
  line `contribution which he is liable to pay in accordance with the provisions of Chapter III or Chapter IV, as the`
  line `case may be, or any scheme framed thereunder or in the transfer of accumulations under Chapter III, or in`
  line `the payment of any charges payable under any other provision of this Code, the Central Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case may be, or such other officer as may`
  line `be authorised, by notification, by the appropriate Government, may levy on, and recover from, the employer`
  line `by way of damages, an amount not exceeding the amount of arrears, in such manner as may be specified in`
  line `the regulations for the purposes of Chapter IV and in respect of Provident Fund Scheme, Pension Scheme`
  line `and Insurance Scheme, such levy and recovery shall be in the manner as may be specified in the respective`
  line `schemes framed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that before levying and recovering such damages, the employer shall be given an opportunity`
  line `of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Board or the Corporation, as the case may be, may reduce or waive`
  line `the damages levied under this section in relation to an establishment for which a resolution plan or`
  line `repayment plan recommending such waiver has been approved by the adjudicating authority established`
  line `under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016) subject to the terms and conditions as may`
  line `be specified by notification, by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (54153)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Recovery of amount due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54153&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any amount due from an employer or any other person in relation`
  line `to an establishment including any contribution or cess payable, charges, interest, damages, or benefit or any`
  line `other amount may, if the amount is in arrear, be recovered in the manner specified in this section and`
  line `sections 130 to 132.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any amount is in arrear under this Code, the Authorised Officer, or the competent authority,`
  line `as the case may be, shall issue to the Recovery Officer referred to in sub-section (4), a certificate`
  line `electronically or otherwise, specifying the amount of arrears and the Recovery Officer, on receipt of such`
  line `certificate, shall proceed to recover the amount specified therein from the establishment or, as the case may`
  line `be, the employer by one or more of the modes mentioned below, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) attachment and sale of the movable or immovable property of the establishment or, as the case`
  line `may be, of the employer;`
  line
  line `(b) arrest of the employer and his detention in prison;`
  line
  line `(c) appointing a receiver for the management of the movable or immovable properties of the defaulter:`
  line
  line `Provided that the attachment and sale of any property under this section shall first be effected against`
  line `the properties of the establishment and where such attachment and sale is insufficient for recovering the`
  line `whole of the amount or arrears specified in the certificate, the Recovery Officer may move such proceeding`
  line `against the property of the employer for recovery of the whole or any part of such arrears.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authorised Officer or the competent authority, as the case may be, may issue a certificate under`
  line `sub-section (2), notwithstanding that proceeding for recovery of the arrears by any other mode has been`
  line taken.
  line
  line `(4) The Authorised Officer or the competent authority, as the case may be, may forward the certificate`
  line `issued under this section, to the Recovery Officer within whose jurisdiction the employer—`
  line
  line `(a) carries on his business or profession or within whose jurisdiction the principal place of his`
  line `establishment is situate; or`
  line
  line `(b) resides or any movable or immovable property of, the establishment or, the employer is situated.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an establishment or the employer has property within the jurisdiction of more than one`
  line `Recovery Officer and the Recovery Officer to whom a certificate is sent by the Authorised Officer or the`
  line `competent authority, as the case may be—`
  line
  line `(a) is not able to recover the entire amount by the sale of the property, movable or immovable, within`
  line `his jurisdiction, or`
  line
  line `(b) is of the opinion that, for the purpose of expediting or securing the recovery of the whole or any`
  line `part of the amount, it is necessary so to do,`
  line
  line `he may send the certificate or, where only a part of the amount is to be recovered, a copy of the certificate`
  line `certified by him, specifying the amount to be recovered, to the Recovery Officer within whose jurisdiction`
  line `the establishment or the employer has property or the employer resides, and thereupon that Recovery`
  line `Officer shall proceed to recover the amount due under this section as if the certificate or the copy thereof`
  line `had been the certificate sent to him by the Authorised Officer or the competent authority, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (54154)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Validity of certificate and amendment thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54154&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Authorised Officer or the`
  line `competent authority, as the case may be, issues a certificate to a Recovery Officer under section 129, it`
  line `shall not be open to the employer to dispute before the Recovery Officer the correctness of the amount, and`
  line `no objection to the certificate on any other ground shall be entertained by the Recovery Officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the issue of a certificate to a Recovery Officer, the Authorised Officer or the`
  line `competent authority, as the case may be, shall have power to withdraw the certificate or correct any clerical`
  line `or arithmetical mistake in the certificate by sending intimation to the Recovery Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The Authorised Officer or the competent authority, as the case may be, shall intimate to the`
  line `Recovery Officer any orders of withdrawing or cancelling a certificate or any correction made by him in`
  line `respect of the said certificate under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding that a certificate has been issued to the Recovery Officer for the recovery of any`
  line `amount, the Authorised Officer or the competent authority, as the case may be, may grant time to the`
  line `employer for payment of the amount recoverable under the certificate and thereupon the Recovery Officer`
  line `shall stay the proceedings until the expiry of the time so granted.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a certificate for the recovery of amount has been issued, the Authorised Officer or the`
  line `competent authority, as the case may be, shall keep the Recovery Officer informed of any amount paid or`
  line `time granted for payment, subsequent to the issue of such certificate.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the order giving rise to a demand of amount for which a certificate for recovery has been`
  line `issued under section 129 has been modified in appeal or other proceeding under this Code, resulting in`
  line `reduction of the demand but the order is the subject matter of further proceeding under this Code, the`
  line `Authorised Officer or the competent authority, as the case may be, shall stay the recovery of such part of`
  line `the amount of the certificate as pertains to the said reduction for the period for which the appeal or other`
  line `proceeding remains pending.`
  line
  line `(7) Where a certificate for the recovery of amount has been issued and subsequently the amount of the`
  line `outstanding demand is reduced as a result of an appeal or other proceeding under this Code, the Authorised`
  line `Officer or the competent authority, as the case may be, shall, when the order being the subject matter of`
  line `such appeal or other proceeding becomes final and conclusive, amend the certificate or withdraw it, as the`
  line `case may be in consonance with such finality or conclusion.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (54155)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Other modes of recovery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54155&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding the issue of a certificate to the Recovery Officer`
  line `under section 129, the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation,`
  line `as the case may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation so authorised by it in this`
  line `behalf, may, recover the amount by any one or more of the modes provided in this section.`
  line
  line `(2) If any amount is due from any person to any employer who is in arrears, the Central Provident Fund`
  line `Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case may be, or any other officer of such`
  line `Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf, may, require such person to deduct from the`
  line `said amount the arrears so due, and such person shall comply with any such requisition and shall pay the`
  line `sum so deducted to the credit of the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the`
  line `Corporation, as the case may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation so authorised by`
  line `it in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any part of the amount exempt from attachment`
  line `in execution of a decree of a civil court under section 60 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(3) (a) The Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the`
  line `case may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf may,`
  line `at any time or from time to time, by notice in writing, require any person from whom money is due or may`
  line `become due to the employer or, as the case may be, the establishment or any person who holds or may`
  line `subsequently hold money for or on account of the employer or, as the case may be, the establishment, to`
  line `pay to the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, or any other officer authorised by it in this behalf either forthwith upon the money becoming due`
  line `or being held at or within the time specified in the notice (not being before the money becomes due or is`
  line `held) so much of the money as is sufficient to pay the amount due from the employer in respect of arrears`
  line `or the whole of the money when it is equal to or less than that amount.`
  line
  line `(b) A notice under this sub-section may be issued to any person who holds or may subsequently hold`
  line `any money for or on account of the employer jointly with any other person and for the purposes of this subsection, the shares of the joint holders in such account shall be presumed, until the contrary is proved, to be`
  line equal.
  line
  line `(c) A copy of the notice shall be forwarded to the employer at his last address known to the Central`
  line `Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case may be, or any other`
  line `officer of such Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf and in the case of a joint account`
  line `to all the joint holders at their last addresses so known.`
  line
  line `(d) Save as otherwise provided in this sub-section, every person to whom a notice is issued under this`
  line `sub-section shall be bound to comply with such notice, and, in particular, where any such notice is issued`
  line `to a post office, bank or an insurer, it shall not be necessary for any pass book, deposit receipt, policy or`
  line `any other document to be produced for the purpose of any entry, endorsement or the like being made before`
  line `payment is made notwithstanding any rule, practice or requirement to the contrary.`
  line
  line `(e) Any claim respecting any property in relation to which a notice under this sub-section has been`
  line `issued arising after the date of the notice shall be void as against any demand contained in the notice.`
  line
  line `(f) Where a person to whom a notice under this sub-section is sent objects to it by statement on oath`
  line `that the sum demanded or any part thereof is not due to the employer or that he does not hold any money`
  line `for or on account of the employer, then, nothing contained in this sub-section shall be deemed to require`
  line `such person to pay any such sum or part thereof, as the case may be, but if it is discovered that such`
  line `statement was false in any material particular, such person shall be personally liable to the Central Provident`
  line `Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case may be, or any other officer of`
  line `such Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf, to the extent of his own liability to the`
  line `employer on the date of the notice, or to the extent of the employer's liability for any sum due under this`
  line `Code, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(g) The Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf, may, at`
  line `any time or from time to time, amend or revoke any notice issued under this sub-section or extend the time`
  line `for making any payment in pursuance of such notice.`
  line
  line `(h) The Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf, shall grant`
  line `a receipt for any amount paid in compliance with a notice issued under this sub-section, and the person so`
  line `paying shall be fully discharged from his liability to the employer to the extent of the amount so paid.`
  line
  line `(i) Any person discharging any liability to the employer after the receipt of a notice under this`
  line `sub-section shall be personally liable to the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General`
  line `of the Corporation, as the case may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation authorised`
  line `by it in this behalf, to the extent of his own liability to the employer so discharged or to the extent of the`
  line `employer's liability for any sum due under this Code, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(j) If the person to whom a notice under this sub-section is sent fails to make payment in pursuance`
  line `thereof to the Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf, he shall be`
  line `deemed to be an employer in default in respect of the amount specified in the notice and further proceeding`
  line `may be moved against him for the realisation of the amount as if it were an arrear due from him, in the`
  line `manner provided in sections 129 to 132 and the notice shall have the same effect as an attachment of amount`
  line `in arrears by the Recovery Officer in exercise of his powers under section 129.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf may apply`
  line `to the court in whose custody there is money belonging to the employer for payment to him of the entire`
  line `amount of such money, or if it is more than the amount due, an amount sufficient to discharge the amount`
  line due.
  line
  line `(5) The Central Provident Fund Commissioner or the Director General of the Corporation, as the case`
  line `may be, or any other officer of such Social Security Organisation authorised by it in this behalf, if so`
  line `authorised by the Central Government by general or special order, recover any arrears of amount due from`
  line `an employer or, as the case may be, from the establishment by distraint and sale of his or its movable`
  line `property in the manner laid down in the Third Schedule to the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (54156)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Application of certain provisions of Income-tax act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54156&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the Second Schedule`
  line `and the Third Schedule to the Incometax Act, 1961 and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings) Rules,`
  line `1962, as in force from time to time, shall apply with necessary modifications as if the said provisions and`
  line `the rules referred to the amount in arrears of the amount mentioned in section 129 of this Code instead of`
  line `to the income-tax:`
  line
  line `Provided that any reference in the said provisions and the rules to the “assessees” shall be construed as`
  line `a reference to an employer or establishment, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (54157)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Penalty for failure to pay contributions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54157&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `If any person,—`
  line
  line `(a) being an employer, fails to pay any contribution which he is liable to pay under this Code or rules,`
  line `regulations or schemes made thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(b) deducts or attempts to deduct from the wages of an employee, the whole or any part of employer's`
  line `contribution; or`
  line
  line `(c) in contravention of the provisions of this Code, reduces the wages or any privilege or benefits`
  line `admissible to an employee; or`
  line
  line `(d) in contravention of the provisions of Chapter IV or Chapter VI or rules, regulations or schemes`
  line `made or framed under this Code respectively, relating to such Chapters, dismisses, discharges, reduces`
  line `in rank or otherwise penalises a woman employee; or`
  line
  line `(e) fails or refuses to submit any return, report, statement or any other information required under this`
  line `Code or any rules, regulations or schemes made or framed thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(f) obstructs any Inspector-cum-Facilitator or other officer or staff of the Central Board or the`
  line `Corporation or other Social Security Organisation or a competent authority in the discharge of his`
  line `duties; or`
  line
  line `(g) fails to pay any amount of gratuity to which an employee is entitled under this Code; or`
  line
  line `(h) fails to pay any amount of compensation to which an employee is entitled under this Code; or`
  line
  line `(i) fails to provide any maternity benefit to which a woman is entitled under this Code; or`
  line
  line `(j) fails to send to a competent authority a statement which he is required to send under Chapter VII;`
  line or
  line
  line `(k) fails to produce on demand by the Inspector-cum-Facilitator any register or document in his`
  line `custody kept in pursuance of this Code or the rules, regulations or schemes made or framed thereunder;`
  line or
  line
  line `(l) fails to pay the cess for building workers which he is liable to pay under this Code; or`
  line
  line `(m) is guilty of any contravention of or non-compliance with any of the requirements of this Code or`
  line `the rules or the regulations or schemes made or framed thereunder in respect of which no special penalty`
  line `is provided in this Chapter; or`
  line
  line `(n) obstructs executive officer in exercising his functions under Chapter XIII; or`
  line
  line `(o) dishonestly makes a false return, report, statement or information to be submitted thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(p) fails or makes default in complying with any condition subject to which exemption under section`
  line `143 was granted; or`
  line
  line `(q) fails to pay any administrative or inspection charges payable under any of the schemes framed`
  line `under Chapter III,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable,—`
  line
  line `(i) where he commits an offence under clause (a), with imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to three years, but—`
  line
  line `(a) which shall not be less than one year, in case of failure to pay the employee's contribution`
  line `which has been deducted by him from the employee's wages and shall also be liable to fine of one`
  line `lakh rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) which shall not be less than two months but may be extended to six months, in any other case`
  line `and shall also be liable to fine of fifty thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that the court may, for any adequate and special reasons to be recorded in the judgment,`
  line `impose a sentence of imprisonment for a lesser term;`
  line
  line `(ii) where he commits an offence under clause (g), with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `one year or with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(iii) where he commits an offence under any of the clauses (d), (f), (i), (k), (l) or (o), with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to six months or with a fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both;`
  line
  line `(iv) where he commits an offence under any of the clauses (b), (c), (e), (h), (j), (m), (n), (p) or (q), with`
  line `fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (54158)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Enhanced punishment in certain cases after previous conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54158&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, having been`
  line `convicted by a court of an offence punishable under this Code, commits the same offence shall, for second,`
  line `or every subsequent such offence, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years and with fine of two lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such second or subsequent offence is for failure by the employer to pay any`
  line `contribution, charges, cess, maternity benefit, gratuity or compensation which under this Code he is liable`
  line `to pay, he shall, for such second or subsequent offence, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `may extend to three years but which shall not be less than two years and shall also be liable to fine of three`
  line `lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (54159)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54159&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Chapter has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was directly in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all due`
  line `diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence has been committed by a`
  line `company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or is`
  line `attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, secretary or other officer of the company, such`
  line `director, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) “company” means any body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) “Director”, in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (54160)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54160&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this`
  line `Code, except on a complaint made by an aggrieved person or such officer as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government for the purposes of offences relating to Chapter III and Chapter IV and the rules, regulations`
  line `or schemes made or framed under this Code relating to those Chapters, and for the purposes of offences`
  line `relating to other provisions of this Code and the rules, regulations or schemes made or framed thereunder,`
  line `by the officer notified by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), no prosecution under this Code shall be`
  line `instituted, except by or with the previous sanction of the authority notified by the Central Government for`
  line `the purposes of offences relating to Chapter III and Chapter IV and the rules, regulations or schemes made`
  line `or framed under this Code relating to those Chapters; and for the purposes of offences relating to other`
  line `provisions of this Code and the rules, regulations or schemes made or framed thereunder, the authority`
  line `notified by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class shall`
  line `try any offence punishable under this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a single complaint may be filed under that`
  line `sub-section by more than one aggrieved persons if they are aggrieved by the same or similar offence`
  line `committed at a place or different places within the jurisdiction of the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (54161)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Prior opportunity before prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54161&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, the`
  line `Inspector-cum-Facilitator or any other officer notified for the purposes of offences relating to Chapter III`
  line `and Chapter IV and the rules, regulations or schemes made or framed under this Code relating to those`
  line `Chapters, by the Central Government; and for the purposes of offences relating to other provisions of this`
  line `Code and the rules, regulations or schemes made or framed under this Code relating thereto, by the`
  line `appropriate Government, shall, before initiation of prosecution proceeding against an employer for any`
  line `offence under this Chapter, give an opportunity to the employer to comply with the aforesaid relevant`
  line `provisions by way of a written direction, which shall lay down a time period for such compliance, and, if`
  line `the employer complies with the direction within such period, then, no such proceeding shall be initiated`
  line `against the employer; but no such opportunity shall be accorded to an employer, if the violation of the same`
  line `nature of such provisions is repeated within a period of three years from the date on which such first`
  line `violation was committed and in such case the prosecution shall be initiated in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (54162)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54162&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence committed for the first time, punishable under this Chapter, being`
  line `an offence---`
  line
  line `(i) punishable with fine only; or`
  line
  line `(ii) punishable with imprisonment for a term which is not more than one year and also with fine,`
  line
  line `may, on an application made, either before or after the institution of any prosecution, be compounded by`
  line `an officer authorised by the Central Government for the purposes of offences relating to Chapter III and`
  line `Chapter IV and the rules, regulations or schemes made or framed under this Code relating to those Chapters,`
  line `by the Central Government; and for the purposes of offences relating to other provisions of this Code and`
  line `the rules, regulations or schemes made or framed under this Code relating thereto, by the appropriate`
  line `Government, in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central Government on payment by the offender`
  line `to the appropriate Government the amount---`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an offence punishable with fine only, the half of the maximum fine provided for that`
  line `offence; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of an offence punishable with imprisonment for a term which is not more than one`
  line `year and also with fine, the three-fourth of the maximum fine provided for that offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply to an offence committed by a person for the second`
  line `time or thereafter within a period of three years from the date---`
  line
  line `(i) of commission of a similar offence which was earlier compounded; or`
  line
  line `(ii) of commission of similar offence for which such person was earlier convicted.`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer referred to in sub-section (1) shall exercise the powers to compound an offence,`
  line `subject to the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government for the purposes of offences`
  line `relating to Chapter III and Chapter IV and the rules, regulations or schemes made or framed under this Code`
  line `relating to those Chapters; and for the purposes of offences relating to other provisions of this Code and the`
  line `rules, regulations or schemes made or framed under this Code relating thereto, by the appropriate`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) Every application for the compounding of an offence shall be made in such form and in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed by the appropriate Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution, no prosecution shall`
  line `be instituted in relation to such offence, against the offender in relation to whom the offence is so`
  line compounded.
  line
  line `(6) Where the compounding of any offence is made after the institution of any prosecution, such`
  line `compounding shall be brought to the notice of the court in which the prosecution is pending in writing by`
  line `the officer referred to in sub-section (1), and on such notice of the compounding of the offence being given`
  line `to the court, the person against whom the offence is so compounded shall be discharged.`
  line
  line `(7) Any person who fails to comply with the order made by the officer referred to in sub-section (1),`
  line `shall be liable to pay a sum equivalent to twenty per cent. of the maximum fine provided for the offence, in`
  line `addition to such fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (54163)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Reporting of vacancies to career centres.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54163&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification, require that from such date as may be specified in the notification, the employer in every`
  line `establishment or any class or category of establishments, before filling up any vacancy in any employment`
  line `in that establishment or such class or category of establishments, as the case may be, shall report or cause`
  line `to be reported, that vacancy to such career centre as may be specified in the notification, and the employer`
  line `shall thereupon comply with such requisition.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the appropriate Government may prescribe the following,`
  line `namely:—`
  line
  line `i) the manner in which the vacancies, referred to in sub-section (1), shall be reported to the career`
  line `centres electronically or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(ii) the form in which such vacancies shall be reported to the career centres; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the manner and form of filing the return by the employer, to the concerned career centre.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be deemed to impose any obligation upon any employer`
  line `to recruit any person through the career centre to fill any vacancy merely because such vacancy has been`
  line reported.
  line
  line `(4) The executive officer shall have access to any record or document in the possession of any employer`
  line `required to furnish any information or returns for the purposes of this Chapter and may enter, at any`
  line `reasonable time, any premises where he believes such record or document to be and inspect or take copies`
  line `of such records or documents or ask any question necessary for obtaining any information required.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (54164)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Exclusions from application of this chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54164&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of section 139 shall not apply`
  line `in relation to vacancies,—`
  line
  line `(a) in any employment in agriculture (including horticulture) in any establishment in private sector`
  line `other than employment in plantation; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any employment in domestic service; or`
  line
  line `(c) in any employment connected with the staff of Parliament or any State Legislature; or`
  line
  line `(d) in any employment the total duration of which is less than ninety days; or`
  line
  line `(e) in any class or category of establishments as may be notified by the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(f) in any establishment (other than Government establishment) with less than twenty or such number`
  line `of employees as may be notified by the Central Government; and`
  line
  line `(g) in any other employment as may be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless the Central Government, by notification direct, the provisions of this Chapter shall not apply`
  line `in relation to—`
  line
  line `(a) vacancies which are proposed to be filled through promotion or by absorption of surplus staff of`
  line `any branch or department of the same establishment or through independent recruitment agencies such`
  line `as Union Public Service Commission, Staff Selection Commission or a State Public Service`
  line `Commission or any other agencies as may be notified by the Central Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) vacancies in an employment which carries a monthly remuneration of less than an amount notified`
  line `by the appropriate Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (54165)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Social Security Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54165&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be established by the Central Government a Social`
  line `Security Fund for social security and welfare of the unorganised workers, gig workers and platform workers`
  line `and the sources of the fund shall comprise of funding received—`
  line
  line `(i) under sub-section (3) of section 109;`
  line
  line `(ii) under sub-section (3) of section 114;`
  line
  line `(iii) from the composition of the offences under this Code relating to Central Government and from`
  line `any other Social Security Fund established under any other central labour law.`
  line
  line `(2) A separate account shall be established and maintained for the funding mentioned under each of the`
  line `clauses (i), (ii) and (iii).`
  line
  line `(3) Social Security Fund referred to in sub-section (1) shall be expended for the purposes for which`
  line `each separate account has been established and maintained under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The Social Security Fund shall be established and administered in the manner prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) There shall be established by the State Government a Social Security Fund for the welfare of the`
  line `unorganised workers in which there shall be credited the amount received from—`
  line
  line `(i) the composition of offences under this Code relating to the State Government; and`
  line
  line `(ii) such other sources as may be prescribed by the State Government, and the fund shall be`
  line `administered and expended for the welfare of the unorganised workers in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (54166)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Application of Aadhaar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54166&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) An employee or unorganised worker or any other person, as the`
  line `case may be, for—`
  line
  line `(a) registration as member or beneficiary; or`
  line
  line `(b) seeking benefit whether in kind, cash or medical sickness benefit or pension, gratuity or maternity`
  line `benefit or any other benefit or for withdrawal of fund; or`
  line
  line `(c) availing services of career centre; or`
  line
  line `(d) receiving any payment or medical attendance as Insured Person himself or for his dependants,`
  line
  line `under this Code or rules, regulations or schemes made or framed thereunder, shall establish his identity or,`
  line `as the case may be, the identity of his family members or dependants through Aadhaar number and for such`
  line `purpose the expression “Aadhaar” shall have the meaning as defined in clause (a) of section 2 of the`
  line `Aadhaar (The Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of`
  line `2016):`
  line
  line `Provided that any foreigner employee shall obtain and submit Aadhaar number for establishing his`
  line `identity, as soon as possible, on becoming resident within the meaning of clause (v) of section 2 of the`
  line `Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of`
  line `2016).`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), the Aadhaar number issued to an individual shall be in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 3 of the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other`
  line `Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (54167)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Power to exempt establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54167&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1)Notwithstanding anything contained in this Code, the`
  line `appropriate Government may, by notification, and subject to the conditions which may include the`
  line `eligibility conditions to be fulfilled prior to grant of exemption and the conditions to be complied with after`
  line `exemption, as may be prescribed by the Central Government in this behalf, grant exemption to an establishment or class of establishments (including factory or other establishments under the control of`
  line `Central Government or State Government or local bodies) or employees or class of employees, from any`
  line `or all of the provisions of this Code or the scheme framed thereunder as may be specified in the notification`
  line `and may renew for further period such exemption by like notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such exemption,—`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of Provident Fund Scheme, Pension Scheme and Insurance Scheme, without prior`
  line `consultation with the Central Board; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of Chapter IV, without prior consultation with the Corporation,`
  line `shall be granted or renewed and the Central Board or the Corporation, as the case may be, shall on such`
  line `consultation forward its view to the appropriate Government within such time as may be prescribed by that`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) The appropriate Government may, in the notification referred to in sub-section (1), specify therein`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed by that Government, which the exempted establishment or the class of`
  line `establishments or an employee or class of employees, as the case may be, shall comply with after such`
  line `exemption:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purpose of grant of exemption in respect of Provident Fund Scheme, Pension`
  line `Scheme and Insurance Scheme, the terms and conditions of exemption shall be specified in such respective`
  line schemes.
  line
  line `(3) The exemption granted under sub-section (1) to an establishment or class of establishments or an`
  line `employee or class of employees, as the case may be, shall be initially for a period of three years from the`
  line `date of publication of such notification and may be extended by the appropriate Government to the extent`
  line `of such period as may be prescribed by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the purpose of grant of exemption in respect of Provident Fund Scheme, Pension`
  line `Scheme and Insurance Scheme, exemption may be extended for such period as may be specified in such`
  line `respective schemes.`
  line `(4) The exemption granted under sub-section (1) shall only be granted if the employees in the`
  line `establishment or class of establishments or an employee or the class of employees so exempted are`
  line `otherwise in receipt of benefits substantially similar or superior to the benefits provided in the provisions`
  line `of the Code or the scheme framed thereunder.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of administering the fund, managing the investments, maintaining accounts of the`
  line `contributions, withdrawals, credit of interest in respect of each employee of the fund created, and any other`
  line `matter specified in the scheme for any exempted establishment or class of establishments, or employees or`
  line `class of employees, a board of trustees shall be constituted by the employer which will be a legal entity`
  line `which can sue and can be sued and the conditions for management of the trust shall be prescribed by the`
  line `appropriate Government as part of the conditions for exemption:`
  line
  line `Provided that conditions for administering the fund, managing the investments, maintaining accounts`
  line `of the contributions, withdrawals, credit of interest in respect of each employee of the fund created, in`
  line `respect of exemption from Provident Fund Scheme, Pension Scheme and Insurance Scheme shall be`
  line `specified in such respective schemes.`
  line
  line `(6) Where an exemption is granted under this section from operation of any or all the provisions of the`
  line `Code or any of the scheme under Chapter III, to any establishment, class of establishments, employee or`
  line `class of employees, the employer in relation to such establishment shall furnish such returns electronically`
  line `in respect of persons employed, accounts maintained in respect of employees, investments made from the`
  line `fund, provide facilities for inspection and pay such inspection charges as the Central Government may`
  line direct.
  line
  line `(7) If employer in relation to any establishment or class of establishments or employee or class of`
  line `employees in respect of whom the exemption has been granted under sub-section (1), fails to comply with`
  line `any of the conditions specified under this section, then, the appropriate Government may on such failure,`
  line `cancel the exemption so granted.`
  line
  line `(8) Where any exemption granted under sub-section (1) is cancelled, the entire amount of surplus and`
  line `reserves, if any, and accumulations to the credit of every employee, to whom such exemption applied, in`
  line `the exempted fund of the establishment in which he is employed, shall be transferred to the respective`
  line `statutory fund created under this Code within such time and manner as specified in the conditions for grant`
  line `of exemption:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any cancellation of exemption from the Provident Fund Scheme, Pension`
  line `Scheme and Insurance Scheme, the time limit, form and manner of transfer of accumulations of exempted`
  line `employees from the exempted funds to such respective funds shall be specified in such respective schemes.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, the employer of an establishment exempted`
  line `under sub-section (1), after the resolution of the board of trustees of the establishment to that effect may`
  line `make an application to the appropriate Government for surrender of the exemption granted under that subsection from the date specified in the application and the appropriate Government may on receipt of that`
  line `application, allow the employer to remit the contribution in the statutory funds under this Code from the`
  line `date specified in the application and process the application for cancellation of exemption and on such`
  line `cancellation, the employer and the board of trustees shall transfer accumulation of each employee and`
  line `surplus and reserves from the fund referred to in sub-section (5), to the concerned statutory funds under this`
  line `Code within such time and in such manner as may be notified by the appropriate Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of any surrender of exemption from the Provident Fund Scheme, the Pension`
  line `Scheme and the Insurance Scheme, the time limit, form and manner of transfer of accumulation of exempted`
  line `employees and surplus and reserves from the fund referred to in sub-section (5), to the concerned statutory`
  line `funds under this Code shall be such as may be specified in the concerned schemes framed under Chapter`
  line III.
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (54168)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Power to defer or reduce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54168&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in Chapter III or Chapter IV,`
  line `the Central Government may by order, defer or reduce employer's contribution, or employee's contribution,`
  line `or both, payable under Chapter III or Chapter IV, as the case may be, for a period up to three months at a`
  line `time, in respect of establishment to which Chapter III or Chapter IV, as the case may be, applies, for whole`
  line `of India or part thereof in the event of pandemic, endemic or national disaster`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (54169)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Liability in case of transfer of establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54169&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `Where an employer transfers his establishment`
  line `in whole or in part, by sale, gift, lease or licence or in any other manner whatsoever, the employer and the`
  line `person to whom the establishment is so transferred shall jointly and severally be liable to pay the amount`
  line `due in respect of any liabilities, cess or any other amount payable under this Code in respect of the periods`
  line `up to the date of such transfer:`
  line
  line `Provided that the liability of the transferee shall be limited to the value of the assets obtained by him`
  line `by such transfer.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (54170)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Members, officers and staff to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54170&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `Every member of a Social Security`
  line `Organisation and the officers and staff thereof, any Inspector-cum-Facilitator, competent authority,`
  line `Authorised Officer, Recovery Officer and any other person discharging any function under this Code, shall`
  line `be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (54171)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54171&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against—`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) a State Government;`
  line
  line `(iii) a Social Security Organisation;`
  line
  line `(iv) a competent authority;`
  line
  line `(v) any officer or staff of a Social Security Organisation; or`
  line
  line `(vi) any other person or authority, discharging the functions or exercising the powers under this Code,`
  line `for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Code or of any`
  line `rules, regulations or schemes made or framed thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (54172)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Misuse of benefits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54172&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `If the appropriate Government is satisfied in the manner prescribed by it`
  line `that any establishment or any other person has misused any benefit provided to him under this Code or`
  line `rules, regulations or schemes made or framed thereunder, then, such Government may, by notification,`
  line `deprive such establishment or other person, as the case may be, from such benefit for such time as may be`
  line `specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be passed unless an opportunity of being heard is given to such`
  line `establishment or other person, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the manner to ascertain misuse of any benefit under this section relating to Chapter`
  line `III, shall be specified in the Provident Fund Scheme or the Pension Scheme or the Insurance Scheme, as`
  line `the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (54436)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Power of central Government to give directions to state government and social security organizations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54436&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give directions to—`
  line
  line `(i) any State Government or a State Board constituted under section 12 to execute in that State, of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Code; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any of the Social Security Organisations in respect of the matters relating to the implementation`
  line `of the provisions of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (54174)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Power to frame schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54174&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, subject to the condition of`
  line `previous publication, frame schemes not inconsistent with this Code, for the purposes of giving effect to`
  line `the provisions thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (54175)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Protection against attachment, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54175&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, the amount standing to be credited in favour of the employee under Chapters`
  line `III, IV, V, VI or VII of any member of any fund under this Code, or of any exempted employee in a`
  line `provident fund maintained by his employer, shall not in any way be capable of being assigned or charged`
  line `and shall not be liable to attachment under any decree or order of any Court in respect of any debt or liability`
  line `incurred by such employee or member or the exempted employee, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any amount standing to the credit of a member in the fund or of an exempted employee in a`
  line `provident fund maintained by his employer at the time of the death of such member or the exempted`
  line `employee, as the case may be, and payable to his nominee or in case of failure of nomination, to his family`
  line `under the scheme or the rules of the fund shall, subject to any deduction authorised by the said scheme or`
  line `rules, as the case may be, vest in the nominee or such family and shall be free from any debt or other liability`
  line `incurred by the deceased or the nominee before his death and shall also not be liable to attachment under`
  line `any decree or order of any court.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, any amount due`
  line `under the Chapters referred to in sub-section (1) shall be the charge on the assets of the establishment to`
  line `which it relates and shall be paid in priority in accordance with the provisions of the Insolvency and`
  line `Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (54176)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Power to amend schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54176&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied that it is necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do, it may, by notification amend the First Schedule, Fourth Schedule, Fifth Schedule, Sixth`
  line `Schedule and Seventh Schedule by way of addition or deletion therein and upon such addition or deletion,`
  line `the Schedules shall stand to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) If the appropriate Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification amend the Second Schedule and Third Schedule by way of addition therein and not otherwise,`
  line `and upon such addition, the Schedules shall stand to have been amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (54177)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54177&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Code, the following`
  line `organisations constituted or established under the enactments repealed under section 164, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Board constituted under section 5A of the Employees' Provident Funds and`
  line `Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(ii) Executive Committee constituted under section 5AA of the Employees' Provident Funds and`
  line `Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952);`
  line
  line `(iii) the Corporation established under section 3 of the Employees' State Insurance Act, 1948 (34 of`
  line `1948);`
  line
  line `(iv) the Medical Benefit Council constituted under section 10 of the Employees' State Insurance Act,`
  line `1948 (34 of 1948);`
  line
  line `(v) the Standing Committee of the Corporation constituted under section 8 of the Employees' State`
  line `Insurance Act, 1948 (34 of 1948); and`
  line
  line `(vi) the Board constituted under sub-section (1) of section 18 of the Building and Other Construction`
  line `Workers (Regulation of Employment and Condition of Service) Act, 1996, shall, after the`
  line `commencement of this Code, continue to exercise the powers and discharge the functions of the`
  line `corresponding organisations under this Code, respectively, the Central Board of Trustees for Employees`
  line `Provident Fund constituted under section 4, the Executive Committee constituted under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 4, the Employees State Insurance Corporation, constituted under section 5, the Medical`
  line `Benefit Committee constituted under sub-section (5) of section 5, the Standing Committee constituted`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 5, Building Workers' Welfare Board constituted under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 7, as if such organisations constituted or, as the case may be, established under such repealed`
  line `enactments, had been constituted under the respective provisions of this Code, till such corresponding`
  line `organisations are constituted under this Code or till their respective time period under the repealed`
  line `enactments expire, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (54178)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Power of appropriate Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54178&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `(1) The appropriate Government may, by`
  line `notification, and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules not inconsistent with this Code`
  line `for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the amount in connection with premium for Group Insurance Scheme of the beneficiaries under`
  line `clause (c), the educational schemes for the benefit of children of the beneficiaries under clause (d) and`
  line `the medical expenses for treatment of major ailments of a beneficiary or, such dependant under clause`
  line `(e) of sub-section (6) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) manner and time within which second appeal may be filed to the Employees' Insurance Court by`
  line `the Insured Person or the Corporation under clause (b) of sub-section (7) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of commencement of proceedings before the Employees' Insurance Court, fees and`
  line `procedure thereof under sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(d) bank or other financial institution in which the gratuity shall be invested for the benefit of minor`
  line `under the third proviso to sub-section (1) of section 53;`
  line
  line `(e) the time, form and manner of nomination by an employee under sub-section (1), the time to make`
  line `fresh nomination under sub-section (4), the form and manner of modification of a nomination under`
  line `sub-section (5) and the form for fresh nomination under sub-section (6) of section 55;`
  line
  line `(f) time within which and the form in which a written application shall be made under sub-section (1)`
  line `and the form of application to the competent authority under clause (b) of sub-section (5) of section 56;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of registration of an establishment by the employer under sub-section (3) and the`
  line `manner of composition of the Board of Trustees of the approved gratuity fund and the manner in which`
  line `the competent authority may recover the amount of the gratuity payable to an employee from the insurer`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 57;`
  line
  line `(h) the qualifications and experience of the officer appointed as the competent authority under subsection (1) of section 58;`
  line
  line `(i) authority to whom an appeal may be preferred under sub-section (3) of section 72;`
  line
  line `(j) class of employers and the form of notice-book under sub-section (4) of section 82;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of recording the memorandum in a register by the competent authority under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 89;`
  line
  line `(l) such other experience and qualifications for appointment as a competent authority under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 91;`
  line
  line `(m) time limit to pay the amount of cess under section 101;`
  line
  line `(n) fees for appeal under sub-section (2) of section 105;`
  line
  line `(o) conditions to acquire, hold, sell or otherwise transfer any movable or immovable property under`
  line `sub-section (1), conditions to invest moneys, re-invest or realise investments under sub-section (2)`
  line `terms to raise loans and take measures for discharging such loans under sub-section (3) and terms to`
  line `constitute for the benefit of officers and staff or any class of them, provident or other benefit funds`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 120;`
  line
  line `(p) conditions and manner of writing off irrecoverable dues under section 121;`
  line
  line `(q) other powers of Inspector-cum-Facilitator under clause (e) of sub-section (6) of section 122;`
  line
  line `(r) form and manner for maintenance of records and registers and other particulars and details under`
  line `clause (a), manner and form for display of notices at the work places of the employees under clause (b)`
  line `and the manner and period of filing returns to the officers or authority under clause (d) of section 123;`
  line
  line `(s) the form and manner of application for compounding of an offence under sub-section (4) of section`
  line 138;
  line
  line `(t) the manner and form for reporting vacancies and form for filing the return by the employer, to the`
  line `concerned career centre under sub-section (2) of section 139;`
  line
  line `(u) the time within which the Central Board or the Corporation, as the case may be, shall forward its`
  line `view to the appropriate Government under sub-section (1), conditions which the exempted`
  line `establishment or the class of establishments or an employee or class of employees, as the case may be,`
  line `shall comply with after such exemption under sub-section (2) and conditions for management of the`
  line `trust under sub-section (5) of section 143;`
  line
  line `(v) manner of determining the misuse of any benefit by an establishment or by any other person under`
  line `section 148; and`
  line
  line `(w) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed by the appropriate Government`
  line `under the provisions of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (54179)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Power of central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54179&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules not inconsistent with this Code,`
  line `for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner, and the conditions subject to which, the provisions of Chapter III shall be made`
  line `inapplicable to an establishment by the Central Provident Fund Commissioner, under sub-section (5)`
  line `and the manner, and the conditions subject to which the provisions of that Chapter IV shall be made`
  line `inapplicable to an establishment by the Director General of the Corporation under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 1;`
  line
  line `(b) manner of establishment and maintenance of career centre and the career services under clause`
  line `(9), the income of dependant parents (including father-in-law and mother-in-law of a woman`
  line `employee), under sub-clause (e) of clause (33) and other authority who shall be deemed to be the`
  line `occupier under sub-clause (c) and the matters which are directly related to the condition of ship, for`
  line `which the owner of ship shall be deemed to be the occupier under the proviso to the said sub-clause (c)`
  line `of clause (52), of section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) the time and manner of registration of establishment, the manner of making application for`
  line `cancellation of the registration, the conditions subject to which the registration shall be cancelled and`
  line `the procedure of cancellation and other matters relating thereto in respect of an establishment to which`
  line `Chapter III or Chapter IV applies, and whose business activities are in the process of closure, under`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of administration of the funds vested in the Central Board under sub-section (1), the`
  line `manner to assist the Central Board in performance of its functions by Executive Committee under subsection (3), the terms and conditions, including tenure of office of members of the Central Board and`
  line `Executive Committee under sub-section (6) and the other functions and the manner of performing such`
  line `functions under sub-section (7), of section 4;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of administration of the Corporation and the manner of representation of States under`
  line `clause (d) of sub-section (1), the manner of constitution of Standing Committee under sub-section (3),`
  line `the manner of administration of the affairs of the Corporation, exercise of powers and performance of`
  line `functions by the Standing Committee under clause (a) of sub-section (4), the duties and powers of`
  line `Medical Benefit Committee under clause (b) of sub-section (5) and the terms and conditions, including`
  line `tenure of office, subject to which a member of the Corporation and Standing Committee shall discharge`
  line `their respective duties under sub-section (7) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of exercising the powers and performance of the functions by the National Social`
  line `Security Board under sub-section (1), the manner of nomination of members, their term of office and`
  line `other conditions of service, procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions and manner of`
  line `filling vacancies under sub-section (4) and time, place and rules of procedure relating to the transaction`
  line `of business under sub-section (6) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(g) other welfare measures and facilities under clause (j) of sub-section (6) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(h) the intervals at which Social Security Organisation or any Committee thereof shall meet and the`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at meetings under sub-section (1), and the fee and`
  line `allowances of members of such Social Security Organisation or Committee under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 9;`
  line
  line `(i) manner of reconstitution of the Corporation or the Central Board or the National Social Security`
  line `Board or the State Unorganised Workers' Board or the Building Workers' Welfare Board or any of the`
  line `Committees under sub-section (1) and the alternate arrangements for the purpose of administration of`
  line `the relevant provisions of this Code under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of maintenance of a provident fund account in relation to the establishment under subsection (1) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(k) the form, manner, time limits and fees for filing of appeal under sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(l) salary and allowances of the Director General or the Financial Commissioner under sub-section`
  line `(3), their powers and duties under sub-section (4) and maximum monthly salary limit under the proviso`
  line `to sub-section (7) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of investment of Employees' State Insurance Fund or any other money which is held`
  line `by Corporation under sub-section (4) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(n) limits for defraying of expenditure under clause (k) of section 26;`
  line
  line `(o) conditions to acquire, hold, sell or otherwise transfer any movable or immovable property under`
  line `sub-section (1), conditions to invest moneys by the Corporation under sub-section (2) and the terms to`
  line `raise loans and taking measures for discharging such loans under sub-section (3) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(p) manner of insurance of employees under sub-section (1) of section 28;`
  line
  line `(q) the rate of contributions under sub-section (2) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(r) the type of administrative expenses and percentage of income which may be spent on expenses`
  line `and the limits for such expenses under section 30;`
  line
  line `(s) the limit for the amount of payment under the proviso to clause (f) of sub-section (1), and the`
  line `qualifications to claim benefits, conditions, rate and period thereof under sub-section (3) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(t) the limits within which the Corporation may incur expenditure from the Employees' State`
  line `Insurance Fund under section 33;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner and time within which the Insured person or the Corporation may file appeal under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (7) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(v) the rates, periods and conditions for payment of dependants' benefit under sub-section (1) and to`
  line `other dependants under sub-section (2), of section 38;`
  line
  line `(w) the qualification of an Insured Person and his family to claim medical benefit and the conditions`
  line `subject to which such benefit may be given and the scale and period thereof, under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 39, and the payment of contribution and other conditions under the third proviso thereof;`
  line
  line `(x) the structure, functions, powers and activities of the organisation for providing certain benefits to`
  line `employees in case of sickness, maternity and employment injury, under sub-section (6) of section 40;`
  line
  line `(y) extended period for insurance, the manner of satisfaction and the manner of calculation of`
  line `capitalised value of benefit payable to the employee under sub-section (1) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(z) terms and conditions subject to which the scheme may be operated under section 44;`
  line
  line `(za) the manner of obtaining an insurance by every employer, other than an employer or an`
  line `establishment belonging to, or under the control of, the Central Government or a State Government`
  line `under sub-section (1) and conditions to exempt and manner of establishing an approved gratuity fund`
  line `under sub-section (2) and the time limit to get establishment registered by the employer under`
  line `sub-section (3), of section 57;`
  line
  line `(zb) the form of notice under sub-section (1) and the proof of pregnancy and proof of delivery under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 62;`
  line
  line `(zc) the proof of miscarriage or medical termination of pregnancy under sub-section (1), the proof of`
  line `tubectomy operation under sub-section (2) and the proof of illness under sub-section (3) of section 65;`
  line
  line `(zd) the duration of breaks under section 66;`
  line
  line `(ze) the number of employees and distance for crèche facility under sub-section (1) of section 67;`
  line
  line `(zf) gross misconduct under the second proviso to sub-section (1) of section 68;`
  line
  line `(zg) rate of interest to be paid by the employer under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 77;`
  line
  line `(zh) the manner of notice under sub-section (1) and the manner of transmitting money under`
  line `sub-section (3), of section 92;`
  line
  line `(zi) the form, manner and fee for application for claim or settlement under sub-section (3) of section`
  line 93;
  line
  line `(zj) the manner and time of collection of cess under sub-section (2), manner of deposit of the cess so`
  line `collected under sub-section (3), and the uniform rate or rates of advance cess under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 100;`
  line
  line `(zk) the rate of interest in case of delayed payment of cess under section 101;`
  line
  line `(zl) the manner of self-assessment of cess under sub-section (1) of section 103;`
  line
  line `(zm) the authority to inquire and impose penalty under section 104;`
  line
  line `(zn) time limit to prefer appeal, appellate authority, form and manner of appeal under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 105;`
  line
  line `(zo) manner of registration as beneficiary under section 106;`
  line
  line `(zp) benefits of a beneficiary under sub-section (2) of section 107;`
  line
  line `(zq) eligible age for registration under clause (a) and form and manner of information under clause`
  line `(b), of sub-section (1) and the form of application, documents for registration and manner of self`
  line `registration under sub-section (2), of section 113;`
  line
  line `(zr) carrying out the matters specified in clause (i) of sub-section (7) of section 114;`
  line
  line `(zs) manner of compounding of offences under sub-section (1) of section 138;`
  line
  line `(zt) the manner of establishment and administration of the Social Security Fund under sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 141;`
  line
  line `(zu) eligibility conditions to be fulfilled prior to grant of exemption and the conditions to be complied`
  line `with after exemption under sub-section (1); and extension period of exemption under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 143; and`
  line
  line `(zv) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed by the Central Government under`
  line `the provisions of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (54180)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Power of state Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54180&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `and subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules not inconsistent with this Code, for the`
  line `purpose of giving effect to the provisions thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of exercising the powers and performance of functions by State Unorganised Workers'`
  line `Board under sub-section (9), the manner of nomination of members of the Board, their term of office`
  line `and other conditions of service, the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions by, and`
  line `the manner of filling vacancies among the members of, the Board under sub-section (12), and the time,`
  line `place and rules of procedure relating to the transaction of business at its meetings under sub-section`
  line `(14) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of appointment and the salaries and other allowances payable to the`
  line `chairperson and the other members of the Building Workers' Welfare Board and the manner of filling`
  line `of casual vacancies of such members, under sub-section (4), the terms and conditions of appointment`
  line `and the salary and allowances payable to the Secretary and the other officers and employees of the said`
  line `Board under clause (c) of sub-section (5) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) procedure to be followed by the Employees' Insurance Court under sub-section (2) and the rules`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 50;`
  line
  line `(d) the amount to be deposited towards the expenditure of the funeral of the employee with the`
  line `competent authority by the employer under sub-section (7) of section 76;`
  line
  line `(e) conditions when application for review is made without certificate of a medical practitioner under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 79;`
  line
  line `(f) the frequent interval for medical examination under the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 84;`
  line
  line `(g) the form of statement to be submitted by the employer under sub-section (1) of section 88;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which matters may be dealt with by or before a competent authority under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 92;`
  line
  line `(i) time-limit for disposal of application and costs incidental to the proceedings under sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 93;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of authentication of memorandum under section 97;`
  line
  line `(k) such other sources of funding and the manner of administering and expending of the fund under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 141; and`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed by the State Government under the`
  line `provisions of this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (54181)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Power of corporation to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54181&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may, by notification, and`
  line `subject to the condition of previous publication, make regulations, not inconsistent with this Code and the`
  line `rules and schemes made or framed thereunder, for the administration of the affairs of the Corporation and`
  line `for carrying into effect the provisions of Chapter IV and the provisions of this Code relating to that Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the cases and matters to be submitted for the decision of the Corporation under clause (b) of subsection (4) and the composition of committees under sub-section (6) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the areas in respect of which the Corporation may appoint Regional Boards and local committees`
  line `and the manner in which such Boards and committees shall perform the functions and exercise the`
  line `powers under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) such other functions of the Director General and the Financial Commissioner under sub-section`
  line `(4), the method of recruitment, salary and allowances, discipline and other conditions of service of the`
  line `officers and employees under clause (a) of sub-section (8) and minimum qualifying service for`
  line `promotion to next higher grade under the second proviso to sub-section (9) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(d) the unit in respect of which all contribution shall be payable under sub-section (3), and the days`
  line `on which the contributions shall fall due under sub-section (4) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(e) maintenance of register of employees by or through the contractor under sub-section (7), and any`
  line `matter relating or incidental to the payment and collection of contribution under sub-section (9) of`
  line `section 31;`
  line
  line `(f) qualifications and experience of other person to certify sickness under clause (a), authority to`
  line `certify eligibility of a woman under clause (b), authority to certify eligibility for payment under clause`
  line `(c) of sub-section (1), the conditions for extension of medical benefits under sub-section (2) and any`
  line `matter relating or incidental to the accrual and payment of benefits under sub-section (4) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(g) continuous period in which the employee contracts occupational disease under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 36;`
  line
  line `(h) constitution of medical board under sub-section (1) and constitution of medical appeal tribunal`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 37;`
  line
  line `(i) the period and the nature of medical benefit which may be allowed to a person under the first`
  line `proviso, conditions for voluntary retirement scheme under the second proviso, payment of contribution`
  line `and other conditions for eligibility to receive medical benefits under the second proviso and the`
  line `conditions for grant of medical benefits to the Insured Person during employment injury under the`
  line `fourth proviso, to sub-section (3), the time for which students of medical education institutions shall serve the Corporation and the manner in which the bond shall be furnished under clause (b) of subsection (4) and manner of carrying out occupational and epidemiological surveys and studies for`
  line `assessment of health and working conditions of Insured Persons under sub-section (6) of section 39;`
  line
  line `(j) other authority for providing permission to leave the area in which medical treatment provided`
  line `under clause (c) of sub-section (3), form of nomination under sub-section (6) and the authority to`
  line `determine benefits under sub-section (9) of section 41;`
  line
  line `(k) user charges to be paid by other beneficiaries for medical facilities under clause (c) of the`
  line `Explanation to section 44;`
  line
  line `(l) time within which the claims, recovery or contribution, from employer by the Corporation and`
  line `recovery of contribution by the employer from the Contractor, shall be made under the second proviso`
  line `to sub-section (1) of section 51;`
  line
  line `(m) the forms of records and registers and of returns to be filed under the second proviso to clause`
  line `(d) of section 123;`
  line
  line `(n) the appellate authority not below the rank of the Joint Director of the Corporation before whom`
  line `appeal shall be preferred and the interest to be refunded to the employer by the Corporation under`
  line `section 126;`
  line
  line `(o) manner of levy and recovery of damages from the employer who makes default in the payment`
  line `of any contribution which he is liable to pay under section 128;`
  line
  line `(p) the circumstances in which and the condition subject to which any regulation may be relaxed, the`
  line `extent of such relaxation, and the authority by whom such relaxation may be granted; and`
  line
  line `(q) any matter in respect of which regulations are required or permitted to be made by this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (54182)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Prior publication of rules, regulations, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54182&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `The power to make rules, regulations and schemes`
  line `under this Code (except the schemes to be framed under Chapter III), shall be subject to the condition of`
  line `the previous publication of the same being made, in the following manner, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the date to be specified after a draft of such rules, regulations and schemes under consideration,`
  line `shall not be less than forty-five days from the date on which the draft of the proposed rules, regulations`
  line `and schemes is published for general information in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(b) such rules, regulations and schemes shall finally be published in the Official Gazette and, on`
  line `such publication, shall have effect as if enacted in this Code:`
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, in the circumstances of epidemic, pandemic or disaster,`
  line `dispense with the condition of previous publication under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (54437)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Rules to give effect to arrangements with other countries for the transfer of money paid as compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54437&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make rules for the transfer to any`
  line `foreign country of money deposited with a competent authority under Chapter VII which has been awarded`
  line `to or may be due to, any person residing or about to reside in such foreign country and for the receipt,`
  line `distribution and administration in any State of any money deposited under the law relating to employees'`
  line `compensation in any foreign country, which has been awarded to, or may be due to any person residing or`
  line `about to reside in any State:`
  line
  line `Provided that no sum deposited under Chapter VII in respect of fatal accidents shall be so transferred`
  line `without the consent of the employer concerned after the competent authority receiving the sum has passed`
  line `orders determining its distribution and apportionment under section 81.`
  line
  line `(2) Where money deposited with a competent authority has been so transferred in accordance with the`
  line `rules made under this section, the provisions elsewhere contained in this Code regarding distribution by the`
  line `competent authority of compensation deposited with him shall cease to apply in respect of any such money.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (54184)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Laying of rules, regulations and schemes, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54184&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every rule, regulation, notification and`
  line `scheme made or framed by the Central Government or the Corporation, as the case may be, under this Code`
  line `shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made or framed, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive`
  line `sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule, regulation, notification or`
  line `scheme, as the case may be, or both Houses agree that the rule, regulation, notification or scheme, as the`
  line `case may be, should not be made, such rule, regulation, notification or scheme shall thereafter have effect`
  line `only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification`
  line `or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule,`
  line `regulation, notification or scheme, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule and scheme made or framed, and every notification issued by, the State Government`
  line `under this Code, shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made or framed, before the State Legislatures,`
  line `where it consists of two Houses, or where such legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (54185)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Effect of laws and agreements inconsistent with this code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54185&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Code`
  line `shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, or in the terms of any award, agreement or contract of service, whether made before or after`
  line `the coming into force of this Code:`
  line
  line `Provided that where under any such award, agreement, contract of service or otherwise, a person is`
  line `entitled to benefits in respect of any matter which are more favourable to him than those to which he would`
  line `be entitled under this Code, the person shall continue to be entitled to the more favourable benefits in respect`
  line `of that matter, notwithstanding that he is entitled to receive benefits in respect of other matters under this`
  line Code.
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in this Code shall be construed to preclude a person from entering into an`
  line `agreement with his employer for granting him rights or privileges in respect of any matter which are more`
  line `favourable to him than those to which he would be entitled under this Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (54186)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54186&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `The appropriate Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers and functions which may be exercised or performed by that Government may, in relation to`
  line `such matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified, be also exercisable by the Central`
  line `Board, the Corporation, the National Social Security Board, the State Unorganised Workers' Board,`
  line `Building Workers' Welfare Board or any officer or authority subordinate to the Central Board, the`
  line `Corporation, the National Social Security Board, the State Unorganised Workers' Board, Building Workers'`
  line `Welfare Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (54187)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54187&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Code, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Code, as may be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years`
  line `from the commencement of this Code.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (54188)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799&sectionId=54188&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_6_0_00036_202036_1623221080799
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following enactments are hereby repealed, namely:—`
  line
  line `1. The Employee's Compensation Act, 1923 (8 of 1923);`
  line
  line `2. The Employees' State Insurance Act, 1948 (34 of 1948);`
  line
  line `3. The Employees' Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952);`
  line
  line `4. The Employment Exchanges (Compulsory Notification of Vacancies) Act, 1959 (31 of 1959);`
  line
  line `5. The Maternity Benefit Act, 1961 (53 of 1961) ;`
  line
  line `6. The Payment of Gratuity Act, 1972 (39 of 1972);`
  line
  line `7. The Cine-Workers Welfare Fund Act, 1981 (33 of 1981);`
  line
  line `8. The Building and Other Construction Workers' Welfare Cess Act, 1996 (28 of 1996);`
  line
  line `9. The Unorganised Workers' Social Security Act, 2008 (33 of 2008).`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,—`
  line
  line `(a) anything done or any action taken under the enactments so repealed including any rule, regulation,`
  line `notification (including the notifications issued by the States), scheme, appointment, order or direction`
  line `made thereunder or any benefit provided or given under any provision of such enactments, rules,`
  line `regulations, notifications or schemes made thereunder for any purpose shall be deemed to have been`
  line `done or taken or provided for such purpose under the corresponding provisions of this Code including`
  line `any rule, regulation, notification, scheme, appointment, order or direction made thereunder and shall`
  line `be in force to the extent they are not contrary to the provisions of this Code including any rule,`
  line `regulation, notification, scheme, appointment, order or direction made thereunder till they are repealed`
  line `under the corresponding provisions of this Code including any rule, regulation, notification, scheme,`
  line `appointment, order or direction made thereunder by the appropriate Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the Employees' Provident Funds Scheme, 1952, the Employees' Deposit Linked Insurance`
  line `Scheme, 1976, the Employees' Pension Scheme, 1995 and the Tribunal (Procedure) Rules, 1997 framed`
  line `or made under the Employees' Provident Funds and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952 (19 of 1952)`
  line `and the rules, regulations and schemes made or framed under the Employees' State Insurance Act, 1948`
  line `(34 of 1948), shall remain in force, to the extent they are not inconsistent with the provisions of this`
  line `Code for a period of one year from the date of commencement of this Code;`
  line
  line `(c) any exemption given under any enactments so repealed shall continue to be in force till its validity`
  line `expires or it ceases to be in operation under the provisions of this Code or till any direction is made`
  line `thereunder for such purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), the provisions of section 6 of the General`
  line `Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) shall apply to the repeal of such enactments.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
